description:
Say yay to free food! So happy to win this awesome japanese claypot rice from @donabe.sg 
We had Kinoko (mushroom delight), the vegetarian choice. Its so flavourful that we forgot that there is no meat inside 😂

Finally tried Egg Slut! The queue was insane even on a weekday morning. But luckily I still manage to get in within 10mins.. I had Fairfax (SGD12) which consists of scrambled eggs (with caramelized onions), cheddar cheese, drizzled with sriracha mayonnaise. I wished that the eggs were more creamy and fluffy though. You can also add patty for another SGD4 and truffle hash browns for SGD4.50, just like what I did 😌 these 2 are not bad. Worth ordering. Total damage for this meal was SGD20.50, which I think is too expensive for a breakfast! Try 一次就好😅

〜屋台料理　其の120〜🤤🤤🤤
Beef Brisket Noodle @Uncle Lee's Hong Kong Noodle & Rice
S$4.00 

Scrumptious Breakfast! 

This stall is famous for soya sauce chicken dishes. But what I wanna recommend is his beef brisket! The flavor of the soy sauce has soaked right in. The meat melts in my mouth. Goes well with chewy noodles.

このオッチャンの店は醤油ベースのチキンが有名。でも個人的にオススメなのがビーフのブリスケット。醤油味がしみてて口ん中でとろけるほど柔らかい。コシのある麺ともよく合う。美味しい！

📍Kazo

// 𝒕𝒂𝒓𝒐 𝒐𝒓𝒉 𝒏𝒆𝒆 𝒕𝒂𝒓𝒕 // 𝟹.𝟼𝟶

Taro lovers rejoice! ✨

This orh nee tart comes with a h u g e dollop of the taro cream paste, that is so delightful paired with the buttery and flaky cookie crust! 😋 It’s also topped with a ginko nut to complete the orh nee dessert experience. I like how the sweetness is just right even though there’s A LOT of filling. But gotta say that it would even be better if the taro taste is more prominent - it’s more coconutty now. 

Verdict: 3/5 
Sweetness: 4/5

Address: 200 Victoria Street, B1-K04, Bugis Junction, Singapore 188021
🕒 Mon to Sun, 10am to 9.30pm (10pm on Fri and Sat) 
Nearest🚇: Bugis

📍GelatiAmo OneNorth

// 𝒘𝒂𝒇𝒇𝒍𝒆𝒔 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 2 𝒔𝒄𝒐𝒐𝒑𝒔 (𝒑𝒊𝒔𝒕𝒂𝒄𝒉𝒊𝒐 & 𝒔𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒘𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒓𝒚 𝒚𝒐𝒈𝒖𝒓𝒕 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒄𝒆𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒍𝒔) // 𝟷𝟹.𝟷𝟶

Omg I think I found my fave waffles + gelato place! The pistachio gelato is really the best I’ve ever had, and it’s so affordably priced, as compared to other cafes! Yogurt strawberry with cereals is really an amazing combo, so refreshing and just the right sourness. The cereal crunch gave the scoop extra crunch ❤️ Served with warm waffles that’s so crispy on the outside yet soft and fluffy on the inside, this is really the most wonderful dessert I’ve had in a while. Would totally come back to try all their other creations! 🧇🍨

// 𝒔𝒒𝒖𝒂𝒓𝒆 𝒄𝒊𝒏𝒏𝒂𝒎𝒐𝒏 𝒅𝒐𝒏𝒖𝒕 // 𝟸.𝟻𝟶

We also tried the super cute square shaped donut that was dusted with cinnamon sugar. The donut was so delicious! It’s chewy and surprisingly, not too sweet. You can choose to have it warmed up too. 🍩😋

Verdict: 4.5/5 
Ambiance: Aesthetic, photo-worthy, minimalistic, super friendly service 

Address: 1 Fusionopolis Way, Connexis B1-11, 138632
🕒 Mon to Sat, 11am to 8.30pm Sun, 2pm to 8.30pm 
Nearest🚇: One North

description:
📍Brotherbird Coffeehouse @brotherbird_bakehouse 

// 𝒔𝒊𝒈𝒏𝒂𝒕𝒖𝒓𝒆 𝒎𝒐𝒄𝒉𝒊 𝒅𝒐𝒏𝒖𝒕 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒕𝒂𝒓𝒐 𝒔𝒐𝒇𝒕 𝒔𝒆𝒓𝒗𝒆 // 𝟷𝟻.𝟶

Came for the Jan-exclusive taro (orh-nee) soft serve! Mochi lovers would adore the chewiness of the donut and I appreciated that it was not oily at all! The mochi donut was served slightly warm and it paired SO WELL with the taro soft serve omgosh 🥰 The taro flavour isn’t too overwhelming, I thought it could have been just a little stronger. There’s also boba and lil bits of granola (??) served together that gives the dessert a good crunch and texture. 🧋 The only sad thing is that the soft serve melted very quickly so there’s really not much time to slowly devour it after taking photos haha :’) 

The cafe interior is really chill and it’s a very lovely place to hangout. There’s a variety of pastries (croissants, cruffins etc.), savoury mains (pastas) and drinks available. Would totally come back again for their monthly specials! ✨ 

Verdict: 4/5 
Ambiance: minimalistic, chill, clean and quiet 

Address: 32 Bali Ln, Singapore 189868
🕒 Wed to Sun, 10am to 6pm (dine-in) Mon & Tue, 10am to 4pm (takeaway) 
Nearest🚇: Bugis

《Mini Shrimp Rolls》

Don’t let the prices of lobsters get you down. These mini shrimp rolls are equally yummy as a quick n easy treat at home! If you are intending to make it, tag me and let me know if you like it! 😉

250g cooked shrimp, chopped 
70g mayonnaise 
Handful of chopped spring onion and dills
Juice from 1/2 lemon
Salt and pepper to taste 
6 mantou, pan-fry till golden OR spray some oil before popping them in airfyer at 180°c for 3-5 min on both side

Need some 🔥 to kick start a new week!
Who else is eating curry fish head today? 🙋🏻‍♀️

#CurryFishHead
#MadeInStaub

Just as I was craving some delicious dessert on a hot and lazy afternoon, @longchengdesserts delivered these yummy handmade dessert right to my doorstep!

🌟Beauty Collagen
Swipe to check out this super refreshing dessert that comes with lots of nutritious and nourishing ingredients in a bowl. Every spoonful is a tasting pleasure in the mouth 😋 
Hubby was very impressed by it and kept praising 有惊喜 as he initially thought these are just the usual cheng tng 😅

🌟Almond dessert / Almond dessert w tangyuan
Both almond paste came chilled and I heated the one with tangyuan in the microwave for 1-2min with stirring in between. The almond paste is creamy n smooth while the tangyuan are chewy and soft, bursting with my favourite peanut and black sesame filling in it. 

I love it that all desserts are freshly made, mildly-sweetened, no preservatives and no artificial flavouring 💯 

Thank you @longchengdesserts and @liveloveatwithjie for hosting this nutritious giveaway! Definitely going to order more for my family from the very friendly owner! Keep up the good work!👏
#supportsmallbusinesssg

So full from economic fried bee hoon breakfast this morning at @yiqifa.beehoon !

We ordered both the fried and white bee hoon, added fish fillet, French beans, cabbage, fried chicken wings, and fried beancurd skin aka zai er. Wanted to add otah and ikan billis too but told myself I should save it for the next visit 😅#greedyme 

We prefer the fried bee hoon which is flavourful and not oily, and the portion is really generous!

Zai er is very crispy and addictive, so are the fried chicken wings! And I finished all the chili on my plate as well as hubby’s 👍 

Don’t miss out on getting a cup of hot coffee from the FoodFare drinks stall to pair with your fried bee hoon - hubby approved! That teh-o kosong was mine.

Thank you @chiaksimi for recommending and hosting this giveaway with @yiqifa.beehoon 
I get to say hi to the friendly couple @foodiecouplecm in person too!

description:
Good food,good ambience, good time!
The recipe for a Great Weekend! 
#greatweekend

I found this restaurant while looking for Nice Japanese food with Great Ambience. JYPSY at Martin Road is the concept created by the people behind PS.Cafe. With a menu of Japanese inspired delights, this restaurant is a must-try for those who enjoy a contemporary take on classic cuisine. The restaurant concept is a beautifully unique setting that takes inspiration from coastal fishing villages, blended into a contemporary chic environment. They are moving soon to new flaship at One Fullerton & their last day (23.01.2022)at 38Martin Road.

We tried the Salmon Tacos ($15), Classic Sashimi 9 pcs ($28) & Wagyu Beef Fried Rice ($26) & Nests of Fries($11) .For the drink we tried glass of Rose' Wine ($17).

Tacos is a must try, with cripsy seaweed & inside they put a lot salmon chunks with wasabi sauce on top. Squeeze a little bit of lemon & damn thats really delicious. For the sahimi, it's so so for me. Omg for Beef Fried Rice, grilled meat is juicy & with kombu butter fried japanese rice, it's the nxt lvl kind of fried rice, super tasty. For the Nests of Fries, I want to try it out cuz almost every table they ordered this. I must say that's alot of Fries & 2 person cannot finished it 😅.

📍Nearest MRT: Fort Canning MRT
⭐: 4/5
💸: $$

Vegetarian Bibimbap “Yu Sheng” 韩式拌饭”鱼生”

Ain’t having bibimbap liked 捞鱼生? The vibrant colours, the lovely vegetables and of course the delicious sauce to round it all up. Instead of usual yusheng plum sauce, i concocted a Gochujang lemon dressing. It’s spicy,tangy and very appetising. I’ve too infused the rice with fresh lemongrass, kaffir lime leaves, I bet you don’t even need me to tell you how fragrant this combi are 😋😋😋😋 

BIBIMBAP INGREDIENTS
🍀Rice @royalumbrellasg (add lemongrass and kaffir lime leaves)
🍀kimchi carrots
🍀pickled cucumbers
🍀edamame
🍀Black fungus (soy sauce and rice vinegar dressing)
🍀Sautéed King oyster mushroom

GOCHUJANG LEMON DRESSING
🍀Gochujang sauce
🍀green lemon juice
🍀Mirin
🍀Sakae

Ps: ain’t that tableware GORGEOUS?!!! It’s older than me btw 🤪

🇸🇬 Today I will share with you one place selling modern style of bak chor mee named Gimee Face Noodle House which is located around Hougang Village area, to be exact is inside the same place as Li Fatt Wanton Noodle.

Why do I call it modern style of bak chor mee? It’s because of their toppings that they put for this bak chor mee. 

I ordered Gimee Face Noodle House’s most favourite and most recommended menu which is Abalone Pork Noodle ($6.80). 

Abalone Pork Noodle consist of noodle (mee pok), abalone, Hanjuku eggs, pork slices, minced pork, pork liver, meatball, fishball, braised shiitake and button mushrooms. What a luxurious toppings, right? 

The highlight of this Abalone Pork Noodle is the Abalone because it’s really seldom for noodle shop having Abalone as their noodle topping.

This Abalone Pork Noodle is surprisingly very savoury and tastyyyyy.

Even though I did take away, the taste of this noodle was still yummy without mistake.

I really like this noodle taste. I do believe once you try it, you will definitely like it.

🇸🇬 Calling out all coconut water lovers!  Do you like to drink coconut water? For me, I like it because coconut water is cooling, will reduce heartiness from your body and it will cure food poisoning.

I know these coconut water benefits because I experienced it before (when I stay in Jakarta). Coconut water is also good for skin. 

Speaking of coconut water, yesterday I went to NTUC FairPrice Waterway Point and found out that they currently have a promotion of buy three CocoThumb for only $5.95. Original price for each CocoThumb is $3.90. 

What a great deal, right? 

This CocoThumb appearance is unique because the coconut water is still inside the fruit. CocoThumb also contains pure coconut water from Namhom coconut tree.

So how to drink it? Do we need to open it ourself using knive? No need. By doing three step instructions from them, you can drink this coconut water: pull the red seal, push the top tube and insert the straw provided inside the tube. 

Fyi, you need to push the top tube a bit hard to make a hole on the coconut shell. 

This coconut water is refreshing. The downsides are it’s a bit hard to push the top tube, this CocoThumb is very bulky & heavy to hand carried and you cannot eat the coconut flesh unless you open it yourself using knive (I would not recommend this as coconut shell is normally super hard).

Other than those downsides, this CocoThumb is a good option to satisfy your coconut water craving.

🇸🇬 Today I will share with you one random bread shop that I visited because I was attracted by the old looking model signboard while exploring Hougang Village.

The name of this bread shop is Hong Kao Liao Li.

After observing all of their breads and snacks that they sell, I am interested in trying their Tapioca Cake.  So, I bought two pieces of Tapioca Cake.

The size of this Tapioca Cake is quite big and the appearance quite makes me drooling (especially the one that has a bit burnt on the side).

This Tapioca Cake is sweet, actually it might be a bit too sweet for people who don’t like sweet snack. For me, the sweetness level is still okay.

Overall I like this Tapioca Cake. I do believe people who stay nearby there also like this Tapioca Cake as in that time (around 11AM) only two pieces of Tapioca cake left before I bought it.

🇸🇬 I recently went to Hougang Village by taking the bus from bus interchange near Hougang MRT station.

When I got there, I passed by one hawker centre and saw super long queue line in front of noodle stall named Li Fatt Wanton Noodle.

Because of my curiosity, I decided to join the queue. 

Fyi, Li Fatt Wanton Noodle is selling five different types of noodle: Wanton Noodle, Fried Wanton Noodle, Shredded Chicken Noodle, Dumpling Noodle and Chicken Feet Noodle.

Each of the noodles types have two different prices: $3.50 and $4.50.

You can also request to add-on other toppings with additional price.

I ordered Wanton Noodle ($4.50) with additional Chicken Feet (2 pieces for $1.50) to take away.

This wanton noodle consists of noodle with charsiew, steamed wanton, green vegetables and chicken feet. Because the price is $4.50, this noodle portion is super a lot.

Wanton noodle taste is similar like the old school wanton noodle taste. It’s deliciously good.

The noodle texture and taste is nice.

The charsiew is quite a lot and tender.

Steamed wanton noodle is also delicious.

Chicken feet is quite huge and I like it. 

No wonder this wanton noodle stall has a lot of fans (based on the queue line). Li Fatt Wanton Noodle could be said as a hidden gem wanton noodle stall.

Overall I am really pleased trying this wanton noodle and I recommend you to try if you are nearby.

🇸🇬 Today I will share with you one of egg tart brands that I occasionally buy whenever their temporary booth is inside the mall. 

This egg tart shop name is Madeleine’s Original Portuguese Egg Tart & Puff.

I purchased one box of six pieces of Portuguese Egg Tart.

Fyi, Portuguese Egg Tart is different from the Chinese Egg Tart. Portuguese Egg Tart is using puff pastries to make the skin casing, so the texture becomes like crunchy puff skin. It’s also baked until the top of the custard’s egg tart is scorched. Normally Portuguese Egg Tart’s custard is creamier than Chinese Egg Tart.

I actually like both of the egg tarts version, but Portuguese Egg Tart will give you a better crunchy bite texture sensation when you chew it.

This Madeleine’s Original Portuguese Egg Tart is yummy and the custard is not too sweet. The skin casing is also crunchy.

I like this Portuguese egg tart 😊. So if you find their booth inside the mall, you have to try this Madeleine’s Original Portuguese Egg Tart & Puff 😊.

description:
𝐆𝐞𝐭 𝐚 𝐭𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐀𝐬𝐢𝐚'𝐬 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐆𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐭 𝐇𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐂𝐮𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬 𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫 𝐎𝐍𝐄 𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐟 𝐚𝐭 @lot10hutong 💯 

🍝 𝚂𝚒𝚐𝚗𝚊𝚝𝚞𝚛𝚎 𝙷𝚘𝚔𝚔𝚒𝚎𝚗 𝙼𝚎𝚎
One of my childhood favourite is this slurping good, saucy dish starring thick yellow noodles lusciously braised in a tantalisingly thick dark soy sauce with pork, fish cake, cabbage and often times with crispy cubes of pork lard. 🤤 

🐓 𝙲𝚕𝚊𝚢𝚙𝚘𝚝 𝙲𝚑𝚒𝚌𝚔𝚎𝚗 𝚁𝚒𝚌𝚎
It’s been agessssss since I last eaten #claypotchickenrice 😆. Dig all the way to the bottom and scrape those smoky, burnt grains of rice off the sides and mix it all up cause that’s what makes claypot chicken rice unique! 👌 Nestled in the heap of aromatic, seasoned charred rice are chicken chunks, Chinese sausages, dried mushrooms and pungent salted fish that gives this dish the flavour factor 🔥. 

🦆 𝙱𝚛𝚊𝚒𝚜𝚎𝚍 𝙳𝚞𝚌𝚔 𝚁𝚒𝚌𝚎
Roast duck is more common to me hence I was interested to try this #braisedduck . Pretty tender and tasty, where you can order a single portion with rice instead of a whole duck if you haven’t got much tummy space 👍 

🐖 𝙱𝚊𝚔 𝙺𝚞𝚝 𝚃𝚎𝚑 𝙽𝚘𝚘𝚍𝚕𝚎 
Another childhood favourite of mine is #bakkutteh where it’s usually served in the same steaming hot pot that’s cooked over the stovetop. The intensity and taste of the broth varies across places, where you also get to choose your cut of pork but this was an individual portion served with dry-based noodles soused in soy sauce and a separate light tasting soup swimming with tender pork, beancurd and mushrooms. 

🥟 𝙶𝚒𝚊𝚗𝚝 𝚂𝚝𝚎𝚊𝚖 𝙿𝚘𝚛𝚔 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝙲𝚑𝚒𝚌𝚔𝚎𝚗 𝙱𝚞𝚗
Have you seen such a girnormous bao? It’s literally translated to Big Bao in English and you’ll find a delicious potpourri of tender pork, chicken, dried mushroom & hard boiled egg all densely stuffed in the fluffy, soft, snowy white steamed bun 😍.

☕️ 𝙲𝚘𝚏𝚏𝚎𝚎 
🥤 𝙱𝚊𝚛𝚕𝚎𝚢 
🥤 𝙷𝚎𝚛𝚋𝚊𝚕 𝚝𝚎𝚊 

Check out @lot10hutong where you can taste tonnes of local Asian dishes from numerous vendors without the need to travel everywhere (and there’s air conditioning too)! 😉 

Thanks @lot10hutong for the invite! 😊

What happens when #PancakeDay falls on #TacoTuesday ? 🥞 + 🌮 

Get some #PancakeTacos from @yellowbrickroadcafe 👌 

🐮🥞 𝙋𝙪𝙡𝙡𝙚𝙙 𝘽𝙚𝙚𝙛 𝙋𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙖𝙠𝙚 𝙏𝙖𝙘𝙤𝙨
Thin tortilla tacos substituted with scrumptiously soft, fluffy pancakes folded with a moreish mishmash of flavourful, tender pulled beef, juicy portobello mushrooms, kale, cherry tomatoes before showering it with grated parmesan and a delicious drizzle of piquant Thai mayo 🔥 

🥞🍵 𝙂𝙧𝙚𝙚𝙣 𝙀𝙮𝙚𝙨 𝙈𝙤𝙣𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙧
If the theatrics of that amazing avalanche didn’t make you drool, let me assure you that every mouthful of this lavish lava #pancake stack was utterly decadent! 😍 
Thick, toothsome biscoff spread slathered between three delectably dense yet fluffy pancakes awaiting to be engulfed by the resplendently rich, mouthwatering mascarpone cream infused with robustly fragrant green tea coconut notes 🤩 . And it doesn’t end there, where the creative accompaniments of crispy soft golden banana fritters, tangy mix-berries compote powder, fresh strawberries and yummy cookie crumbs elevated the entire dish to a whole new level 💯.

🍝 𝙐𝙣𝙖𝙜𝙞 𝙈𝙚𝙣𝙩𝙖𝙞𝙠𝙤 𝙋𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙖
Pancakes here are a must but their fantastic fusion pastas are incredible too! Wowed by the explosion of heavenly flavours embodied within this unpretentious  looking dish. Flying off the charts with an unimaginable umami kick was the silky, smooth al dente spaghetti soused in a remarkably rich, creamy mentaiko sauce and topped with that gloriously glazed, sexy slab of sweet, salty, oh so umami unagi that was just so tantalisingly tender with a pleasant chew 🤤🤤🤤. Tossed with succulent  shiitake mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, where the heaviness was alleviated by the briny balance of petite popping pearls of fish roe 💯.

🍵 𝙈𝙖𝙩𝙘𝙝𝙖 𝙃𝙤𝙪𝙟𝙞𝙘𝙝𝙖 𝙏𝙖𝙧𝙩
Tried their #matchatart before and I loved it and this seasonal Christmas tart with an additional nuttiness from the roasty hojicha was even better 💚💚💚

🍹𝙁𝙚𝙨𝙩𝙞𝙫𝙚 𝙁𝙧𝙪𝙞𝙩 𝙋𝙪𝙣𝙘𝙝
Refreshing with all that punchy zest from the raspberry cold brew tea mingling with lemon juice, white peach, yuzu and rosemary 🤩 

🍫 𝙄𝙘𝙚 𝘾𝙝𝙤𝙘𝙤𝙡𝙖𝙩𝙚

📍 jecs.sg (hbb)⁣
⁣
got their 6” original burnt cheesecake during their crazy 11.11 sale (paid $11! u.p. $45 😮) and had absolutely zero regrets. looked and tasted really good — smooth and creamy with a richness to it which i prefer compared to other cheesecakes that would just taste like milk more than anything. also, adding the base was a genius idea; there was a buttery textural contrast with every bite which made it more addictive. overall, i’d recommmend @jecs.sg if you’re looking for a solid cheesecake in general because it’d please both burnt cheesecake and classic new york style cheesecake lovers!⁣
⁣
rating: 8/10

📍 chuan yang ji mutton soup steamboat⁣
🚌 whampoa / balestier⁣
⁣
Merry Christmas everyone 🦃 They serve some amazing mutton here!!! I’ve always shied away from ordering mutton because they usually have a less pleasant gamey smell which most people would also know about. But not here!!!! Idk how they do it but the mutton is so tender and slightly chewy with barely any hint of gaminess at all, if you didn’t tell me I was eating mutton I’d probably guess that it was pork/beef.⁣
⁣
Definitely try the Grilled Lamb Chop 烤羊排 ($6 for members, $8 otherwise) it’s really amazing 😭 and not to mention well seasoned too! The normal mutton skewers go for $1.30/stick ($2.50 for non members). They also have ala carte noodle dishes for $8.50 which is pretty affordable imo, and signing up as a member entitles you to member pricing/discounts = more savings 🥳⁣
⁣
rating: 9/10 (that grilled lamb…<3)

📍 kim dae mun⁣⁣
🚌 dhoby ghaut/somerset

come here for affordable korean food in town!! super wallet friendly; basically everything is under $10. have to preface that I rarely eat korean cuisine so I can’t compare these to those in food courts but in general, I felt that everything was pretty good!⁣
⁣
Garlic & Chives Pancake ($4.50)⁣
with crisp edges and soft doughy middles, I thought this was worth the price given its portion, but if kimchi was mixed in too it’d be even better!⁣
⁣
Egg Roll ($3)⁣
I really liked this even though it’s just eggs LOL. soft and light, easy to pop into your mouth in between bites of the main dishes.⁣
⁣
Korean Beef Soup ($9)⁣
was surprised to see the generous amount of ingredients in the bowl, from glass noodles to tofu and veggies apart from the beef itself. plus ordering this already gets u a bowl of rice & side to begin with! while the meat was average, the soup was warm and hearty and i finished every drop. ⁣
⁣
Spicy Pork ($9.50)⁣
my favourite out of everything we got! the meat was tender with a chew, sauce was spicy and sweet. a classic done well.⁣
⁣
overall, their food feels really homely and comforting to me and I love how communal the whole set up is HAHA it’s like a canteen! though the queue can be long during peak hours, it’s constantly moving and service remains upbeat. some may find it overrated but personally I’d say the hype is justified!⁣
⁣
rating: 8/10

📍 the summer acai⁣
🚌  kovan⁣
⁣
so glad I caught their 1f1 opening promo last week bc they’re at the top of my personal acai ranking along w/ coocaça rn 🤩 even without the discount, these are extremely worth the price with very generous portions!!! the acai base was really tasty (quite similar to AAA i feel) and not icy/diluted while the toppings were fresh and I love how they give waay more fruits (and everything in general lol) compared to other brands 👀 also special mention to their yuzu sorbet it’s sooo good, slightly citrusy but not too sour. the lemon sorbet on the other hand was too sour for my liking but my friend preferred this over the yuzu, so it really comes down to your own preference!⁣
⁣

📍 two men bagel house⁣⁣
🚌 novena⁣
⁣
the last time I ate tmbh was 2 years ago on the day As ended... only a few days ago did I finally feel rich enough to eat here again 💀 They used to have ala carte customisation options which I found to be more worth but now I don’t see them on the menu anymore?

𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐁𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐥 𝐰/ 𝐒𝐦𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐝 𝐌𝐚𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐏𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦 𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐞𝐬𝐞⁣ ⁣ ⁣ 
($𝟔++)⁣
Amazing!!! The cc tastes exactly as its name suggests, a little caramel-y with a hint of smokiness. Loved the nuttiness and crunch from the pecans! Went so well with the sweet bagel which guys I brought home, scraped off the cc before toasting it and omg I encountered my first love (bagel version) it was crispy and crunchy on the exterior but soft yet chewy inside… and those warm bursts of blueberries… with the cold cream cheese…🧎🏻‍♀️ ⁣
⁣
𝐒𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐲 𝐁𝐞𝐬𝐭 ($𝟏𝟑++)⁣
Fennel sausage, sunny, cheddar, hash, onion marmalade, smoked garlic aioli.⁣
The fennel sausage was pretty frickin delicious but a taaad salty. On the whole quite a heavy bagel so it’d be better to share with a friend (which if you don’t alr exchange half your bagel with your friend’s for ✨variety✨ , you’re doing it wrong).⁣

𝐁𝐞𝐜𝐤𝐢𝐞 ($𝟏𝟑++)⁣
House smoked bacon, scrambled eggs, cheddar, spicy ketchup.⁣
I preferred this over Sunday Best mainly because of the spicy ketchup it was so good for some reason LOL and it’s *the* BEC combi, you just can’t go wrong with classics!⁣
⁣
Overall, they serve up really good bagels with choices that can definitely give indecisive people (re: Me) a hard time. But honestly I feel that it’s overpriced like most sandwich places (K***o) are these days 😭 Like it’s supposed to be casual takeaway kinda food but comes w cafe price tag (adding gst+svc, some are almost $20) without the same ambience/svc which rly dissuades me from coming even tho the food is great!!! But bagels are not easy to make at all and everything is expensive nowadays… will just blame it on inflation 👍🏻⁣
⁣
rating: 8/10⁣

We came here over the weekend. It was our first visit to Le Shrimp🦐 and not knowing what to order, we went with the friendly service staff’s recommendations and ordered the following dishes:

🧡Mapo Tofu with Minced Shrimp Ramen🍜 - Seasonal Special. I totally adored the dry ramen tossed in the aromatic and spicy mala sauce, along with yummy ingredients like the firm tofu cubes, fried beancurd crisps, Sichuan pickled vegetables and fresh minced shrimp. This entire bowl was SO good and addictive! Wish that it would become a permanent item on the menu. 

🧡Le Signature Trio Shrimp Ramen🍜. It comes in a very rich prawn broth with generous amounts of ‘burnt’ cabbage slices, and feature 3 main ingredients, handmade ebiko prawn paste balls, prawn dumplings (our favourite) and big fresh prawns. A very robust and satisfying ramen dish, done Chinese style!

🧡Red Garoupa with Preserved Vegetables in Tonkotsu Broth. This side blew our mind with the super rich and creamy tonkotsu broth, and fresh, tender, big garoupa fish slices, all perfectly balanced off by the sour and appetising preserved vegetables. 

🧡Braised Pork Ribs with Scallion. This side has 4 big chunks of super tender and flavourful braised pork ribs. They actually remind us of the famous N brand of canned stewed pork, albeit these are freshly prepared and taste so much more better with no preservatives. 

For drinks, we each had one of their Apple and Plum vinegar drinks and they were a perfect complement to the delicious but very rich meal. 

Our verdict? We will definitely be back. In fact, we are sorry @paradisegrpsg for taking so long to try out Le Shrimp😆

✅Promotion:-
Maybank Credit or Debit cardmembers and Paradise Gourmet Rewards (PGR) members (which I am😋) will be able to enjoy the Mapo Tofu with Minced Shrimp Ramen at $14.90++ for both dine-in and takeaway. Available till 31 March 2022 at Le Shrimp Ramen outlets while stocks last.
location: Le Shrimp Ramen at Plaza Singapura

description:
When I saw that @thebelly_eats has launched a new range of bee hoon cum noodle homemade dishes along with her popular ngoh hiang rolls, I thought “Wow, perfect combination for a yummy meal!”, and quickly placed my order for dinner. 

The food arrived rather early around 3ish in the afternoon, but no problem. I simply kept them in an airy spot and come evening, reheated the ngoh hiang in the toaster oven and bee hoon in the microwave and viola, dinner is ready. 

The stewed pork bee hoon was so good, loved that the rice vermicelli was so qq and fragrant with bites of stewed pork, generous amount of vegetables and umami sliced mushrooms. The crispy fried shallots and sliced chilli given by Helen added more fragrance and heat to the dish, which was seasoned just right. One box is good for 3 persons actually. 

For the ngoh hiang, it’s a different take from my family’s recipe, but they were very enjoyable with the sweet and tangy belachan chilli dip. So chunky and crunchy with water chestnut bits too, 2 or 3 rolls with the bee hoon is just nice!

Simple and easy Honey Pomelo Tea 蜂蜜柚子茶, only requires 3 ingredients, a Pomelo, some rock sugar and honey.

First of all, scrub the pomelo with salt and rinse the surface with water. 

Cut the skin of the pomelo and remove the white part in between the skin and slice thinly. (the white part is very bitter) 

Separate the pulp from the white part skin of the pomelo and set aside. 

Boil pomelo peel in boiling water for 3 mins and rinse. Repeat if water still taste bitter.

Cook pulp and peel. Add rock sugar and simmer till the sauce thicken.

Wait for the pomelo sauce to cool completely and place in a 100% sanitized airtight jar.

Add honey and keep in the fridge.

Simple and easy Almond Florentine Cookies 黄金杏仁脆饼. Just mix all ingredients, bake until caramelised and crisp.

Ingredients :
1 cup Florentine Powder 麦芽糖粉
1 cup Almond Slices 杏仁片
1/2 cup Sunflower Seeds 葵花子
1/2 cup Pumpkin Seeds 南瓜子
2 tbsp White Sesame seeds 白芝麻
2 tbsp Black Sesame seeds 黑芝麻
1/2 tsp Salt 盐

Steps:
1. Mix well all ingredients except sesame seeds
2. Spread mixture evenly onto a baking tray with a baking paper. If you want it to be thin and crispy, spread it thinly
3. Sprinkle sesame seeds onto the mixture
4. Bake at 150°C for 15 - 20 mins or until golden brown
5. Cut into pieces when it's hot. It's won't be crispy when it's hot. Once it's cool, break into pieces
6. Store in a airtight container and enjoy

[Prawn & Fish Ball Kway Teow]

One of the favourite dish that couldn’t go wrong … It’s convenient & easy to cook.

Recipe:
Kway Teow (flat rice noodle)
Vegetables or bean sprouts 
Garlic, minced
Prawn
Fish ball
Eggs
Cooking oil 

Sauce:
Red chili paste (blend big red chili + garlic + small red chili + a little water)
Oysters sauce
Light soy sauce
Sweet soy sauce (kecap manis)
Few dash of pepper
*Splash a little water (last)

Method:
1. Heat cooking pan with olive oil, sauté minced garlic. 
2. Stir fry prawns & fish balls until almost cooked, push aside. Add in egg, let it sit for awhile & scrambled. stir well.
3. Add in rice noodles, vegetables and chili paste, stir to combine.
4. Add in all sauce to taste. Continue to stir fry and correct taste.
5. Lastly add a splash of water. Give a final stir and off the heat.

🇰🇷 #Gejang ※ Korean Marinated Raw Crab at @thegogijip! 🦀

Seen good reviews at this place and decided to try it out cause there were dishes that intrigued me. Turns out to be one of the most expensive Korean dinner I have ever paid for. 🤣💸

1️⃣ 𝙂𝙚𝙟𝙖𝙣𝙜 ※ 𝙎𝙤𝙮 𝙈𝙖𝙧𝙞𝙣𝙖𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝘾𝙧𝙖𝙗 (3pcs) @ $85.00 - Definitely an aquired taste. Either you like it or you don't like it. I tried it with and without rice and personally, I like it with rice and a little #gochujang to make it spicy and saucy. But would I order again, nahs. Not my kinda food. 😅

2️⃣ 𝘽𝙚𝙚𝙛 & 𝙋𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙎𝙚𝙩 @ $138.00 (𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙚𝙨 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝 𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙖𝙢𝙚𝙙 𝙚𝙜𝙜, 𝙤𝙣𝙚 𝙨𝙤𝙪𝙥, 𝙛𝙧𝙚𝙚𝙛𝙡𝙤𝙬 𝙨𝙞𝙙𝙚 𝙙𝙞𝙨𝙝𝙚𝙨 (𝙗𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙝𝙖𝙣) 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙫𝙚𝙜𝙚𝙩𝙖𝙗𝙡𝙚𝙨 (𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙗𝙗𝙦 𝙬𝙧𝙖𝙥𝙨) 👍🏻 Their #Iberico pork is good!! Absolutely love the quality and freshness which doesn't gives off any swiney taste. Would be better if the beef striploin was a ribeye instead.

3️⃣ 𝘽𝙚𝙚𝙛 𝙄𝙣𝙩𝙚𝙨𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙚 @ $38.00 - Wasn't as good as I expected. But it is definitely a burst of buttery taste on the tastebud.

4️⃣ 𝙎𝙚𝙖𝙛𝙤𝙤𝙙 𝙋𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙖𝙠𝙚 @ $22.00 - One of the better ones as compared to many korean restaurants.

Overall, I think the food is really good quality Korean food and its definitely on the pricey side. The service here is MUCH better as compared to many other korean places with mostly impatient grumpy staff, and be sure to book in advance as the wait can be long.

📍72 Tanjong Pagar Road, Singapore 088493

🅆🄸🄻🄻 🄸 🄱🄴 🄱🄰🄲🄺? Yes if I am in the mood for a good Korean BBQ with premium cuts! 🍽️

🇹🇭Sanook Kitchen🇹🇭 How did I ever miss this? 😌 Passed by their outlets so many times but never gave it a go.

The green curry chicken was creamy, spicy and chock full of ingredients, at just $8.90! 🥰 Grilled fish 🐟was soo firm and succulent and had that smoky flavour. 🪵 Honey blue pea flower drink 🍹 was refreshing to sip on between mouthfuls of curry hehe.

I rarely mention service, but I felt that the staff there were all so genuinely warm and friendly. ☺️ Had a pleasant and enjoyable dining experience! 💛

#sgfoodies

🍜 Braised Pork Noodles🍜  The real life hack - making more of whatever I’m making and freezing it, so that I can churn out instant proper meals whenever I need to. 🙃 Thank you past me, for feeding today me. I am appreciate. 🙏🏻 

#homecookedsg #sghomecooking #sghomecooks #sghomecook #braisedporkbelly #braisedporknoodles #makeaheadmonday #makeaheadmeals #freezermeals #freezercooking

🍱 Monday’s Lunchbox 🍱 Got a new lunch box over the weekend because the previous one broke… AGAIN. 🥲 Thankfully they are from daiso so it wasn’t too painful for my wallet. Today we have a salted egg yolk bun from @crystaljadesg, butter corn 🌽 , apples 🍎 and crackers 🍪! #mondaymorning #lunchboxideas #lunchbox #lunchboxideasforkids #lunchboxesaroundtheworld #lunchboxforkids #lunchboxinspo #lunchboxinspiration #lunchboxidea

🏝 Sea Scent 🏝 There was only one thing bad about this place… which is that it’s closing in Jun 2022. 😭

The char and smoky taste of the cajun chicken was perfection 🥺, lemon butter mussels were fresh and juicy, and thin crust pizza 🍕had a perfect crunch and wasn’t chewy at all! 😌 You can dine outdoors and enjoy the sea breeze and sound of waves 🌊, or indoors where there’s aircon (always my priority 😂). 

Bill came up to $72 for the 3 dishes which I felt was ok!

#sgfoodie #sgeats #sgeat #sgfood #sgfoodeats #sgfoodshare #sgfoodsteps #sgfoodlover #sgfooddiary #keppelbay

🥟Tim Ho Wan🥟 Quick dinner at @timhowan_sg for dinner last night! 🥢 Char siew polo bun was a delight as usual 👌🏻, and I also loved my usual malay cake which I rarely see anyone order. It’s so light and bouncy??? 🥺 Oh and the har gow 🦐 was plumper and juicier than usual! #dinnersg #sgdimsum #dimsumlover #dimsumtime #dimsumtime #sgeats #sgeat #sgfoodlover #sgfooddiary

@watami.sg 

tasty and affordable! 
i loveeee sukiyaki and mentaiko makis. 
the sukiyaki was loaded with fresh ingredients and broth was sweet and refreshing
the maki was freshly rolled, rice was soft and gelled well with the ingredients 
THIS cheesy curry chicken was unexpected. something that I wouldn’t order but hubby decided to order. really good dry chicken with some sort of dry rub, and potatoes, baked. 

everything costs less than $10 EACH
i wonder how they keep their prices low and food so tasty?? 💯💯 

this place 5eva long queue so i’m glad i finally got to try it

Roasted pork belly noodles with onsen egg from Tun Xiang
Looks good.. but doesn’t taste like it’s worth $10. My house downstairs one nicer. Haha!

A delightful set meal at @sukiya.singapore 

A small portion is sufficient for me! 
In Japan, I always look forward to the spring onion and raw egg sukiyaki beef rice from a competitor that I shall not name here 🤣 (anw that competitor’s branch in SG is so terrible so I don’t think it’s competition anw) I will eat it at least twice in Japan for a short holiday trip.

When Sukiya came I was so excited because finally I get to have this meal here!! Dare I say.. it’s quite close to what I had in Japan leh 🥲🥲🥲

Soba salad to cleanse the palate after days and days of processed food 

(not pictured: instant dumplings) 🤣🤣

I just wanted something more clean.. used a random soba salad recipe i found online with low expectations and it turned out great leh!! 

the ginger-garlic-scallion sauce tasted like chicken rice lmao 
sautéed some king oyster mushrooms to go with it

good meal! hubby and i wolfed it down. the dumpling.. we kept asking each other if you’d like the dumpling (means not nice)

@nipongnaepongsg 

hubby isn’t a fan of korean food and somehow during friend gatherings this restaurant never comes up YET why is it I see this everywhere on social media?? haha 

finally one day we made it! he sacrificed and decided to give it a try..

wow. soup was good, noodles were good, portion was big, we left with very full stomachs
and more imptly, my hubby enjoyed his meal too 😊 maybe he just never gave Korean food a chance

Scissors Cut Curry - one of the best curry rice in Singapore 🍛

Never judge a book by its cover. May looks a bit unappetizing, but trust me taste sooooo good! Each pate cost differently depending on what ingredients you choose (both pic are $4.60 each), and then mixed with 4 different sauces like curry, braised gravy, chilli sauce & chilli oil. 

The curry is not those very gao type and not spicy. Surprisingly is very well balanced but I'm a 'zhong kou wei' people, so will prefer it to be gao and spicy. 

📍Scissors Cut Curry 
29 Jalan Besar, Singapore 208905

City Hot Pot - super worth it individual hotpot in Singapore. 

Get to choose 1/2/4/6 pax set meal, which comes with 1 soup, 1 veg platter & 1 staple; which portion is really a lot.

My all time favorite soup definitely have to get it is Fish Milk soup. But there are 14 types of broths and top up $1 for a double soup based. 

Do call to book first before heading down as its always fully booked. Alternative, they do have home delivery as well. 🤩🤩

📍City Hot Pot
One Raffles Place, #04-26/27/28, Singapore 048616

Ending 2021 with great vibes, great views & great food/drink. 

One of the best rooftop bistro & bar in Singapore that you must not missed! Looking for a chillax place with your colleagues after work or mini gathering with your friends, this is a must to visit. Enjoy happy hours with 20% off all alcohol till 7pm.

Yakinikuku Like - Famous Japanese restaurant for 1-2 pax diners

Always wanted to try this out when they first open in PLQ, but the queue was so crazy. Usually you will have to wait approx 60mins, but I guess with the festive season, the waiting time are slightly longer. 

Super affordable which you can either order in set meal or ala carte; and get to choose beef, pork or chicken with different meat sizes (50g, 100g, 200g). Each set allows you to choose rice, kimchi or salad and comes with seaweed miso soup. 

Meat are pretty decent but for those heavy eater, i would not recommend as portion are pretty small. But, definitely alright for ladies 

Do check out their IGS before heading down to see if they are issuing the tickets and do head down early 😂😂

One of the best fish soup in Singapore - Xin Yuan Ji @xinyuanji.fishheadsteamboat 

Have tried before their Fish Steamboat (which served using traditional charcoal to heat up the pot), fish soup and now here I am trying their Curry Fish Head. 

Curry gravy are pretty rich & flavorful but not that sour despite the dish is Assam Curry Fish Head. And pretty much generous with the ingredients they give, includes cabbage, eggplant, tau pok, tomato etc. Fish is so fresh and tender but just a bit small.

Definitely will come back again to try out other dishes they have.
location: Xin Yuan Ji - 新源记鱼头炉

description:
📍𝐅𝐥𝐢𝐩𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐬

𝐀𝐰𝐚𝐲𝐮𝐤𝐢 𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐰𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐲 ($𝟐𝟔.𝟖𝟎)
𝗪𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘀𝗵 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗮𝗸𝗲𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝗲 𝗳𝗹𝘂𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗿 but I really loved how 𝗳𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗵, 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗷𝘂𝗶𝗰𝘆 the 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘄𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀 were. The 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 and 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁 𝗮𝘁 𝗮𝗹𝗹, which makes this dessert 𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘁𝘁𝘆 𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗮𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗲!
⭐️7/10

𝐇𝐚𝐳𝐞𝐥𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 ($𝟐𝟏.𝟖𝟎)
The pancakes for this one were 𝗳𝗹𝘂𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗿, because we specifically requested for a fresh batch. Likewise, the 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁, and I 𝗲𝘀𝗽𝗲𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗹𝗹𝘆 𝗲𝗻𝗷𝗼𝘆𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮 which added just the right amount of sweetness. 
⭐️7/10

Overall, I would say that the pancakes were pretty decent! Though they were 𝘀𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁𝗹𝘆 𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘀𝗲, they were still 𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗳𝗹𝘂𝗳𝗳𝘆 with a 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗲𝗴𝗴𝘆 𝘁𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲. Only gripe was the slight inconsistency in the pancakes’ fluffiness.

🙆‍♀️🏠 𝐉𝐢𝐚𝐛𝐚𝐛𝐚 

🍵🖤Matcha Black Sesame Swirl Bagel with Matcha Mochi + Black Sesame
🍵❤️Matcha Black Sesame Swirl Bagel with Matcha Mochi + Red Bean

Full review on my feed👀

🙆‍♀️🏠 𝐉𝐢𝐚𝐛𝐚𝐛𝐚 
[Won from her giveaway]

First off, the bagels were 𝗵𝗲𝗳𝘁𝘆 and filled with 𝗲𝘅𝘁𝗿𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘆 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗸 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗲𝗿𝗼𝘂𝘀 𝗮𝗺𝗼𝘂𝗻𝘁 𝗼𝗳 𝗳𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀. The bagels themselves were 𝘀𝗼𝗳𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝘄𝘆 with a 𝗳𝗶𝗿𝗺 𝗯𝗶𝘁𝗲! Both contained 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮 𝗺𝗼𝗰𝗵𝗶, which was really 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝘄𝘆 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗲𝘁𝗰𝗵𝘆, exactly how I like my mochi to be. 

🍵🖤 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐒𝐰𝐢𝐫𝐥 𝐁𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐌𝐨𝐜𝐡𝐢 + 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞
Enjoyed the 𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆 𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗵, 𝗻𝘂𝘁𝘁𝘆 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁𝗹𝘆 𝗯𝗶𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 flavour profile of the bssm. Perfect for hardcore bssm lovers!
⭐️8/10

🍵❤️ 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐒𝐰𝐢𝐫𝐥 𝐁𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐌𝐨𝐜𝐡𝐢 + 𝐑𝐞𝐝 𝐁𝐞𝐚𝐧
The red bean paste was 𝘀𝗺𝗼𝗼𝘁𝗵 with 𝗰𝗵𝘂𝗻𝗸𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗲𝗮𝗻 in it. It kinda reminded me of 𝗽𝗼𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗴 𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗲𝗮𝗻 𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺, so if you’re a fan of that, you’ll like this! 
⭐️7/10

Overall, these bagels tasted really 𝘄𝗵𝗼𝗹𝗲𝘀𝗼𝗺𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗮𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗹 as the 𝗳𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻’𝘁 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁 𝗮𝘁 𝗮𝗹𝗹. Thank you @jiababa88 for the wonderful giveaway🥰🥳

📍𝐇𝐯𝐚𝐥𝐚

🍠𝐒𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐭 𝐏𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐨 𝐌𝐨𝐧𝐭 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐧𝐜 ($𝟖.𝟖𝟎)
Thoroughly enjoyed the 𝙣𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙖𝙡 𝙨𝙬𝙚𝙚𝙩𝙣𝙚𝙨𝙨 from the 𝘀𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁 𝗽𝗼𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗼 which had a 𝙨𝙢𝙤𝙤𝙩𝙝 𝙩𝙚𝙭𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙚. The 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗺 within was also 𝙥𝙧𝙚𝙩𝙩𝙮 𝙡𝙞𝙜𝙝𝙩 though I’d prefer sweet potato > cream (as I’m not a fan of cream). The 𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝗯𝗮𝘀𝗲 was 𝙘𝙧𝙪𝙢𝙗𝙡𝙮 and 𝙨𝙤𝙛𝙩𝙚𝙧 𝙩𝙝𝙖𝙣 𝙖𝙫𝙚𝙧𝙖𝙜𝙚, and had a 𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜𝙚 𝙤𝙛 𝙨𝙖𝙡𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙚𝙨𝙨. 

🍠𝐒𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐭 𝐏𝐨𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐨 𝐆𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐨 ($𝟔.𝟖𝟎)
Similarly, the sweet potato flavour was 𝙥𝙧𝙤𝙢𝙞𝙣𝙚𝙣𝙩 and 𝙩𝙖𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝙣𝙖𝙩𝙪𝙧𝙖𝙡 (definitely no artificial taste!) I liked that the gelato was 𝙩𝙝𝙞𝙘𝙠 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙢𝙪𝙨𝙝𝙮, and 𝙙𝙞𝙙 𝙣𝙤𝙩 𝙢𝙚𝙡𝙩 𝙩𝙤𝙤 𝙚𝙖𝙨𝙞𝙡𝙮.

🍵𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐈𝐜𝐞 𝐁𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐝 ($𝟔.𝟓𝟎)
Preferred this to the other ice blends as it was not as diluted!

@Dopadopa.SG
𝙏𝙬𝙤 𝙎𝙘𝙤𝙤𝙥𝙨 𝙤𝙛 𝙂𝙚𝙡𝙖𝙩𝙤 𝙬𝙞𝙩𝙝 𝘾𝙧𝙤𝙞𝙨𝙨𝙖𝙣𝙩 ($12.30) | 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝟭

𝙍𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙚𝙬: 

Craving for something sweet? 🍬

@Dopadopa.sg serves up gelatos in a myriad of delicious, creative flavours such as Matcha Cheesecake, Butter Crumble, and Blueberry Pie! 🤩

Having been to @Dopadopa.sg numerous times, we are convinced that their best gelato flavours are the Home Roasted Pistachio and Butter Crumble. The former boasts a bold nutty flavour, while the latter possesses a creamy, buttery flavour that is rounded with salted cookie crumble bits 😋

If gelatos ain’t your thing, grab a croissant. Despite specialising in gelatos, @Dopadopa.sg’s croissants are incredibly well-executed and can rival even the best croissant-specialty bakeries in Singapore 👍🏻

𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝 𝙍𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜: 4.75/5

@Shinshosg
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙧𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝𝙚𝙨 | 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝟭

𝙍𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙚𝙬: 

Rarely do we have ramen in Singapore because more often than not, we taste disappointment 😬

@Shinshosg, however, is a rare gem we are glad to have discovered. Their Special Black Truffle Ramen ($17.90) had a rounded flavour. It was flavourful without being salty — a balance which most local ramen shops has failed to achieve. In fact, the bowl of ramen tasted better as we ate. Though on the leaner side, the chashu was immensely tender 😋

While the truffle ramen was great, what really stood out to us were the Crispy Chicken Skin With Spicy Aioli ($5) and Ultimate Pork Belly Yakiniku Don ($10.90). 

The chicken skin, deep-fried to golden brown perfection, paired seamlessly with an accompanying creamy spicy dip 👍🏻

We thoroughly enjoyed the optimal lean-to-fat ratio each pork belly slice had. The pork belly slices also boasted a gorgeous char, providing us a subtle smoky flavour with each bite. 

The only let-down was the Hokkaido Scallop And Caviar Taco ($9.90) which arrived more minuscule than expected 🤔 While delicious, we certainly do not think that it warrants the hefty price tag it came with. 

𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝 𝙍𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜: 4.7/5
location: Shinsho Ramen GR.ID 神將拉麵

description:
@Eat3bowls
𝘼𝙨𝙨𝙤𝙧𝙩𝙚𝙙 𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝𝙚𝙨 | 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝟭

𝙍𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙚𝙬: 

Missing the mouthwatering night market foods in Taiwan? Get a taste of Taiwan right here at @Eat3bowls! 🤩 Their Braised Pork Rice ($5) is to-die-for. What can possibly go wrong with fluffy short-grain rice topped with meltingly-tender braised meat? 🤤 The rice bowl is generously drizzled with a sweet-savoury braised gravy too.

For a complete meal, top up $1.50 for a whole braised egg 🍳 Similar to the Ajitsuke Tamago (“Ramen Egg”), @Eat3bowls’ braised egg has a custardy egg yolk and is immensely flavourful. 

To complete your dining experience, wash your foods down with a satisfying glass of Fresh Milk With Brown Sugar Pearls ($4.30)😋

𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝 𝙍𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜: 4.5/5

description:
@Laifabar
𝘽𝙪 𝙅𝙞𝙖𝙣 𝙏𝙞𝙖𝙣 𝘾𝙝𝙖𝙧 𝙎𝙞𝙚𝙬 𝙒𝙖𝙣𝙩𝙤𝙣 𝙈𝙚𝙚 ($8) | 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝟭

𝙍𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙚𝙬: 

Char Siew made of pig armpits, anyone? 🤪 Sounds repulsive, but in actuality, it tastes a whole lot better than your run-of-the-mill Char Siew made from lean pork loin! 

Also known as Bu Jian Tian, the pig armpit is a part that is both tender and springy at the same time. You can savour Char Siew made from this unique pork cut at @Laifabar 🐽 

The lean to fat ratio of the Bu Jian Tian Char Siew at @Laifabar can be likened to that of Wagyu beef. It is extremely fatty and bursting with delicious natural oils with each bite! 💦

@Laifabar never disappointments. Be sure to check them out at the newly-opened @clunyfoodcourt if you haven’t done so already! 😉

𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝 𝙍𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜: 4.7/5

@Seeseelokloksg
$1/𝙎𝙠𝙚𝙬𝙚𝙧 | 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁 𝟭/𝟭

𝙍𝙚𝙫𝙞𝙚𝙬: 

What’s your favourite meal of the day? 🤔 Nothing beats supper, in our opinion! There is no better way to unwind at the end of the day than a gossip session with delicious foods 🥳

The next time you are planning a supper meetup with friends, consider @Seeseelokloksg for its affordable array of deep-fried skewers priced at $1 each! @Seeseelokloksg is opened until late from Tuesdays to Sundays.

Enjoy sinful skewers from pillowy mantous, oozy cheese tofus, and crispy zai er (“mock goose”) dipped in flavoursome sauces 😋

If fried skewers aren’t up your alley, top up $8 for a broth to cook your sticks in. We opted for the laksa broth which tasted great with the cheese tofu skewers! 👍🏻

𝘿𝙞𝙨𝙝 𝙍𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙣𝙜: 4/5

Finally come here after hearing so much of this place @anitaeats 😂😂😂

A hearty and comforting dinner to celebrate a BFF early birthday.  All the dishes remind me of my mom cooking.

A number of their favorite dishes were sold out so good reason to return to try the rest of the menu🤣🤣🤣

We had:
■ Fried farm chicken with garlic 
■ Steamed pork with salted shrimp paste
■ Homemade yong tau foo with sauce. 
■ Sambal petai with shrimps 
■ Stir fry Choy sam with garlic 

We love all the dishes👍😋😋😋

description: Transition Phase - Day 36. 👍😋
Transition Phase - Day 33. Taste of Taiwan without VTL, PCR & Quarantine

Brioche French Toast from Wakey Wakey. Found in The  Concourse along Beach Road, they opened in 2018 by the group behind the popular cafés Strangers’ Reunion and Curious Palette. Serving up a similar concept with slight variations in their offerings, I was curious to taste their food having dined previously at the latter brand. It allured me with the item that was always my weakness at brunches, and I had probably eaten my fair share of.

Bread: 7.5/10. A deep brown exterior on both the toasts showed promise of a crisp texture, and delivered a well made crunch without being too crumbly like biscuits. It was also supported with a relatively fluffy inner texture with good moisture, absorbing the custard adequately. That said, flavours were a bit muted with the bitterness of its toast being forward, and lacked a strong synergy with the other ingredients in the dish. It could afford to be more heavy-handed with spices to enrich its profile, while complimenting and supporting the toppings

Toppings: 7/10. Opting for the sweet and savoury route was a bold move, as the complexity in achieving a nice balance was often the downfall of the attempt. A smart pairing of maple-glazed bacon and apple compote was key to its moderate success, with homemade crumble a nice finishing touch. However, I felt the added vanilla ice cream contrasted too much against the bacon, and along seasonal berries felt like another profile included into its already delicate balance. Having them separate tasted better, but contradicted the intention of putting everything on the same plate

Overall: 7.3/10. A pretty decent version of the said dish, with their well prepared toasts rightfully being the star. I appreciated the difficult attempt of serving both ends of the flavour spectrum, which almost succeeded sans the berries and ice cream. Perhaps they could create a berries and ice cream French Toast item, which I would love to see them work their magic on. $20.90++ might seem a bit steep, but a good execution made its worth.

Sid Burger from Sid Burger and Craft Beer. It opened in early 2021 along Icon Village at Tanjong Pagar, and had been on my list of burger spots to visit since. From the same group behind Vatos Urban Tacos, this small shop specialised in handcrafted burgers and craft beers, the latter being offered through its wide range. For me, the former appealed more, and seeing its rave reviews and 4.9 rating on Google made me even more keen to visit and taste the hype through its namesake burger.

Juiciness: 7/10. Made using a Wagyu and Angus blend, the patty tucked itself snugly on the bottom bun, a different presentation from the usual arrangement of being sat on fresh greens which it did not have. While I enjoyed the beefiness, its relatively small form limited how much taste it offered. Its texture was decent from the tender insides to its crisp exterior, but again hardly felt in a complete bite. Maybe a double was needed to fully enjoy the work put into its beef patties

Bun: 5.5/10. Crowned with sesame seed buns, both top and bottom undersides were lightly toasted, thoughtful to support the moisture from its other elements. Sadly, I found its inner texture too soft, that while was enough to hold up the weight, lacked the bite I craved for in buns. It was also quite plain, and could be improved by toasting them with grease or butter

Synergy: 7.5/10. Topped off with a generous serving of BBQ shredded pork, along with jalapeño relish, pickled red onions, apple coleslaw and sriracha mayonnaise, it delivered a smoky aroma and taste largely assumed to be from the pork. The heat kick of the jalapeño, onions and mayonnaise complemented and elevated flavours, with its coleslaw a refreshing balance. Supposedly had cheddar cheese, but that either melted or was omitted, and missed a binding element

Overall: 6.7/10. A decent burger, but did not impress to what I expected. There were promising aspects which I felt could built upon to become a real contender. Being a smashburger the single patty was quite off balanced, doubling it up might do the trick along with the missing cheese. A good price of $12++ during Happy Hour, its great service would bring me back for its other items.

MEME Fish & Chips from MEME Bistro Bar. A relatively new spot opened only in September 2020, they served up usual bar bites and mains in their gathering-friendly setting for an enjoyable dining experience. Being along Mackenzie Road made them a bit inaccessible, but still only a short stroll away from Little India MRT. I scrolled past some posts on them before and looked forward to tasting what they had to offer.

Fish: 7/10. Served on a giant metal platter, the fish slab had a decent coloured batter that it supposedly coined their MEME Special Batter. Not just for show, this was a good reflection of its well spiced flavour that enhanced each bite. Its thin coating compared with the fish made a good ratio, and had nice crisps and crunches with its craggy exterior. The fish was a bit too soft for me, that dampened the experience by breaking apart too easily and did not stick well to the batter

Chips: 6/10. To match the size of its fish and platter, an equally generous portion of fries cushioned the fish. Its little specks of herb were quite negligible and could do with more seasoning, while texture wise there was also nothing special about them. An average batch of fries I would not mind having but would not finish

Tartar Sauce: 6/10. Called “lemon sauce” on its menu, I was not sure if it was really that since it looked like just mayonnaise with a pinch of the same herb used for its fries. It paired decently with the main components, but again felt almost replaceable with any generic sauce. A missed opportunity to further elevate the dish

Overall: 6.3/10. While first impressions were promising, it turned out relatively mediocre not from its execution but rather how it compared with others. It was not bad, just not impressionable to justify searching for the spot to visit. $17.90 perhaps was for its portion, I would skip this and go for something more enticing like the MEME Ultimate Burger, that already sounded like a winner.

Cod Fish Brioche Burger from Surrey Hills Grocer. This spot sat within Arena Country Club at Joo Koon, meant to mimic the experience of visiting farms in Australia. It opened recently in January 2022 with its cafe a subset of the grocer. Their menu was supposedly designed in collaboration with an Australian Michelin-starred chef, and I made the trip one day to appease my wanderlust.

Fish: 6.5/10. Instead of the usual battered and fried fish patties, they presented a relatively lighter option with a grilled cod. Without a crust to hide under, its glistening surface with nice charred marks were promising marks of good execution. The delicate nature of cod meant it flaked easily, and without an outer layer holding things together made it a bit messy. Its moistness showcased the innate flavour of the fish, but felt it was on the mild spectrum for both taste and texture 

Bun: 6.5/10. The top brioche bun sat propped ajar from the burger when served, but I was quite pleased by the glisten just like the fish it supported. Cutting through it after crowning, its surface first crackled then gave way to a soft and relatively fluffy core. Not much liquids for it to soak up meant it retained its form throughout. The buttery taste of brioche was mild, which I had hoped to be more potent to enhance the already lighter fish

Synergy: 7/10. Complementing the burger was a house made dill tartare slathered on both buns, finished with pickled green chilli, lettuce and carrots. The sauce was a nice way of incorporating the quintessential herb into the dish without eating it alone, and tartar a classic use for fish. However, the other vegetables felt awkward for their respective flavours and textures, I thought the oriental salad could work adequately as the fresh elements instead

Overall: 6.7/10. Quite a decent burger that was more an upscale version, reflecting the Australia brunch culture I missed dearly. They worked well as a break from the urban jungle with a relaxing experience, which was not that inconvenient given its short walk from the MRT. Its price was relatively high at $24++, but I assumed was for its sustainable sourcing. Hope to try items off their brunch menu next!

Chicken & Pancakes from Birdfolks. Established in late 2017, the concept started from the owners’ experience in the US that left an unforgettable impact on them. An extended period of experimenting led them to develop a unique Singapore-style instead of recreating flavour. Located in NEWest, I made the special trip to try what I had been missing out on.

Chicken: 8/10. Their signature fried chicken were made upon order, prepared with an American-style brine and batter method. They envisioned fried chicken to have a nice crust encasing the juicy meat that was achieved in this boneless thigh. Their unique spice blend made for a well flavoured mouthful, coupled with its deep brown caramelised crust delivered layers of taste and texture. I only wished for more craggy bits for an added crunch

Waffles: 6/10. Yes I know these were not waffles but its ingredients were similar but maybe in a different ratio. I thought these buttermilk pancakes had a rustic charm, its simple but consistent looks made it feel homemade. While on the flatter end, these still had a slight fluff for a nice chew to complement the crisp chicken. I wished for more flavour though as these were plain and lacked an oomph to enhance the dish as a whole

Sauce: 6/10. Served with a mini pitcher of maple syrup, the no-frills option offered some sweetness to the dish with its accompanying moisture. A subtle point, but did appreciate its segregated serving to give me control of the amounts I preferred. The butter felt more suited for the pancakes, though I did try it with the chicken out of curiosity, with minimal impact

Overall: 6.7/10. As their name suggested, they did their bird well but its other components was a bit average. If solely based on the chicken, they were probably one of the better places to visit for. Otherwise for said dish, it needed much more from its other components. Seeing other diners order their other mains like rice bowls and burgers, I would love trying them in my next visit.

2️⃣ 𝐀𝐥-𝐅𝐮𝐧𝐠𝐡𝐢 𝐏𝐚𝐬𝐭𝐚
Pasta Al-Funghi mixed with freshly picked Mushrooms cooked with White Wine and Broth
3️⃣ 𝐏𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐨𝐛𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐨 𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐀𝐠𝐥𝐢𝐨 𝐎𝐥𝐢𝐨
Sliced Garlic Chilli Chicken Broth with Shimeji Mushroom and Australian White Wine
4️⃣ 𝐖𝐢𝐥𝐝 𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐒𝐨𝐮𝐩
5️⃣ 𝐓𝐒𝐀 𝐁𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐞 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐒𝐚𝐭𝐚𝐲
6️⃣ 𝐓𝐒𝐀 𝐆𝐚𝐫𝐥𝐢𝐜 𝐓𝐫𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 𝐅𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐬 (𝐀𝐥𝐚 𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐭𝐞 $𝟏𝟓, 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐩𝐚𝐫𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐒𝐞𝐭 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐥)
7️⃣ 𝐅𝐥𝐚𝐭 𝐖𝐡𝐢𝐭𝐞

We started with the Wild Mushroom Soup. While the flavours are good, the texture is too waterey. The Satay is pretty good, and the Chilli is nice and strong 🍄

The Chicken To-nite and Al-Funghi Pasta are decent choices. However, the Portobello Mushroom Aglio Olio is most definitely nothing like an Aglio Olio. The taste resembles a Mala Pasta instead (sour and spicy). It is definitely challenging to finish this Pasta 😐

At least the Truffle Fries are still good 🍟

We have dined at The Social Alley a couple of times, and we feel that standards could be more consistent. There are days where the food is fantastic, but on other occasions, it seems like the Chef had a bad day. The diners at the table beside us were equally disappointed with their lunch 🧑🏻‍🍳

Nevertheless, if you are around the area, you can give The Social Alley a try. Let us know what you think of their food! 💭

𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗢𝗿𝗶𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗮𝗹 𝗦𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗮𝘄𝗮𝗻𝗴 𝗪𝗵𝗶𝘁𝗲 𝗕𝗲𝗲 𝗛𝗼𝗼𝗻 🦐

Founded by Tay King Huak under the name You Huak Restaurant in 1999 as a Zi Char Hawker Stall at Chomp Pang Market 👦🏻

When the market closed in 2000, Mr Tay moved his business to Jalan Tampang (Sembawang) and established his own restaurant ⬆️

Their signature dish is their White Bee Hoon, which is a Rice Vermicelli dish cooked with seafood, vegetables and eggs in a gravy 🌱

The gravy is made by simmering a Chicken Broth for over 8 hours. Generous amount of fresh Deshelled-Prawns, Squid and Eggs are cooked with the Rice Vermicelli! 🦑

In 2013, the restaurant rebranded to "White Restaurant" when second generation Mr Victor Tay took over the business. Under his leadership, the brand expanded rapidly and today, there are 7 White Restaurant outlets islandwide! 📈

We like that White Restaurant's White Bee Hoon ($7/$12) is prepared using fresh Seafood (we are not big fans of treated translucent-looking Shrimps). The dish is also very eggy, with good flavours from the gravy! Squeeze the Lime onto the Noodles to give it a nice zesty taste 🥚

We also tried their Yam Paste ($4.80), and it has generous amount of Coconut Milk and Gingko Nuts. Lime Juice and Barley are priced at $3 🥥

🍄🍄[30 𝐌𝐢𝐧 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞] 𝐉𝐚𝐩𝐚𝐧𝐞𝐬𝐞-𝐢𝐧𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐝 𝐌𝐮𝐬𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐦 𝐏𝐚𝐞𝐥𝐥𝐚. Keeping things simple and meatless with tonight's experiment. The rice grains and mushrooms soaked up all the butter and dashi stock so it was quite a bomb of umami and honestly quite the comfort food. 🤭 

Ingredients:
White mushrooms
Shimeji mushrooms
White onions, chopped
Arborio rice
1 cup dashi stock
Butter
Sake
Italian herbs
Black pepper

Caramelise the onions in melted butter. Add the rice and coat well in the butter sauce, then the mushrooms. Stir around abit, then add sake and dashi stock. Add the Italian herbs and let it simmer for 15-17 minutes till all the stock has evaporated. Add black pepper and stir through.

Sprinkle spring onions before serving.
.
.

description:
[𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞]🐓🍔𝐓𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐲𝐚𝐤𝐢 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐁𝐮𝐫𝐠𝐞𝐫. Putting my spin on this because I think it's the perfect way to start the weekend! Even if you've had a meh week, let's remember the only constant thing in life is the weekend so this is the best time to recharge, detox and eat your favourite foods. 🤣

I used chicken thigh and marinated it in some teriyaki sauce, minced ginger, sake, sesame oil, pepper and dark soy sauce for some colour. Leave in the fridge for at least 30 mins for the flavours to seep in.

For the salad, I used a mix of purple and green cabbage and added a bit of wafu sauce as well for extra zing.

Panfry the chicken, toast your bread, add sriracha mayo if you wish to the bun when it's done. Assemble the ingredients together and top it off with some furikake. 

Happy Saturday everyone!

description:
🍜[30 𝐌𝐢𝐧 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞] 𝐙𝐡𝐚 𝐉𝐢𝐚𝐧𝐠 𝐌𝐢𝐚𝐧. Made a slight tweak from my previous attempt by combining hoisin and spicy bean paste together and this tastes about as legit as the ones you can get outside. I added 榨菜(potherb mustard) for extra crunch and tanginess. Try it for yourself!

Ingredients:
Minced pork
Potherb mustard 
Diced mushrooms
Chopped garlic
Chopped shallots
Noodles (I used fresh ramen)

Seasoning:
1 tbsp hoisin sauce
1 tbsp doubanjiang
Dark soy sauce
Light soy sauce
Huadiao wine
Sesame oil
Pepper
Sugar

Boil the noodles till al dente and drain the water.

Stirfry the garlic and shallots, add the mushrooms and mustard, doubanjiang and hoisin sauce and blend it all together. Then add the pork mince, break it up into crumbs, then the rest of the seasonings. Add some water to make gravy and simmer. Lastly, add slurry to thicken. 

Pour the meat gravy over the noodles and garnish with sliced cucumber if you wish.
.
.

"Making the world sweeter, one bun at a time."

Saw @thebunclubbakes on @pickupp.sg and I knew I had to get it 🙊 Got this box of The Perfect Partouze at $24! This box consists of 6 buns, namely milk, chocolate, biscoff, matcha, pink milk and thai tea! The buns were soft (before heating up) and fluffy. My preferred way and also the reccomended way is to heat up via an oven/air fryer/pan-fry. The bread would be real crispy yet fluffy at the same time. We enjoyed all flavours except their pink milk 😐 My favourite would be their biscoff! It was more watery than the usual sauce but it made it less sweet and cloying if you were to eat the whole bun on your own. Overall, the flavours were on-point; you get what you ordered! ALSO!! I just realize they have pandan kaya flavour (not included in the box i ordered) 🥲 I guess i'll have to re-order again next time 🤪

Don't forget to swipe for cross sections!!

姜蒜焖排骨 Braised Pork Ribs
.
//材料 Ingredients// 
油 Oil - 2汤匙 Tbsp
排骨 Pork Ribs - 500克 gram
姜末 Minced ginger - 1汤匙 gram
蒜末 Minced garlic - 1汤匙 Tbsp
豆瓣酱 Soy Bean Paste - 1 1/2 汤匙 Tbsp
水 Water - 500毫升 ml 
.
辣椒 Chilli - 2根 <切斜片/slice>
黑酱油 Dark Soy Sauce - 1汤匙 Tbsp
糖Sugar - 1茶匙 Tsp
水 Water - 200毫升 ml 
.
//步骤 Step//
热2汤匙油，把排骨煎至两面金黄
加入蒜末和姜末一起炒香
加豆瓣酱拌炒
加500毫升的水中小火焖30分钟
.
加入辣椒，黑酱油和糖拌匀
再加200毫升的水焖多10分钟
就可以上桌啦！
.
*注意⚠️
每个锅和火候都不一样，时间和水可能需要自己注意下哟！
.

今天跟大家分享一道下饭菜
茄汁日本豆腐 《Tomatoes Egg Tofu》
汁淋饭都好吃😋
.
//材料 Ingredients//
🔸蛋豆腐 Egg Tofu - 2条 stick
🔸蒜米 Minced Garlic - 1汤匙 Tbsp
🔸番茄 Tomatoes - 2颗 <切丁 Cut dice>
🔸番茄酱 Tomato Sauce - 1汤匙 Tbsp
🔸生抽 Light Soy Sauce - 2汤匙 Tbsp
🔸糖 Sugar - 1茶匙 Tsp
🔸水 Water - 100毫升 ml
🔸金针菇 Enoki Mushroom - 1包 pack
.
//步骤 Steps//
🔹热油，把日本豆腐2面煎至金黄，备用
🔹热油炒蒜米，加入番茄丁炒烂
🔹调味加入生抽， 糖和番茄酱
🔹倒入水拌匀
🔹加入金针菇和煎好的日本豆腐
*金针菇还会出水哟
🔹滚一会，拌匀就搞定!
.

甜点控看过来吧！
你听过达克瓦兹 Dacquoise吗？
.
简单介绍下：-
✨它和马卡龙是好姐妹，一样都是来自法国
✨属于豪华的甜点
✨只是材料比例上有些不一样而已
✨甜度上呢，达克瓦兹没有马卡龙那么甜
.
非常感谢木木家 @mumubakery2020 送来的法式甜点 - 达克瓦兹 Dacquoise，美得像个艺术品
太精致了，看了也疗愈😍
.
这个精致的达克瓦兹可花了木木家差不多两年的时间研发，用的都是最上等的材，就为了给大家吃到最好的味道
.
木木家的达克瓦兹饼皮外酥内软
内陷没有使用色素，香料，完全纯天然，你可以吃到食材本身的香气
非常推荐你们试试！
.
木木家在来临的情人节有推出情人节甜点礼盒，太平和吉隆坡的朋友快去询问下哟！希望木木家的甜点可以让小俩口浪漫加倍、恋情升温，甜蜜蜜💕
.

大年初七 《人日》
吃面，寓意着用面条缠住岁月的双腿，取长寿之意
.
我特地准备了一道肉碎长寿面
做法简单，还不懂吃啥的朋友可以参考下
.
//材料 Ingredients// <1人份>
🔸油 Oil - 1汤匙 Tbsp
🔸蒜米 Minced Garlic - 1茶匙 Tsp
.
🔸肉碎 Minced Pork - 50克 gram
#8foodlabmeatmarinateratio 
🔺生抽 Light Soy Sauce- 1茶匙 Tsp
🔺麻油 Sesame Oil - 1茶匙 Tsp
🔺玉蜀黍粉 Corn Starch - 1/2茶匙 Tsp
🔺白胡椒粉 White Pepper - 少许 little 
*拌匀，腌制
.
🔸香菇 Shitake mushroom - 2个 <泡水，切薄片 slice>
🔸生抽 Light Soy Sauce - 1汤匙 Tbsp
🔸黑酱油 Dark Soy Sauce - 1茶匙 Tsp
🔸胡椒粉 White Pepper - 少许 little
🔸糖 Sugar - 1/2茶匙 Tsp
🔸水 Water - 50毫升 ml
🔸面条 Noodles - 1人份 pax
🔸豆芽 Bean Sprout - 少许 Some
.
//步骤 Steps//
🔹热油，炒蒜米
🔹加入腌制好的肉碎和香菇拌炒
🔹调味加生抽，胡椒粉和糖
🔹加水焖一会
🔹起锅备用
.
🔹煮一锅水烫面条和豆芽，盛盘
🔹淋上炒好的肉碎
🔹撒上炸葱和青葱
🔹就搞定！
.
祝大家人日快乐！😁❤️
.

#comfortfood #asianfoodie #foodporn #igfood #singaporeeats #8dayseat #thefeedfeed #whati8today #sgfood #foodilysm #asianfoodrecipes #food #onmyplate #f52grams #tastingtable #foodgasm #sgfoodies #eeeeeats #yoursingapore #stfoodtrending #sgfoodblogger #dailyfoodfeed #burpplesg #koreanfriedchicken #koreanfood #friedchicken

Got a request from my gal to bake a Korean minimalist cake for her birthday. 

These cakes are either single or two-tiered and have a simple colored frosting around them. Though they look simple but let's admit it, icing cakes are relatively difficult no matter how much practice you have done😕

Ta-da! This is our unique look of Korean style cake. It may appear a bit messy, but hey! that’s actually part of her personalized design…bake with love and efforts as well!🤣

🍞 No. 26 - Finding time to make a sourdough loaf hasn’t been easy. Another loaf, another opportunity to experiment 😉

Ingredients :
Bread Flour 240g
Unbleached All-Purpose Flour 60g
Water 240g
Levain 60g (starter was fed 1:1:1)
Salt 6g

Method:
- Autolyse starter, flour and water, for 1 hour
- Add Salt 
- Rest 10 minutes
- Stretch and Fold, once
- Rest 30 minutes
- Coil Fold 3 sets, 40 minutes interval
- Rest the dough for at least 1 hour before shaping
- Preshape the dough
- Rest 20 minutes
- Shape the dough
- Rest the dough in the banneton basket for 20 minutes
- Cold Retard 14 hours at 1-3°C
- Place dutch oven in the oven and preheat at 250°C
- Bake covered at 250°C for 23 minutes, and bake another 17 minutes at 230°C uncovered
- Cool for at least 3 hours before slicing

Am I Addicted’s signature Korean-western fusion cuisine blends unique, punchy flavors to plant-based dishes for a guilt-free and nutritious dining experience, from healthful nibbles to nutrition-packed mains.

🥗𝗞𝗮𝗹𝗲 𝗪𝗮𝗹𝗱𝗼𝗿𝗳 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝗮𝗱 $𝟭𝟲
This plate of salad consists of Kale, Waldorf Dressing, Apple, Grapefruit, Candy Sunflower Seed. A refreshing start of the meal.

🌾𝗕𝗶𝗿𝗱 𝗼𝗳 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗲 $𝟭𝟴
This is a nutritious breakfast meal that I frequently consume. There are a generous amount of granola, almond slices, strawberry, banana, chia seed, soy milk, coconut chips, and a hearty scoop of mixed berry sauce.

🍄𝗗𝗼𝗲𝗻𝗷𝗮𝗻𝗴 𝗧𝗿𝘂𝗳𝗳𝗹𝗲 𝗥𝗶𝘀𝗼𝘁𝘁𝗼 $𝟮𝟱
There is Doenjang (Korea Miso), Barley, Dasi Stock, and Combine Mushroom in this, and it is important to mix all of the ingredients together before eating it as there was a layer of truffle oil on top. This is my favorite dish out of everything, the truffle flavor isn't overpowering, but the earthiness of the mushroom adds a fragrance to the dish.

🧀𝗚𝗿𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗖𝗵𝗲𝗲𝘀𝗲 𝗞𝗶𝗺𝗰𝗵𝗶 𝗦𝗮𝗻𝗱𝘄𝗶𝗰𝗵 $𝟭𝟲
The sandwich is made with vegan cheese and kimchi. The toasty bread was the nicest part, as it went perfectly with the ingredients.

🍝𝗧𝗢𝗥𝗧𝗔 𝗗𝗜 𝗥𝗜𝗦𝗢 𝗣𝗔𝗦𝗧𝗔 $𝟮𝟮
This pasta is filled with Vegan ingredients such as Vegan Based Squid & Shrimp, Vegan Cheese, Korean Rice Cake. This is just a plate of pasta; it's nothing spectacular, but it's decent.

Argentinian Prawn Pasta? I didn’t expect the Argentinians to do pasta, but I really shouldn’t be that surprised considering that pasta is pretty much a universal dish. While it is neither a hundred percent Italian or Argentinian, @tonito.singapore piquant prawn pasta is definitely a hundred percent exquisite.⠀
⠀
Silky strands of spaghetti done al dente are bathed luxuriously in a palatable pomodoro sauce, and fortified with two titanic Argentinian prawns, littleneck clams & shredded crabmeat. The sauce is a textbook example of how to do an excellent pomodoro : smooth, thick, garlicky, and jam packed full of satisfying savouriness with just a little sweet & sourness to shake it up. Just the perfect sauce for the pasta.⠀
⠀
As one would expect of any self respecting restaurant, all of the seafood on the plate were commendably fresh. The huge prawns still retained their subtle sweetness, but now boasted a newly acquired smokiness from being grilled expertly. Garlic & prawns are a match made in heaven, and this is definitely seventh heaven. I mean, the prawns are comprehensively blanketed by fried garlic. Unless you’re Dracula, that’s Flavortown on the back of a couple of prawns.⠀
⠀
As for the clams & crabmeat, they don’t add much in the way of flavour, but they definitely complete the dish and give it a sublimely satisfying weight. The crabmeat in particular will ensure that almost no mouthful is purely pasta and nothing else. Nossir, the carbs are completed by all the deeply satisfying seafood that rounds it all out. If you’re ravenously hungry and have an insatiable craving for pasta, this ponderous plate of prawn pasta is just what you need.⠀
⠀
But wait, there’s MORE! With the brilliance of #burpplebeyond, you can enjoy TWO plates of this amazing Argentinian Prawn Pasta for the price of one! That’s right, TWO of these Argentinian beauties for the low, LOW price of $26++! Now, I’m crying for this Argentinian prawn pasta, but they are most definitely joyful tears.⠀
⠀
Thank you so much for the invite, @tonito.singapore and @burpple!

It’s #tacotuesday, and I wanna taco ‘bout how revolutionary these flippin’ fabulous fish tacos from @tonito.singapore are ($18++ for a ménage à trois). Fried fish tacos are a dime a dozen, but Tonito’s are so clear of the majority it’s not even fair to the other players anymore. The flour tortilla transporting everything is standard stuff, but like what your parents always used to say, it’s what’s inside that really matters. And the stuff inside these toasted flour tortillas are simply stellar. ⠀
⠀
Thick fingers of fish (probably dory) are brilliantly battered in the most ethereal encasement I have ever had the pleasure of biting into, and are deep fried to absolute perfection. The tremendously thin layer of batter is astonishingly airy, and is crispier than a freshly minted hundred dollar bill. That impossibly thin batter barely conceals the flaky, moist & meaty fish underneath.⠀
⠀
If these fried fish were to be taken on their own, it would merely be decent as opposed to spectacular. Thankfully for the fish, the accompanying pineapple salsa & tartar sauce are its ride or die homies who uplift the fried fish into another plane of palatability. The tangy & satisfyingly salty tartar sauce blesses the fish with it’s unctuous, savoury qualities while the peerless pineapple salsa provides sweetness & sourness to light up all the taste receptors simultaneously.⠀
⠀
The pineapple salsa is undoubtedly what led the tacos into flavour nirvana. The ripe diced pineapples were invitingly sweet, while the added diced tomato & a squeeze of lime juice turned up with a whole lot of extra zest. The saliva extracting sourness completely offset any negligible greasiness from the fried fish, while cohabiting with the salty & sweet elements exceptionally well for a perfect, piquant harmony of flavours that are utterly irresistible.⠀
⠀
Now, some of you are thinking that paying twenty bucks for a trio of tacos is extortionate, but that’s where #burpplebeyond comes in. Oh yeah, all tacos are one for one with Burpple Beyond! Get in there and smash these spec-taco-lar babies, stat!⠀
⠀
Truly appreciate the generosity, @tonito.singapore & @burpple!

While you can’t guarantee that Mondays are going to start right, you can definitely start your meals at @tonito.singapore right with this scintillating seafood ceviche ($25++). Considering that it’s built from onion salsa, tomato leche (tomato cream?), mixed seafood, and shredded tortillas covering it all, it’s technically a salad. A seafood salad, yes, but still technically a salad.⠀
⠀
Details aside, this ceviche is a textbook example of a proper appetite whetting starter. The sour, sharp onion salsa & chunky tomato leche will send your salivary glands into overdrive, and the crunchiness will compel you to keep chomping away. The felicitously fresh & expertly cooked seafood mix of scallops, shrimps & squid provide that addictively bouncy texture and add their sweet briny flavours to the dish. The crisp tortilla strips soak up all the zesty juices of the ceviche real fast, so you’re gonna have to devour this ceviche as fast as possible.⠀
⠀
All the seafood & vegetables are bound together by a judicious application of lime juice and chilies, which makes this ceviche irresistibly spicy & sour. Perfect for getting you all fired up for the rest of what is almost guaranteed to be a magnificent meal.⠀
⠀
Mucho gracias for hosting me, @burpple & @tonito.singapore!⠀
⠀

Gewürztraminer is by far my favourite white wine varietal due to its fragrant lychee aroma and sweet fruity and floral flavours. However, it’s one of the more uncommon wine varietals in Singapore, so when I do see a bottle of gewürztraminer, I grab it without much hesitation.⠀
⠀
I’m truly glad I didn’t hesitate to splash the cash for this bottle of 2019 Wolfberger gewürztraminer, because every last sip was glorious. The body was slightly syrupy, falling nicely between the thinness of a sav blanc & the thick buttery body of a chardonnay, which complemented the sweet fruitiness of the wine. ⠀
⠀
The aroma of ripe lychee dominates the nose, but after the gewürztraminer opens up more, the soft scents of pineapple, honey, elderflower and perhaps a hint of rose. The flavours are absolutely fabulous, with sweet ripe lychees leading the way for the charmingly citrusy & slightly peachy notes to follow.⠀
⠀
Many people regard German automobiles as the pinnacle of German engineering. While that isn’t entirely wrong, the existence of Wolfberger’s 2019 vintage gewürztraminer is clearly THE shining example of German engineering.⠀
⠀

The dessert course of the brilliant #burpplebeyond is @tonito.singapore very special Chocolate Tres Leche cake, which sees a slab of spiced chocolate cake sparingly garnished with some candied pistachios, a couple of blueberries, whipped cream and lubed up by the puddle of tres leches, which is a triple threat of condensed milk, evaporated milk, and heavy cream. Yes, this is a choccy milk cake.⠀
⠀
Tres leches cake is traditionally a sponge cake, but this one was a very intriguing cross between a mousse and a sponge cake, flavoured with slightly bitter dark chocolate. The spice component is very mild, with just fleeting hints of cinnamon & nutmeg flitting over your palate as you devour this wet little sweetie. The sweetness is extremely subtle here, and most of the sugar rush actually comes from the tres leche mix as opposed to the cake itself.⠀
⠀
The Chocolate Tres Leche is a subtle dessert, but it does more than enough to satisfy moderate dessert cravings. A suitable swan song to a sublime set menu if you ask me, and the pleasure of the Burpple Beyond set is heightened by the knowledge that it only costs $58++.⠀
⠀
Mucho gracias for hosting us, @tonito.singapore & @burpple!⠀
⠀

Good food and good vibes with friends at Hello Arigato @helloarigato.official last week! If you love Japanese-inspired dishes or sandos, this is one cafe worth checking out in the Upper Thomson area! ⁣
⁣
The 𝗧𝗲𝗿𝗶𝘆𝗮𝗸𝗶 𝗦𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗼 may look unassuming, but it is downright satisfying! I mean, just look at that glorious cross-section (if you are wondering why I only have half, it's because Bb's friend took the other half 😆)! The chicken thigh sandwiched between soft pillowy Japanese milk bread was tender and juicy, with the teriyaki glaze bringing an umami oomph with every bite. We love that the lightly toasted bread retained its crispiness and did not become soggy. ⁣
⁣
𝗠𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗸𝗼 𝗣𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗮 is a good option for pasta lovers, with the mentaiko sauce and generous sprinkling of tobiko lending creamy richness and umami to the wafu pasta dish! The raw scallops were fresh, with lemon zest cutting through the sweetness of each piece. However, we felt that the pasta choice could have been better - perhaps capellini or angel hair would have worked better with the seafood flavours. Nevertheless, it's worth getting if you love mentaiko! 🧡🍝⁣
⁣
Didn't try the 𝗞𝗮𝘁𝘀𝘂 𝗦𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗼 but BB's friend loved the thick panko-breaded pork cutlet between the bread slices. Shall get that next visit!⁣
.⁣
📍 Address: 227 Upper Thomson Rd, Singapore 574359⁣
.⁣
.⁣

Found our new favourite wallet-friendly option in town at New Station Snack Bar @newstationsnackbar! Their forever looong long queue was a big reason why Bb never tried till recently but better late than never right? ⁣
⁣
Perhaps the most-egg-citing dish on their menu, their 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗲𝗱 𝗘𝗴𝗴 𝗣𝗼𝗿𝗸 𝗥𝗶𝗯𝘀 was our favourite. Deep-fried to a nice golden brown colour, the boneless pork ribs are tender and well-marinated. The batter is not as crispy as one would expect, but understandably so since the pork ribs are covered with a generous coating of the salted egg sauce. The sauce is creamy and rich without being surfeiting, with a hint of aroma from the curry leaves & slight heat from chilli padi. It's so good that we pretty much swept up all the sauce with rice LOL.💛⁣
⁣
Bb is not a fan of kailan, but the combination of 𝗦𝘁𝗶𝗿 𝗙𝗿𝘆 𝗞𝗮𝗶 𝗟𝗮𝗻 𝘄 𝗚𝗮𝗿𝗹𝗶𝗰 was nicely executed as a side dish. The 𝗙𝘂 𝗬𝗼𝗻𝗴 𝗢𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗲𝘁𝘁𝗲 is crispy outside and fluffy with lots of ingredients within too! 👍🏻⁣
.⁣
📍 Address: Far East Plaza 14 Scotts Road #05-95 Singapore, 228213⁣
.⁣
.⁣

Com-pho-ting vibes at The Kind Bowl @thekindbowl_sg, a hole-in-the-wall that serves up vegan Vietnamese cuisine! We were impressed with 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗞𝗶𝗻𝗱 𝗣𝗵𝗼 - we honestly couldn't tell this was plant-based. The broth is light but has a good depth of flavour, and the generous portion of silky flat noodles is substantial for one person. The chicken meat is replaced by shredded marinated seitan as the main protein. While discernable texture-wise, the seitan was similar in taste to the real deal. Alliums like onion and garlic can be removed upon request.

Or you can try their rendition of Bún chả in the form of 𝗕𝗕𝗤 𝗗𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁! Love the variety of ingredients that came along with the rice noodles (skewered mushrooms/mock meat, shredded carrots & radish), and our favourite is their deep-fried spring roll. The fried shallots gave a crispy bite as well. If anything, we felt that there could be more sauce to mix everything together given the generous portion of noodles.

Highly recommend getting some sides to go along too! We liked the 𝗢𝘆𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗠𝘂𝘀𝗵𝗿𝗼𝗼𝗺 𝗙𝗿𝗶𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 for the crisp batter and the meaty texture within.
.
📍 Address: 71 Killiney Rd, Singapore 239527
Also available at Northpoint.

Ooh lala, this 𝗦𝗲𝗮𝗳𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 from Sedap Wok @sedapwok_halal is legit SEDAP! 🦞🦐🐟 This platter will definitely satiate any seafood cravings you may have! Finally crossed off Kream & Kensho @kreamkensho from my ever-growing wishlist (at this point, I lost count😆) while running errands in the Kampung Bahru area! Enjoyed the cosy minimalistic vibes of the place, definitely somewhere for you to chill alone or enjoy a good brunch session with friends! ⁣
⁣
Their signature 𝗛𝗼𝘁𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗦𝗮𝗸𝘂𝗿𝗮 𝗘𝗯𝗶 𝗖𝗮𝗽𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗶 might be one of the pricier options on their menu but the rich umami flavours from the combination of shio kombu, sakura ebi and the generous topping of ikura more than made up for it. The scallops are also nicely seared and succulent, and the capellini is well-cooked and al-dente. The chilli oil adds a spicy kick that wasn't too overwhelming for Bb but did come across as slightly cloying towards the end. If you love all things spicy, this is the dish to get!⁣
⁣
𝗠𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮 𝗟𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲 was a safe choice as the beverage to go along with the pasta. Shall pop by for other creative concoctions soon~ 👍⁣
.⁣
📍 Address: 35 Kampong Bahru Rd, Singapore 169355⁣
