Looking for Sat nite hangout ? Home to the best of SG craft beers!  @goodluckgoodluck.sg  is a newly rebranded concept, and were formerly called Good Luck Beerhouse; housed amidst an eclectic mix of shophouses along Haji Lane, dedicated to representing the local craft beer community. Serving the best of Singaporean beers, alongside Asia-inspired cocktails, local stir fry, burgers, and dim sum, it’s still great to #drinkforgoodluck at here. 

𝑾𝑯𝑨𝑻 𝑰 𝑯𝑨𝑫: 
◾ Golden cereal fish & chips ($17):  CNY specials only - beer battered seabass fillet deep fried in cereal, chili & curry leafs. Tons of thick cut skin on fries. 
◾ Szechuan fries ($10): Great bar bites along with ice cold craft beer. AHHHHHHHHHH~.
◾ Katsu Curry Godzilla ($15): Butter milk fried chicken cutlet in Japanese curry gravy.  BEWARE, open your mouth big to sink your teeth in. Juice might splatter. Get ready some napkins. 
◾ Osmanthus White Negroni ($18): Bombay sapphire gin,	DOM, Osmanthus, Martini dry vermouth - Refreshing and light. 
◾ The General Lager than life - Pilsner 4.2% alc ABV.

Overall, the vibes is good, cozy place for catch ups, and pretty airy.  Reservations required. 

📍  Goodluck Beerhouse 9 Haji Ln, Singapore 189202 +65 6391 9942 .

HOUSE SIGNATURE Of @tartzy_tarts -  Orh Nee Tarts and Walnut Milk Tarts, with fresh homemade Orh Nee and Walnut Milk.  Each petite tartlet is low in sugar (natural sweetness of the ingredients) and made from scratch with fresh fillings all in small batches. 

𝗪𝗛𝗔𝗧 𝗜 𝗧𝗥𝗜𝗘𝗗:
◾ Mini Lava Orh Nee Tarts with Pumpkin crust (set of 6pcs $8.40): best seller, each tartlet is of mini bite size, with pumpkin mixed into the crust. The orh nee filling is freshly grinded, really smooth & creamy, not too sweet nor overly yam-my.
Yam Paste (orh nee) is signature Teochew dessert. Sweet pumpkin balances out the creamy yam paste - and there you get a heavenly perfect match flavor. The Orh Nee Tarts’ crust has slight orange-y color due to the pumpkin. 
Tarts can be kept refrigerated up to 5 days.

◾ Walnut milk Tarts (set of 2 pcs $8.64) : 1st in Singapore - rich, smooth nutritious walnut milk paired with crumbly tart crust. Walnut milk is a plant based milk, low in carbs, fat & cholestrol, with high protein & fiber. So you indulge without any guilt.
Each walnut milk tart is made from freshly grinded walnuts, so 100% guarantee freshly made upon orders.

@tartzy_tarts has other flavors of tarts such as Grilled banana choco, apple cinnamon, mango oreo, oreo freshmilk, and even Yam paste cheesecake tarts.
FREE delivery for order above $25, otherwise delivery fee is $9.

Order at: tartzy-freshstew.com.sg/collections/tartzy-tarts

@championflagship has been ranked as the world 1st Bolo bun concept store with its super IG-worthy aesthetics inside the cafe and its famous Bolo bun! 

We had the following; 
Classic with butter 
✨crunchy, golden-brown top resembling the texture and look of a pineapple. 
✨ Firm on the outside with a sweet, crumbly crust, and soft and fluffy texture on the inside, it is a messy but delightful eat overall! 
✨ loved the rich savoury flavour from the melted butter, which balanced out the sweetness of the Bolo bun overall. 
✨ one different thing about their Bolo bun is their thick and buttery crust, which would be perfect if it could be more crumby? 

Original Bolo bun 
🥐 Pretty similar in texture to the butter one we tried but personally we prefer their butter bolo bun more. 
🥐 personally enjoyed the fluffiness of the bread alot! 

Champion’s Milk Tea $5.50 – 6.00
✨ pretty thick and flavourful, and intense in its tea flavour, which kinda reminded me of the Yuan yang i had in Hong Kong 

Champion’s Coffee $5.50 – 6.00
✨ the coffee was pretty good, though i would appreciate a more intense coffee flavour and less sweet. 

Verdict - it is worth the queue? 
✨ it is good to try their butter bolo bun and for the cafe vibes, but taste wise I personally feel that it was not as overwhelmingly good as i have expected it to be. 

P.S Don’t forget to check out their promotion for 10% off 1 premium tea + 1 bolo bun, till 13th Mar 2022

📍 Championflagship 
92 Tanjong Pagar Road 
Opening hours: Tues- Sun
11am - 7pm

Located in the stretch of popular cafes In Tanjong Pagar, @aliceboulangeriesg is situated at Icon Village and has been known for its fine selection of French desserts and pastries. 

I received a range of pastries from @aliceboulangeriesg and this is what I have tried out; 

Sea Salt Chocolate Tart - $10.30
🍫 A decadently rich chocolate tart with a pinch of sea salt helps to intensify the flavor love how this balances out the taste, leaving a tart that is not overly creamy and sweet at the same time.

Yuzu Tart (Contain Alcohol) - $13
🍋 Delicate Yuzu curd, this tart has a bright and refreshing taste with a slightly bitter aftertaste from the Yuzu peel. 
🍋 We enjoyed this flavor the most, and most importantly their tart base was firm, and not overly crumbly yet with a buttery mouthfeel! 

Lychee Raspberry Croissant - $7.50
🍒 Well-balanced flavours, of both tartness and sweetness together, 
🍒loved how beautifully presented the crossing was, with chewy lychee bits inside, and smooth vanilla cream. 

Pistachio Chocolate Croissant - $7.50
🥐 This croissant, in particular, stood out the most to me, with its beautiful green and brown stripes, 
🥐 It has a nice crispy exterior, and buttery fragrance from the crust, filled with distinct nutty pistachio cream and pistachio bits. 
🥐 Loved how the chocolate cream gives that extra creamy and bittersweet mouthfeel to the croissant. 

Curry Chicken Puff - $8.60
🥯 Crispy and flaky pastry, which was not overly buttery nor oily at the same time. 
🥯 The chicken curry filling was pretty fragrant and savory with the right amount of spiciness would be perfect if the fillings can be a little more! 

Their bakes are also available in Savoury box (a mix of croissants, Pastries box and the All times Favourites, their pastries are also available for takeaway and delivery!

Delivery from; 
12- 4 pm on weekdays, 
12 - 5 pm on weekends.

Review: 
✨ this is definitely a cafe that i would pop by soon! Do give them a try and share with me your views! 

📍Alice Boulangerie 
12 Gopeng St, #01-05/
11 Icon Village, S078877

Opening Hours; 
Sun- Thurs 8 am - 6 pm
Fri- Sat; 8am - 9 pm

Desserts are the fairy tales of the kitchen—a happily-ever-after to supper ~~ Terri Guillemets

Come by this beautiful cafe located along Tanjong Pagar Road, and you will be in for a great dessert experience with your loved ones! 

Literally spoilt for choice from their wide range of desserts and trust me you will be back for round 2! 

We had; 
Mango Cake - S$9.50
🥭Juicy mango cubes layered in vanilla sponge complemented with bavarois mousse.
🥭 A personal favourite for me, i loved how the mousse was light and airy and most importantly it is lightly sweetened, blended with the tangy mango cubes which balanced out together. 

Strawberry St Honore - S$9.50
🍓 Baked pistachio frangipane in almond tart shell, strawberry macaroon and strawberry chantilly cream.
🍓 totally mesmerised by this beautiful tart, paired with juicy and sweet strawberries and smooth strawberry cream! 

Raspberry Puff- S$9.50
✨ Choux Puff with cripsy outer layer of craquelin and filled with raspberry cream.
✨ slight tangy flavour, a pretty refreshing tart for me! However it would be perfect if the choux puff shell could be slightly more crispy! 

Matcha Mont Blanc 
🍰 green tea cream, chestnut mousse, almond tart 
🍰 the matcha was not as intense as i thought it would be, but certainly decent enough for my liking! 
🍰 Was pleasantly surprised by the roasted and nutty flavour from the chestnut cream inside the tart! 

Botanic Garden Tea 
🍵 green tea, white tea, rose petals, lemon grass, elder flower, ginger and natural flavouring 
🍵 Perfect for pairing with your desserts! 

Pop by this beautiful cafe for some high tea with your GFs today! Their cakes are also available for delivery/takeaway! 

📍 Delicatesse 巧彰
102 Tanjong Pagar Rd 088523,

Want to have a meal under the STARS? 💫

Visited @seoulgoodsg at Punggol East Container Park for some Korean food the other day! I got the Grilled Chicken Ricebowl ($12.90) - the grilled chicken was cooked well, with crispy skin and tender flavouful meat! A simple ricebowl packed with Korean staples such as kimchi and pickled radishes, it was truly a hearty meal!

Their Chicken Jajjangmyeon's ($10.90) thick black bean sauce was more savoury than sweet and the dish also had plump noodles which we liked! 💖

📍 Punggol Container Park
🥢 7/10

OOZEY grainy black sesame paste sandwiched between two crisp-thin slices of bread, this Black Sesame Toast ($3.50) from @coffeebreakamoy is one that rivals my favourite Kaya Butter Toast from Ya Kun! 🤤✨ I especially loved how their black sesame paste had a more liquid-like consistency as compared to the thick kind! However, I felt that the black sesame paste was on the sweeter side and I would have preferred it less sweet. You can also never go wrong with butter in toast 😍

My friend and I also ordered their earl grey cream toast ($3.50) which features bread prepared the same way but with a filling made of earl grey infused whipped cream 😌 This was quite delicious, but I'm still a black sesame kind of gal 🤪

Ordered the black sesame kopi which was disappointing because it was literally just grainy black sesame in kopi (and the black sesame sinks right to the bottom). The black sesame didn't add any flavour whatsoever to the kopi at all, but it was $3.50 for a cup 🥶

On the flip side, the butter pecan vanilla ($4.50) we ordered was super delicious 😋 It tasted like a Starbucks drink (but cheaper!) - sweet and creamy!

Overall, I would be back to have my black sesame toast fix again and again, but I wouldn't get their black sesame kopi 😗 They also serve many other unique flavours of toast and drinks, which I would be back to try!

📍 Amoy St Food Center, Coffee Break
🥢 8/10

Glutinous Rice Bowl < 糯米饭>
This delicious sticky rice is packed with meat, mushrooms, dried shrimps, fried shallots, and premium lap cheong (Chinese sausages)🤎❤️

Recipe (5-6 servings)
Ingredients:
- 3 cups glutinous rice, soak for at least 3 hours
- 6 dried mushrooms, soaked and sliced 
- 80g-100g dried shrimps, soaked and minced
- 300g pork or chicken, cubed
- 2 Chinese sausages, sliced and roasted 
- 4 shallots, chopped 
- Free onion, chopped 
- Cooking oil, salt, oyster sauce, sesame oil, light and dark soy sauce, pepper, water or chicken stock (I estimated the amount used)

▪️Marinate meat with oyster sauce, sesame oil, light soy sauce and pepper.  Chill it for at least 2 hours.
▪️ Prepare seasonings in a bowl - oyster sauce, light and dark soy sauce, salt  and pepper.  Combine well. Keep aside for use later. 
▪️In a heated wok, add oil and sauté separately the chopped shallots, mushrooms, dried shrimps and meat.
▪️Add drained glutinous rice and continue to sauté with all the ingredients for a couple of minutes until well combine. 
▪️Add seasonings and continue to sauté for about ten minutes. 
▪️Add water bit by bit as you sauté.
▪️Turn off heat and drizzle with sesame oil. 
▪️Transfer to a big bowl and steam it in a steamer on high heat for 30 minutes. 
▪️Use chopsticks to fluff the rice and drizzle more water. 
▪️Close the steamer lid and let it steamed for another 15 minutes. Turn off heat and let it cool in the steamer until serving time. 
▪️Add roasted Chinese sausages or lap cheong on the rice. Garnish with cut green onion. 
▪️Served it with homemade chili and stir-fried veggie of your choice. Enjoy!

Waffles burger for lunch today. This is flourless version of waffle! Because 姐姐 here cannot take flour as it rises my blood sugar. 

A very simple way of doing, all you need is just eggs and mozzarella cheese. Swipe 👈🏻 to see the video on waffle making.

I love the taste of the cheesy! 

Ingredient for waffles:
• 2 Eggs ( enough for 2 pieces- depending on ur waffle maker size)
• 1 tsp of Garlic Powder (optional)
• Handful of Mozzarella cheese (Own Preference)

Method:
• Add garlic powder to egg and stirred well.
• Heat up the waffle maker and brush with butter.
• Add some mozzarella cheese
• Add a portion of the egg (own judgement)
• Cover it till it firms.
• Add on some cheese and pour a bit of egg
• Cover it up till a bit brown then served! 

Ingredient for burger:
• 2 Waffles
• 1 Chicken Breast Patty (I made my own) 
• Lettuce 
• 1 Slice of cheese
• Cherry Tomatoes 🍅

description: Here's to those trying to make a difference to their lives
Life brought us to unexpected places but fate keeps us together
Life is a corridor of open and closed doors

📍Around (AMK) 

got my waffles & gelato fix at a cosy and minimalist dessert cafe nestled in the heartlands 🌾 there was nobody at all on that Friday afternoon, very chill vibes and the staff was friendly! 

𝐇𝐚𝐥𝐟 𝐖𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 + 𝐒𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐜𝐨𝐨𝐩 ($8) 

redeemed the Burpple 1 for 1 deal so it made up a full-sized waffle and 2 scoops of house-made gelato. 

the 𝘄𝗮𝗳𝗳𝗹𝗲 🧇 was served THICK and golden-brown, already indicators of a mouth-watering good waffle. the crispy exterior and soft, fluffy cake-like insides provide a wonderful textural contrast and the fragrance of the buttermilk batter is exceptional too. topping it off with some drizzles of maple syrup 🍯 , crushed caramelised Biscoff biscuits 🍪 and dusting of icing sugar. every bite was pleasantly addictive and nowhere near to cloyingly sweet. truly a top-tier waffle! 💯

moving on the gelato🍦they didn’t have a lot of choices that day but all’s well because both flavours we got were SO GOOD and highly recommended! 👍🏼

𝗯𝗹𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝘀𝗲𝘀𝗮𝗺𝗲 was rich, earthly, aromatic and flavourful - you can tell it’s made from pure, grounded black sesame seeds. at the same time, it wasn’t too bitter and there’s a nice balance of sweetness and milkiness like a gelato should be. 😋

𝗽𝗲𝗮𝗻𝘂𝘁 𝗯𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 was another classic and as a huge PB fan, i can vouch that this is super well-executed! 🥜 imagine those indulgent, ultra fragrant, nostalgic old school peanut butter tubs you can find in neighbourhood bakeries but in a creamy gelato form. it’s rich but not too salty or sweet. 

💸 $8 for such quality waffles and gelato?? super worthy deal with Burpple Beyond and i would 101% come back again! 🥰 btw seems like the prices at the Alps Residence outlet are slightly more expensive but the glasshouse concept is so pretty~

#waffles #gelato #wafflesandicecream

📍Munchi Delights 

finally headed down to Yishun Park Hawker Centre to try the IG-famous and generously stuffed 𝐌𝐮𝐧𝐜𝐡𝐢 𝐩𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐚𝐤𝐞𝐬! 🔥

[NEW] 𝐋𝐨𝐭𝐮𝐬 𝐁𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐟𝐟 ($1.80) 🍪

calling all 𝗯𝗶𝘀𝗰𝗼𝗳𝗳/𝘀𝗽𝗲𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝗼𝘀/𝗰𝗼𝗼𝗸𝗶𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿 fans, DO NOT MISS THIS! 😍✨ @munchidelights’ new flavour is a pure 100% Lotus Biscoff™ Crunchy spread - no frills, no watered down version. 👍🏼 biting into this Biscoff goodness makes me forget about traditional MJK flavours for a moment to savour this wonderful fusion of modern-meets-tradition. 😋 never thought the sweet and fragrant caramelised biscuit spread could pair so well with the soft kueh-like pancake! 

🌟 9/10 

𝐁𝐞𝐥𝐠𝐢𝐚𝐧 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 ($1.80) 🍫

true to testimonies of the many high-praising reviews out there, this chocolate is indeed of 𝘀𝗼𝗹𝗶𝗱 𝗾𝘂𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆!! 💯😮‍💨 far from those artificially sweetened kind, this is lusciously rich Belgian chocolate with bitter cocoa notes and only a tinge of sweetness - a dark chocolate fan’s dream come true - and only at the cost of $1.80! 🤩 got this with 𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝘁𝗲𝗮 𝗽𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗮𝗸𝗲 and i could taste the subtle hints of green tea 🍵 but definitely the decadent chocolate is the overpowering flavour. 

🌟 9/10 

overall, $1.80 for an indulgent sweet treat is super value for money! based on foodies’ reviews, there’re some hits and misses with the wide array of flavours but i would highly recommend these 2!! ate half chilled and half heated up and BOTH ARE DELISH 😛

#minjiangkueh #lotusbiscoff #belgianchocolate

📍Two Bake Boys [collab] 

@twobakeboys’ beautifully crafted crepe cakes with lots of love and dedication are not only ✨IG-worthy✨but also boast a delectable taste. 

each delicate layer is soft, pliable, and slightly chewy. the crepe cake and fresh cream layers come together nicely to give a delightful springy bite. cake flavour is on the milder side, yet natural and distinct. love that their crepe cakes are not too sweet which means you can go bold with drenching them in their respective sauces for max indulgence! 

𝐁𝐨𝐱 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝟗 ($62) comes with 9 unique flavours, some of which are their new launches for September.

𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐢 𝐓𝐞𝐚🧋
the signature OG flavour - fragrant and creamy Thai milk tea made with authentic tea leaves sourced from Thailand 🇹🇭

𝐓𝐡𝐚𝐢 𝐑𝐨𝐬𝐞🌹
a harmonious blend of earthly tea and floral notes.

𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐁𝐚𝐧𝐚𝐧𝐚🍵🍌
soft caramelised bananas embedded in the layers + rich matcha sauce go so well together with the cake!

[Fruit series] 𝐂𝐨𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐮𝐭🥥, 𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐨🥭 and 𝐇𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐲 𝐃𝐞𝐰🍈 come with chunks of fruit flesh that give an added natural sweetness and refreshing texture. my fav is the tangy mango!

𝐍𝐞𝐚𝐩𝐨𝐥𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐧🍓
top layers are strawberry flavoured while bottom layers are chocolate flavoured - an old school combi that doesn’t go wrong. 

𝐇𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐬 🍼
brings back nostalgic memories of a childhood coffeeshop drink. unique take on a cake flavour and it was well-executed! 

𝐎𝐯𝐚𝐥𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐞🍫
as a chocolate lover, this is definitely my no.1! ❤️ decadently rich chocolate sauce with crunchy Ovaltine pop to top it off really elevated the Ovaltine-flavoured cake, and it’s not as sweet as it looks! 

turning the Covid crisis into an opportunity, and fuelled by a passion for baking, @twobakeboys was born. it now has its own brick-and-mortar takeaway shop at CT Hub 2 (Lavender), do check them out! ☺️

thank you Kitty @twobakeboys for sending these lovely crepe cakes over! 🙆🏻‍♀️ 

#crepecake #sgbakery #supportlocalsg

📍Onkei Tonkatsu (Paya Lebar Square) 

this 𝗢𝗢𝗭𝗬 𝗖𝗛𝗘𝗘𝗦𝗬 𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗸𝗮𝘁𝘀𝘂 🧀 has been on my mind ever since i saw @weitingforfood’s mouth-watering review! 🤤 

𝐂𝐡𝐞𝐞𝐬𝐞 𝐑𝐨𝐬𝐮-𝐤𝐚𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐒𝐞𝐭 ($19.90++) 

what’s not to love about a thick slab of pork loin generously slathered with deep-fried golden brown panko breadcrumbs and stuffed with oozy, melted and stretchy mozzarella cheese? 😍 take a bite of the tonkatsu and be greeted with the ultra crispiness and fragrance of the batter that is pleasantly light and not greasy. 

the rosu (pork loin) is tender, juicy and lean with a small amount of fatty parts. however the consistency could be improved as some parts are a bit tough and dry. 

the cheese is a wonderful addition as it cuts through the heaviness of the meat, creating a delightful savoury and cheesy indulgence. 😋 i highly recommend this cheese and tonkatsu combo!! it really gives a whole new tonkatsu experience. 💯

𝐌𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐤𝐨 𝐑𝐨𝐬𝐮-𝐤𝐚𝐭𝐬𝐮 𝐒𝐞𝐭 ($19.90++) 

while the cheese was perfect, we felt that the pure cod roe (mentaiko) was a tad too concentrated, salty and spicy. the umami kick is very strong which kind of overpowered the meaty tonkatsu taste. mentaiko purists might enjoy this super rich salted roe though! 🙈

🍚 each set comes with a choice of white or brown pearly Japanese rice, Tonjiru soup (miso soup with soft pork, radish and mushrooms), pickles and a generous heap of shredded cabbage paired with roasted sesame sauce. 

🌟 9/10 for the cheese tonkatsu!! everyone PLS TRY IT!

#tonkatsu #cheese #japanesefood

📍Tamago-EN 

𝐒𝐨𝐮𝐟𝐟𝐥𝐞 𝐏𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐚𝐤𝐞 ($8.90++) 🥞

first time trying soufflé pancakes and ITS TRUE it really feels like biting into a cloud! ☁️ jiggly to the touch, these thick and round pancakes are ultra soft, fluffy and airy - each bite literally melts in your mouth. the pancake is eggy and fragrant, and pairs perfectly with the light fresh cream. the accompanying maple syrup and dusting of icing sugar enhanced the overall sweetness to a nice degree 👍🏼 i love it! except the brown exterior was a bit over-burnt and dry. 

🌟 8.5/10

𝐒𝐨𝐛𝐨𝐫𝐨 𝐊𝐢𝐦𝐜𝐡𝐢 𝐔𝐝𝐨𝐧 ($10.50++) 🍜

Chinese + Korean + Japanese fusion dish?? there was a generous amount of savoury minced pork stew, kimchi, radish sprouts, spring onions, and a fresh, raw egg yolk to top it off. 😍 this dish is very flavourful but the kimchi taste was too strong and overpowering that i couldn’t really taste the stew and yolk… on the other hand, the inaniwa udon is PERFECT! slightly thinner than the usual udon so it’s not as starchy but the bouncy and chewy texture remains. 💯

𝐌𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐢𝐤𝐨 𝐒𝐚𝐥𝐦𝐨𝐧 𝐂𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦 𝐎𝐦𝐮 𝐑𝐢𝐜𝐞 ($15.90++) 🍳

highlight of this dish is definitely the beautiful swirl of silky smooth, semi-cooked omelette enveloping the fragrant butter rice beneath. 😋 the omu rice comes with spinach, salmon and roe doused in cream sauce that is not too heavy or jelak. sadly, the mentaiko taste was lacking.

𝟓-𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐦𝐚𝐤𝐢 𝐓𝐚𝐦𝐚𝐠𝐨 𝐒𝐤𝐞𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐬 ($9.50++) 🥚

these tamagoyaki (Japanese omelette) skewers come with 5 different toppings: tomato, seaweed, salmon, mentai mayo and zuwaigani (snow crab). my fav is the mentai mayo that is so rich and umami 👍🏼 the other flavours are pretty good too except the seaweed tasted kinda weird. 

🌟 7.5/10 (mains and sides) - quite pricey for standard egg dishes but hey, you’re getting some quality Japanese egg 🤩

It’s a snoozy mid-week and I decided to get a cuppa from @bimbocoffeesg! Ended up ordering a couple of them as I could not make up my mind and the plethora of coffee offerings at @bimbocoffeesg were just too tempting!!

Bimbo Coffee offers the conventional coffee like black and white coffee and also really unique flavours like yuzu and cinnamon. The coffee is brewed to order and the flavours are infused by the Bimbos themselves! The beans that they used are chosen carefully to match the different profiles and they use a variety of beans for different flavours to bring out the best in each of their coffee!

I tried the rose, mint, melon and red dates flavoured coffees and also their white coffee! You can choose whether you would like to have your coffee sweetened or unsweetened when you order them. My favourite would have to be the red dates coffee because the coffee is slightly on the stronger side and leaves my caffeine cravings satisfied!

Do check out the handcrafted coffees @bimbocoffeesg if you are longing for some caffeine shots or a cuppa creamy coffee!

• Korean foooood • 😋🥘
Korean food for lunch! Shared a few dishes with my friend who also enjoy Korean food! 

• Kimchi tofu soup: Soup arrived bubbling hot and tasted good! Had a well balanced sourness and spice. Quite a generous amount of ingredients + rice provided!

• Tuna Kimbap: Tasted fresh and refreshing 🤣 I like how each of the pieces looked different as it was hand-cut. Quite yummy.

•Tteobokki: Chewy as usual but the sauce is a bit strange? It was more on the sweeter side than savory/spicy. Overall taste was so-so.

• Japchae: Very springy and had a strong aroma of sesame oil. Quite addictive but the portion was quite big and can become a bit jelat after awhile.. 

• Banchan/side dishes: 6 free side dishes was offered! I enjoyed the crunchy kimchi most and we even got a free refill of it (upon request) 🤣. The spinach and the rest was also tasty except for the random cold pasta dish that tasted very out of place.. 🤔

Overall, the food tasted authentic and good. 👍🏻

• Mee Hoon Kueh • 🥢
Best comfort food to have on a rainy day! Been having their ban mian/mee hoon kueh for some time before their recent relocation. I love their MHK cos I get to see them flattening the dough using the manual machine and tearing it into many pieces. I like how irregular each pieces are and it’s so chewy yet soft 😋. My parents prefer their Ban Mian and the noodles are v smooth! The soup seems lighter than before but still good. Do support them if you are nearby! 👍🏻
location: 阿發面粉粿 - Ah Huat Mee Hoon Kueh

description:
• White Bee Hoon • 🥢🥡
Dad brought this back for dinner hehe. It was nice and savory but just too salty for my liking.. Would prefer it to be less salty. Overall, it was still quite yummy!
location: White Restaurant - The Original Sembawang White Beehoon

description:
• Ice cream • 🍦🍧
Throwback to Jan when I tried this for the first time! My friend said that their ice cream is “damn nice” and I was quite excited to try it. Unfortunately, I found it so-so only 😫.. this was some lychee sorbet flavour and it was nothing special. Maybe it was the flavour that I got? 

The cone was made on the spot and contained some spices. Unfortunately, I found the spices in the cone quite yucky— oops? I just didn’t like how it tasted in the biscuit. I would get the cone next time if they have an alternative cone version WITHOUT spices.. 🤣

• AGLIO OLIO!! • 🍝🌶
Happy PH everyone! Made some Aglio Olio for lunch today with le fam and the prawn was the star today! Enjoyed the food and also the time spent cooking. 🙌🏻

Year of the Tiger 🐅 Wishing everyone to be bold and fearless. Happy Chinese New Year! Love to you all. 🧧 💫 ❤️

こんにちは‼️
つ、遂に2年ぶりにありつけた、旨過橋の🦑ゲソ天そば。
メンバーN口親分の巧妙な口車に乗って、もとい、貴重なアドバイスに従って、比較的お客さんの少ない10:30すぎにピットイン。先客3人で、セーフディスタンス🙆🏻👌✨。
今日は若干薄めに感じる暗黒汁も、ゴロゴロゲソ天との相性はまさに最強‼️
金ちゃんの目の前で食べましたが、一瞬「んっ⁉️」と言う顔しましたが、何の問いかけも無く、黙食完了😊。大満足💯の370円で、ご馳走様でした‼️😋

おはようございます‼️
宿泊先のホテル周辺には、ちょっと歩けばかなりの数の立ち食いそば屋があります。本日は課題店の一つであった御徒町の鶏だしそば･うどん三丁目を初放浪。お父さんとお母さんの気持ちの良い挨拶が印象的。300円の朝そばもめっちゃ魅力的ですが、初心の通り今日の海鮮三点盛りをチョイス。鶏と生姜の効いた出汁が良いですね～。好みも別れるでしょうが、自分的には◎ですね。次回は必ず朝そば行ってみたいと思います。
では今日も張り切って参りましょう～‼️👍

description: Goatfish or some said Red Mullet is so delicious! Watch the video on my YouTube channel tonight #homecooking #homecooked #homecook #homecookedmeal #homecookingisthebest #homecooks #homecookedfood #seafood

Spicy Thai Chicken Indomie

@Indomisg  has a special taste and enjoyment. You don't need a lot of additional seasoning to feel the pleasure. Add a little topping like Thai-style chicken which is spicy and delicious with a sunny side up on top will be so perfect

Full recipe below:

1 serving

Ingredients 
1 pkt. Indomie Mi Goreng Original
150 gr Minced Chicken
1 pcs. Chili Padi
1 pcs. Large Chilli 
¼ pcs White Onion 
2 Cloves Garlic 
3 Stalks Holy Basil Leaves 
1tbsp Soy Sauce
1tbsp Oyster Sauce
2tbsp Fish Sauce
½ tbsp Sugar 
1 pcs egg

Cooking the Indomie
	1.	Boil noodles for 3 mins
	2.	Put seasoning on plate, drain noodles once cooked, and mix well.	

Spicy Thai Chicken
	1.	Add cooking oil to the pan
	2.	Using medium heat, sauté garlic, onion, large chili, and chili padi until fragrant 
	3.	Add in minced chicken, 
	5.	Pour in Soy Sauce, Oyster Sauce, Fish Sauce, and Sugar.
	6.	Stir until the chicken is cooked, turn off the heat 
	9.	Add in holy basil leaves stir for 30 secs
	10.	Serve with Indomie Mi Goreng Original and sunny side up

✨Toa Payoh Lucky Pisang Raja✨
Omggg I keep finding myself going back for more Goreng Pisang🍌🤭particularly from this shop in Toa Payoh‼️ I walked passed this shop many times but never really had the chance to try it until my BFF 👭 highly 💯 recommended it and raved 🗣 abt how good 👍🏻it was; I couldn’t resist any longer🤤🤤

It really didn’t disappoint!!! SOOOO DELISH🤪 Before I even bite into it, the batter on the outside already looks so good????😱 #notsoggy (Looks 👀 ultra crisp🤩🤩) It’s fried till a perrrfect golden brown😜

MmmmHmmm Crispy and warm on the outside but sweet 🍌 & creamy on the inside😌

Even after having a few, I find that it wasn’t too jelat☺️; smth I look 👀 out for in deep fried foods because if done wrongly❌, it can be really greasy🥲 & unappetising🥴

Hehe my turn to recommend it to you guys!🥰 Though they specialise in Goreng Pisang🍌, they sell other fried items too! For example, Fried Chempedak, Fried Sweet Potato 🍠 Sesame Peanut 🥜 Balls, Fried Sweet Potato 🍠 etc……Can see myself going back for more!!😁

Featuring 📸
~ Goreng Pisang 🍌 
~ Fried Sweet Potato 🍠 Sesame Peanut 🥜 Balls

Sometimes, the small little things can be touching too!

My friends and I arranged a gathering on Sunday and so happened that my hubby has an official meeting and couldn't take care of our son, so I decided to bring my son along with me for the lunch gathering. During the lunch, my friends teased my son asking if he brought money to pay for the meal. My son replied that he did want to bring his wallet but daddy said that mummy will have less worries if I don't bring money. Later on, when I got home, my hubby told me actually our son did plan on dipping into his piggy bank so that he could bring enough money to take care of his mummy. Oh....so sweet of him! And, during the meal, he was on his best behaviour throughout and making sure that everyone had a good time.

Dish of the day @mouthrestaurant :
Mouth-watering dim sum includes Salted Egg Yolk Bun (Must Try! Life-changing, so good), Crispy Chopstick Prawn (Crispy and delicious), Deep Fried Prawn Dumplings, Pan Fried Beancurd Roll (one of my favourite dish), Egg Tart (my son's favourite dish) and steamed Prawn Siew Mai etc.

Every day can be a fresh start!
Do not like the way things have been going, why not just start afresh and find ways to fix things until you like them!

Grocery shopping used to be a chore as have to go to different places to get the best deals for different things, now everything can be shopped online and delivered, so much time and money saved.

@tankfullyfresh - they delivered fresh and frozen seafood to your doorstep and even offer free delivery above $60. 
1. 150 - 200g of codfish- fresh and no fishy smell, so suitable for steaming.
2. 500 - 600g of red snapper - the fish comes fresh and already thoroughly cleaned, so no hassle to have to de-gill and clean the fish yourself. Can just rinse and it is ready to steam.
3. Canada Scallop 200 - 240g - Fresh and soft, not chewy or rubbery at all.
4. Frozen Tiger Prawn 1kg - juicy prawns

Thank you @thefitureco for arranging & @tankfullyfresh for the seafood.

Make time to listen to each other!

Sometimes, when we are home and busy with our own stuff, we hardly pay attention to what the people around us are saying. My hubby always says that he told me something already but I have no recollection of it at all! Sometimes I even think he might be hallucinating - Who did he actually tell the message to? 

So, a good idea is to have a nice sit down meal and switch off all devices so that we can listen to each other attentively.

@booncafe.sg @itespore:
1. Curry chicken with country loaf - SGD6.00. The country loaf is so fluffy and nice, if only the cafe can help to heat it up a bit will be perfect.
2. Cafe Breakfast - SGD7.00. Fluffy egg with the same nice country loaf and a nicely dressed salad.
3. Black coffee - SGD2.50. The freshly ground coffee aroma is totally awesome.

Is the season of the year again where we are blessed with all the nice cuisines and joyous people around us.

Happy Chinese New Year to all in advance.

Thank you @botanictsg for sharing this Nonya CNY Special:
1. Babi Pongteh - The Babi is a mixed of Soya and Konnyaku.
2. Sambal Pentai Seafood - The seafood are made of Konnyaku to give a chewy texture and this is one of my favourite as the sambal is so good.
3. Ayam Buah Keluak - Ayam is made of gluten and is so flavourful with the unique taste of the Buah Keluak.
4. Nonya Curry Fish Head - The fish head is made of beancurd and seaweed. It absorbed the appetising gravy very well for a fantastic taste explosionon my tongue. 

All dishes are allium free and plant based. Good not only for vegetarians but for anyone taking a break from meat!

I’cook Dinner: Giant Scallops & Prawn Dumpling Ramen in Tonkotsu Broth with Greens.
*
These scallops are 2 inches in diameter. Very sweet. Defrost and just simmer them in the tonkotsu broth. My tonkotsu broth is home-made from pork bones. You can use a pressure cooker to make a batch and then freeze. Added some dashi to boost the umami flavours. The prawn dumplings were wrapped in advance and frozen. Just cook them when needed. Noodles cook briefly for 40sec and then quench in cold water to maintain the QQ texture of the noodles. Assemble all ingredients and pour the broth over. Sprinkle over spring onions and sesame seeds as garnish.
*

I’review: Jin Jin’s Durian Red Bean Shaved Ice Dessert.
*
This dessert stall at ABC Brickworks is famous for their 流氓冰 (Gangster Ice), which actually sounds like 榴芒冰 (Durian Mango Ice). I find the combo of durian and mango a little too heaty for me, so I opted for durian red bean ice instead. The durian puree is really not bad. Real durian puree. The red bean is throughly cooked and soft. Not too sweet. They drizzle some condensed milk on top for the ice. Again, not too sweet. The dairy taste is just nice. Not bad for a try.

I’review: Yi Sheng Prawn Hokkien Mee, ABC Brickworks Hawker Center.
*
This prawn noodles stall at ABC Brickworks hawker is actually quite famous. Today i see, wha, only 2 people Q-ing faster buy. End up waiting for 35min because there is a snaking invisible Q. Partly because the uncle cook slowly for the wok hei and only do a few plates at a time instead of one whole wok together. The uncle is frail and the auntie got attitude. Will probably loose this stall in 10 years. The wok hei is there and the taste of the gravy is not bad seriously. But at $5, there is only 2 tiny prawns so i feel short changed. You can tell from the greyish brown colour of the gravy, there is wok hei and there is char. The smells is not bad. The chilli spiciness is also just right. But will i wait 35min for this? I don’t think so. It’s very good plate of Hokkien mee but it is not in the WOW category. If you want to be wowed, try the wow wow west.
*
Price: $5 nett
Rating: 7.9/10
*

description:
Celebrating my dear friend @sandy_lavignedor and my birthday at Claudine Restaurant. 

I would like to call this restaurant @chef_julien Royer’s (of 3 stars Odette) home kitchen.  The restaurant name is homage to his dear mother and the food inspired by his childhood memories of his mother’s recipe and traditional French dishes. The menu is extensive and the main courses are designed to be shared, just like in a family meal. I get intimidated by food so fanciful I don’t know what I am eating or have to guess. Thankfully the dishes here are straight forward and come with multi-layers of texture and flavor. So guessing a bit of the ingredients needed but it is fun as you try to re-engineer the recipe!

Corkage policy here is 1 for 1. There are some wines here that are pretty reasonably marked up. In fact I saw a Champagne that was priced lower than I bought retail! I guess importing their own wines helped with that. 

Menu:
Organic Egg Forestiere- A panko crusted egg over baby spinach, black truffle vinaigrette and topped with 40 months parmesan shavings had me mopping up the sauce and yolk so clean, the server who came back to clear the plate thought he send me an empty plate!

Saint-Nectaire Croquettes- topped with a dallop of savory Vin Jaune gel and filled with umami-licious oozy cheese from Auvergne. I think the standard serving should be 6 and not 4. 

Chou Farci - Stuffed Cabbage stew. Stunning! I will need to find words to describe it. I will dedicate another post just on this. 

Pariterole- I wished for a dessert out of the kitchen, and not a cheese selection as suggested. It was lovely! Vanilla cream, textured by the pecan praline and the crust with lavish dark chocolate sauce, I prefer this over a cake!

Good morning and Breakfast is ready 🌞🌞

Well, as a wise man once said, practise makes perfect. Therefore, I am practising my bread baking again. This time, to begin with my experiment, I added 5 more grams of water to the original recipe into the dough. I want to achieve a super fluffy and soft bread. 

During the kneading process, after the dough had fully absorbed the butter, the dough became more sticky as I kneaded it. I panicked for a moment.

However, I didn’t give up, otherwise I wouldn’t have any bread to eat 😂 So, I continued kneading the dough nonstop by using both the stretch-and-fold, as well as the slap-and-fold methods. It took me quite awhile before I was able to knead the dough till it was smooth. I also used abit more oil this time to assist me with the sticky dough. Oil is good for this soft bread as it locks in the moisture of the dough.

I want to perfect this versatile sweet dough bread so that I can add different kinds of fillings for my daily consumption. I will then move on to more challenging bread types.

Here is my version of the sweet bread with additional 5 grams of water. I inserted some pork jerky as fillings for this bread. Super soft and fluffy, I like it! Self bake is definitely superior to store-bought, as it is cheaper, healthier and more hygienic. 

Will be trying other bread designs soon, Akan Datang in Malay, coming soon in English.

Happy Sunday to all here.
.
.

It is so rare these days to find any hawker or restaurant selling this classic Singaporean Cantonese version of curry beef brisket noodle, 咖喱牛腩麵.

I used to eat this for lunch during my school days in a nearby coffeeshop next to the school. Sadly, this coffeeshop is no longer in existence. However, some good food memories will linger in your mind for the rest of your life. Do you have such an experience or is it just me? 

All of a sudden, a craving for this curry beef noodle returned to haunt me. I just have to cook this dish to satisfy my cravings. 

Finally, this is very own version of the curry beef brisket noodle. To be honest, I can’t really recall the taste of a dish that I have tasted donkey years ago, but I remember it being so good. Humbly speaking, I had my cravings satisfied with my version of the melt in mouth curry beef brisket with noodle it was really yummylicious. I will definitely cook this dish again. Simply irresistible.

Friends, blessed weekend.
.

description:
Finally I cleared all my mandarin oranges. I baked this Chiffon Cake using my remaining mandarin oranges. I squeezed the juice earlier and freeze it.

Chiffon is one of the cakes I baked the most. The more I baked the more confident I become. My first attempt in sharing my cake ingredients. As for the process, you can refer to my earlier Chiffon process which is parked in my profile highlight (my apologies, i m still learning how to express it in writing. Give me some time) 🙏🏻🙏🏻

Offered this cake to my siblings’ family as I m still on a no carb diet. They loved it. I received very good feedback, the cake was so soft and fluffy. The mandarin orange taste was what they love most. 

Still going strong on my fifth day no carbs no sugar diet.  As of todate I lost  2 kg 💪🏻💪🏻 looking forward to my cheat day next week. Now thinking of what to cook on that cheat day 😂😂 

Friend yay … it is Friday ✨✨do have a blessed  weekend 🤗🤗

Ingredients:-

[Dry]
Cake flour - 100 gms
Sugar - 75 gms (maximum reduction 20%)
Baking Power - 6 gms

[Wet]
Egg yolk - 4 
Vanilla Essence - 6 gms
Orange Juice - 88 gms
Oil - 55 gms

[Meringue]
Egg White - 4
Sugar - 100 gms
Cream of Tartar - 2 gas

1 whole orange zest (include during the folding of the batter n meringue)
.
.

Splurged on steak for the first time and it was a wonderful experience. Read lots of raving reviews on this place that’s been conferred one of the best steakhouses in Singapore. I went for the Tajima Wagyu Tenderloin after discussing the price with my wallet. They age their own beef and grill their meats over an Argentinian Parilla which I’ve learnt is not very commonly done. I had mine medium rare and because of the aging process in the cabinet, the red juices (myoglobin + water) doesn’t ooze out of the meat when you cut into it. Every bite was a delight, full of flavor and juiciness. Yes, it’s worth the damage on my wallet. 
The little bottle of palate cleanser, a mix of Bourbon whiskey and apple juice, prepares you well for the gastronomic experience before they serve you your steak. 
I’m writing in reverse order but the loaf of bread came first as an appetizer. It was warm and fluffy on the inside, crispy on the outside, and went superbly well with the butter and salt. I tried very hard not to finish it to leave space for the steak. Not to forget the shot of pumpkin soup which I also loved. 
Thoroughly enjoyed every bit of my meal! Since I was seated right in front of the open kitchen, I also enjoyed watching the chefs at work, with one feeling the music and doing little dances while she prepared her dishes. 
#sgsteak #steakhouse #skirtrestaurant #wagyubeef #sgfoodies

IM ALIVEE (long due posts sorry)

Eggslut 🍳🥚
Fairfax 6.5/10 
WAS SO EXCITED FOR THIS BUT disappointment 🤢🤢 this is like inferior to the Mac's scrambled egg burger.. Super jelat because of the generous amount of eggs so I really struggled to down this. Could have more cheese & caramelized onions to add more dimensions to this! Bun was diaappointing as well because it didnt have the brioche sweetness i was expecting :( very fluffy though!

Truffle hashbrowns 7/10 
Honestly really crisp and loved the bite-size but some were tasteless while others super salty >< truffle taste wasn't the strongest but i liked its faint aroma! if youre gonna try this because you love truffle,, i'd say give it a miss 

Overall will not go back again, I prefer shake shack HAHAHAH

All Day Breakfast Club @ HV! 7.5/10 affordable and decent quality in general, portions pretty big too!! I got the: 
1. All Star Plate with Pancakes 
2. Rosti with Sausage
3. Pink Lemonade

Loved the pancakes because they were so soft, fluffy and slightly sweet 😋😋 scrambled eggs were creamy and the potatoes were fried well with seasoning that tasted like Calbee chips HAHA. I felt like the Rosti was generally well fried but I remembered Marché's one to be better, loved how the sour cream complemented it and wished there was more! I also really enjoyed the pink lemonade because its a good refreshing drink that went well with the heavy meal, plus it was super cute that there was a layer of sugar coating the top part of the drink 😃 retro vibes bit service a bit 🤔🤔

HELLO GUYS WE’LL FINALLY BACK WITH BREADY REVIEWS 😎

✨Steep✨

1.  French toast ($17)
Comprised of broiche, mascarpone, berry compote, maple granola, fresh fruits, toasted almonds and HONEY THYME SYRUP. This dish did live up to its expectations with the super fluffy and soft broiche. The best part was prob the mascarpone bc it was mild but managed to balance the overall sweetness of the dish. We recommend trying the honey thyme syrup on its own first to see if you like it before drizzling. Tbh on its own, the honey thyme syrup tasted nice to us but might be a bit too much when drizzled onto the French toast which is already sweet on its own. The syrup also tends to bring out the sourness of the berries so drizzle at your own risk ⚠️ HAHAHA

2. Grilled cheese ($11) 
The grilled cheese was perfectly toasted without any burnt parts. The two types of cheeses (smoked cheddar and Edam) added another layer of dimension to the taste. The caramelized onions 🧅 were a great addition. Overall all the flavours came together really well! We recommend to eat this fresh and hot 👌🏻

All in all, we used burpple and it came down to $20 in total (+ additional $0.30 for iced water) which we felt was really worth it given the big portion served and standard of the food!

SUPER ADDICTIVE COOKIES 7.5/10🍪

SORRY FOR THE INACTIVITY GUYS but midterms are killing me and unluckily for me, it extends way beyond week 8, and all the way to probably finals 🥲 

To cheer me up, my friend gave me these cookies and my oh my, I couldn’t stop myself!! Super crispy, crunchy, loaded with chocolate chips and nuts!! HOW TO STOP??

description:
4 more places to grab quality dumplings in Flushing! 
•
📍Tantou King’s Fuzhou Fish Ball
41-18 Main Street
This shop is tucked away in the back of what looks like a corner store. The price is another example that you don’t always have to pay extra for quality! These dumplings were my favorite on this part of the crawl. Bonus: They also have peanut butter noodles for $3 👀 ⭐️ 9/10
•
📍Nan Xiang
39-16 Prince Street
Another restaurant known for their xiao long bao, I would have never thought to order their steamed dumplings! The meat was juicy and flavorful. They gave me a xiao long bao vinegar but I think they needed some good chili oil!⭐️ 8.5/10
•
📍Best North Dumpling Shop
41-42A Main Street
This unsuspecting shop is located inside a quiet mall. They make a huge variety of dumplings and some big steamed buns. The dumplings were boiled fresh to order. I wish they had a bit more flavor but great for the price! They also sell frozen dumplings to take home! ⭐️ 7/10
•
📍 Mr. Easy
133-35 Roosevelt Avenue
Located in the New York Food Court. Aunties wrap the dumplings at the counter! Their chili oil was a great supplement to their dumplings! ⭐️ 7.5/10

Prawns are fat and juicy, there’s also shredded chicken and egg slices inside.

09:00 - 17:00 weekdays.

description:
#throwback to last week when lamian got to try these handmade kuehs! Lamian's human have been trying to get these several times but was unable to, until last Friday! The kuehs were very colourful, well-made and fresh! Lamian's favourite was the abok abok sagu with the gula melaka, and the lapis sagu (the rainbow coloured one 🌈 😍). The kueh texture was Q and very fragrant which brings joy to the various senses.

The kueh salat was good too, but lamian would like it with a bit more rice cos lamian likes the blue-ish rice 😅 The box was really big but the variety in the box was great as lamian's family all had different favourites. Till the next time! (If we get lucky again hahaha)

#lamian #travel #lamiantravels #minions #despicableme

Good morning! Here's one of lamian's favourite toasts to have - honey butter toast from @thehainanstory 😋 a cup of tea/coffee, two half boiled eggs and toasts is a typical breakfast dish here, although you can have it throughout the day too 😅 

Lamian liked the toast here so much, lamian came back to have it again the very next day and the following week! The toast was nicely toasted, and was light and fluffy. Imagine a thick cut of French toast hahah! And the mix of honey and butter was a nice combination of sweet and salty! Lamian liked the teh-o here too which wasn't too astringent and had a nice tea fragrance 😊 lamian will be back for more!!! 

#lamian #travel #lamiantravels #minions #despicableme

Good morning! What are you having for breakfast? Lamian is very excited to use lamian's new In The Soop cup for a cup of honey mint to go with the two slices of cake from Serangoon Garden Bakery. Lamian really likes the butter cake here that's light and fluffy with the nice buttery fragrance that's not too overpowering. And of course, the banana cake 😋 lamian was a little too late and the bread were sold out, but if you're in time, do try the bread too! 🍞

Also, check out lamian's flower that has just bloomed 😊

#lamian #travel #lamiantravels #minions #despicableme

After all the feasting over CNY, lamian had to take a lot of cooling food to quell the heatiness. So lamian was very happy to hear of the chrysanthemum aiyu jelly from @ninefresh Lamian likes to have ninefresh desserts that are very hearty in its portions, taste good and affordable at the same time 😁 

The chrysanthemum aiyu jelly has hints of the floral taste and fragrance which made it a joy to eat. Lamian likes the grape pearl jelly too which was nice and fruity but not too sweet (tastes very much like grapes too!) 🍇 Lamian will definitely be having this again before this special dessert goes off the menu. 

#lamian #travel #lamiantravels #minions #despicableme

description:
@downstairs_sg (by @songfabkt) has probably one of the most affordable meals that you could get at @sunteccity! 

We tried:
• Lu Rou Fan $6.00
• Salted Egg Chicken Nasi Lemak $8.90
• Kaya Butter Toast Bun $2.60
• Kopi/Teh $1.30 each 

Lu Rou Fan (aka braised pork belly rice) with lava egg is reasonably priced and comes in a legit portion. The pork belly is pretty well braised and has a good combination of lean meat and fats, very well marinated and braised, thus giving a tender texture!  I also like how they added a generous portion of the pickled sour mustard to this dish, its savoury and sourness does helps to balance the greasiness of the braised pork and also opens up your appetite for more food! 😆

Salted Egg Chicken Nasi Lemak on other hand wasnt really what i would prefer. The rice is light, fluffy with nice coconut fragrance and pretty flavourful. But the crispy chicken was tough and the batter was kinda thick. The salted egg sauce is smooth but comes with very subtle salted egg taste. But the sambal chilli was pretty good though. 

The toast bun is fluffy, but not those toasted crispy ones if you expecting for those. But its still pretty good to go with a cup of kopi and teh with it! 

🍽 Downstairs
📍3 Temasek Blvd, B1-132 Suntec City, Singapore 038983

Saturday Lunch Menu:
@original_botak_jones's wildly popular Cajun Chicken - Char Grilled Chicken topped with melted cheese! 

Chicken tasted very flavourful, well marinated and pleasantly tender and juicy!  We chose cajun fries and colesaw as our sides. I particularly like the crinkle-cut Cajun Fries as they are typically crunchier than straight fries and also more flavourful too because they are able hold more spices and seasoning on them. The colesaw, on the other hand, tastes pretty mediocre, so if you dont like colesaw just go for other sides ya.

Heard so much rave about @syip.sg's tiramisu and I thought I should give it a try since tiramisu is easily one of my favourite desserts!

We tried:
• Kahlua Tiramisu $10++
• Creamy Chicken Scrambled Egg Croissant $16++

The Kahlua Tiramisu is a super comforting treat for anyone who loves Tiramisu! My favourite tiramisus are usually those containing kahlua (coffee liqueur), especially those that has a good balance between coffee and alcohol! Cause very importantly, Kahlua elevates the coffee aromas! IMO, this Tiramisu pretty much fits the bill! The coffee liqueur steeped sponge fingers taste like an almost perfect balance of the coffee and alcohol. Its further nicely completed with smooth mascarpone cream that has great consistency between fluffy and mousse-like. I know it’s a sinful indulgence, but I bet you will be just like me – can’t stop after the first spoon. Lol.  

Creamy Chicken Scrambled Egg Croissant features a croissant blanketed with the creamy chicken, mushroom, and soft scrambled egg. The croissant itself is not too bad, its fluffy and fragrant. When eaten together with chicken & mushroom pieces and soft scrambled egg, it gives a very full bodied and rich texture. But tbh, I don’t think it’s a very special dish, but probably still worth giving it a try anyway. :)

🍽 SYIP
📍79 Owen Rd, Singapore 218895

WOOD-FIRE DINING EXPERIENCE
 
Visited a fancier restaurant for our anniversary, here’s what we had. 

•🍞Assorted breads with homemade seaweed butter; the breads were so soft! 🧈The butter so good it deserves a photo of its own.

•🦞Lobster Bao; like a mini lobster roll. Lobster chunks served on deep fried charcoal mantou. Yums!

•🦪Grilled Normandy Oyster with caviar & nage; not bad but not our favourite. And both of us had bits of shell in the broth as we slurped the oysters down.

•🐷Western Plains Pork; pork belly, pork neck, pork leg and pork fat. This was our favourite dish of the night! All the different cuts of meat were tender and flavourful while the deep fried pork fat adds a different texture to the dish.

•🐟Grilled Seabass; seemingly ordinary grilled fish but they’ve removed the bones of the fish and it’s then dry aged. You can taste the nice flavour of the fish without any fishiness.

•🥩Australian Wagyu Striploin; recommended medium rare. Look at the beauty, the marbling. It’s cooked by taking the beef on and off the heat several times so it’s cooked to perfection instead of the outsides being more cooked and insides extremely rare.

•🍡Matcha Mochi; Complimentary as we were celebrating our anniversary. Thank you Butchers Block!

Lovely food with friendly wait staff.

🌟🌟🌟🌟
💰💰💰💰💰

📍Butchers Block
328 North Bridge Road, Raffles Arcade 02-02 to 02-07
Singapore 188719

TAIWANESE FOOD
How can we not order the 3 bowls set when the eatery is named Eat 3 bowls?

What the 3 bowls consisted of:
•Braised Pork Rice
With a good mix of fatty bits, it gives the melt in your mouth feel. The rice had generous amounts of gravy too. Tasty.

•Shredded Chicken Rice
Shredded chicken topped with fried shallots atop a bowl of rice. I was pleasantly surprised that the rice was drenched in sauce. Not at all dry and so appetising. Comfort food.

•Oyster Pork Intestine Mee Suah
The Mee Suah broth was a bit on the watery side, not too starchy (I actually like it this way). The Mee Suah was firm and not too mushy. Served with braised pork intestines, a piece of plump oyster and a dollop of minced garlic. Delish.

Also added on sides of egg and braised cabbage 🤩

Our choice of drinks:
~Fresh Milk with Grass Jelly - check out the glass full of grass jelly! But would request for less sweet next round. Like that they serve with metal straw too.

~Iced Coffee - the coffee is in the form of a piece of ice shaped like a polar bear on ice. The coffee will melt into the milk to give you ice coffee. Cute!

Overall, enjoyed the food and will be back again. However, we over-ordered for 2 pax this round. Will order lesser next time!

📍Eat 3 Bowls
462 Crawford Lane
Singapore 190462

Saw @dazeliciousss recommendation and I went to check out @sevenskissaten for brunch! Thanks for reco!! 👍👍

We picked Chicken Stew Thick Toast (S$19) and 7S Breakfast (S$32). These are all day breakfast menu items! To complete the meal, I also ordered 7s Cream Latte (S$8).

1️⃣ 𝘾𝙝𝙞𝙘𝙠𝙚𝙣 𝙎𝙩𝙚𝙬 𝙏𝙝𝙞𝙘𝙠 𝙏𝙤𝙖𝙨𝙩
The chicken stew was very rich - it contained chicken chunks, potatoes, broccoli, carrots, cheese and mushrooms. It was served in thick chunky toast (such a cute presentation!! 🥰). I like how they served 2 slices of toasts on the side as well. I enjoyed dipping the toasts in the stew - the toasts really soaked up the stew so well! The stew did get a tad bit jelak towards the end but thankfully the saltiness of the miso soup managed to help me get through it! That aside, I wanna give credit to their almond salad too! It was so so fresh - veg were so crunchy and almonds were so crispy!

2️⃣ 7𝙎 𝘽𝙧𝙚𝙖𝙠𝙛𝙖𝙨𝙩
This is their signature breakfast Omakase breakfast set in a single serving! The plate's unique layout was something I have never seen before. Highly recommend this 7/8-course signature dish. I believe they switch up the dishes every now and then as I have seen a couple varied dishes online. Overall, I really love this set and the dishes went well with the sticky Japanese rice and miso soup. Yums! 😋

3️⃣ 7𝙎 𝘾𝙧𝙚𝙖𝙢 𝙇𝙖𝙩𝙩𝙚 
The drink was very creamy and sweet. Tho the latte was pretty nicely brewed, I felt it's a lil overpriced. Shoulda ordered the normal latte instead .😅

Saw that they have really pretty desserts but we were too full to order more 😂. Definitely will return again to check them out!!

Location📍: Tiong Bahru
Nearest MRT 🚆: Tiong Bahru EWL

So yesterday, my dad and I took leave to spend the afternoon together. It has been perhaps 2 decades since we last spent time one-on-one talking and just enjoying time together. Then, it was my dad bringing me to the playground and playing with me. Yesterday, it was 2 ways – us catching up on each others’ lives and talking about the mini adventure/journey I’ll be embarking on in a few months’ time. 

The time spent was particularly significant to me – having worked for a few years, I started to catch a microcosm of what my dad (and my mum) do just to provide for the family. It was no longer the idea of ‘parents making sacrifices’ that I thought of when I was younger, but rather, it actually hit me how much it actually mean – time, finances, housing, car, vacations (air tickets, accommodations, food), insurance, food, medical and other bills and taxes, the activities my sisters and I want to learn (ballet, piano, Chinese calligraphy, arts and craft, and others..) and their love and care despite having only a mere 24h just like everyone else. 

To my dad who hardly says ‘no’ to me, to my dad who says instead, ‘lets try this’, ‘lets go’, ‘(lets do it) for the experience’, ‘lets have fun’, ‘(not to) be penny-wise and pound-foolish’, to my dad who always remind me 'it's the memories and the people that count, rather than the things (materials / food / places)', and to my dad who supports me in the various things I do (despite not exactly agreeing / being concern, such as my ‘new journey’), words can’t express how I truly feel. 

Thanks daddy <3

(Last pic: we arrived and my dad's phone rang... and he had to answer a work call 🥲, thankfully there wasn't any other calls for that afternoon)

After trying @noce.nuts ’s hazelnut butter, when @kneadandpinch approached me about her bread and how she would be incorporating @noce.nuts ‘s cashew nut butter, I was rly excited! 

Featured here is @kneadandpinch ‘s Walnut Cashew Banana Bread ($26 - family size). As a huge fan of nuts, @kneadandpinch ‘s version of banana bread is definitely an elevation of the usual ones. Imagine the lovely crunch of walnuts within the banana loaf that adds texture to the otherwise soft and moist bread. That’s not all, now add to your imagination the crisp and freshness of almond flakes sprinkled on a drizzle of @noce.nuts ‘s cashew butter, atop the banana bread. Can you feel the nuttiness of this banana bread!! I love @kneadandpinch ’s creativity in incorporating not only the usual walnuts, but also cashews (in terms of butter) and almonds (in the form of flakes) into her bread – this is definitely the first for me. Besides this, you can expect the combination of textures, from the soft and moist banana bread to the crunchy walnuts, the crispy almond flakes, and finally the creamy and rich cashew butter. Taste-wise, I found the banana flavour not as strong as I expected, and this makes her banana bread more acceptable by a larger audience, where those who don’t fancy banana might be able to accept – like my mum who not only accepts but finds the cake nice. What I particularly appreciate is how @kneadandpinch does not skimp on the ingredients and the generous amount of nuts in her bread is definitely a selling point to a nut lover like myself. Additionally, I also like how her bread has just the right sweetness which makes it great for breakfast, supper, or tea.

"Spaghetti, Jumbo Lump Crabmeat, Shaved Parmesan, Spicy Pomodoro Sauce with a touch of Cream"

• Southern Chicken and Waffle $22++
Ordered without looking at the photo or reading the description and was surprised to see the waffle as a charcoal one! Was surprise after tasting the waffle -- there seems to be honey on the inside. While it's nice on it's own, it might be a tad too sweet for those who intend to have it tgt with the chicken. Quite a worth item to get especially if you love variety in your food! It consisted of buttermilk fried chicken, charcoal waffle, potato gratin, served with a side of salted egg yolk sauce, maple syrup and butter. 

• Umami Roasted Chicken ♡ $23++
This was like SO GOOD?? We initially didn't plan to order this but we're so glad we did. Lovely pizza crust that felt somewhat laminated and reminds me so much of a croissant. The ingredients were plentiful and the whole pizza was of a good size and so flavourful. Would definitely order this again.
"Marinated Roasted Chicken, Dashi Sauce, Roma Tomatoes, Jalapeno, Mayonnaise, Bonito Flakes"

• Latte $5.5++
Perfect end to a lovely meal!

My colleague L's farewell @yardbirdsingapore . It was originally supposed to be at blu kouzina but I ain't a fan of Greek food, esp after my trip to Greece in 2019. So one of my colleagues decided to change the location to sth I'd very much prefer 🥰.

We ordered:

• Mac & Cheese $14
Five artisanal cheeses, crispy herb crust
- I love the one at Bread Street Kitchen and decided to suggest getting this 🧀

• Lobster & Shrimp Roll $32
Avocado, brioche, celery, house salt & vinegar chips
- Was thinking of this as well cause Lobster roll hahah 🦞

• The Great American Burger $29
Short rib, brisket and chuck blend, double patty, house-smoked pork belly, american cheese, house pickles, special sauce, house fries 
- Just look / read the description! A hearty burger indeed 🍔

• Lewellyn's Fine Fried Chicken $34
1/2 of our famous bird served with honey hot sauce
- Strongly recommended by one of my colleagues 👍🏻

Didn't have photos of the Fried Chicken -- which is supposed to be the most insta-worthy.. cause i was getting super embarrassed when my table which consisted or 3 middle-age guy colleagues, turned their phone torch on and tried to shine on the food, and added that they usually see ppl doing that 🤣. But what was funnier was when they finally realised (after turning their torches off) that the photos taken without the torch had a better lighting 🤣🤣🤣 -- swipe to the 2nd pic for a over-exposed photo.

But anyways great time, good service, nice food!

O Coffee Club High Tea (2 - 6 pm)

One of the high tea that ends late ~ 6pm, so my sisters decided to bring me after their work/school. Special thanks to one sis for planning this at the very last minute after we shifted from lunch to dinner to accommodate the other sis and hence changing location too ❤ and also the other sis for literally running with her 'white cape' past the doctors and patients to get the car and drive us to the location with 15mins to order ❤. 

There are 3 of us and @ocoffeeclubsingapore didn't allow the addition of tier for one pax, so we decided to try their all-day-breakfast instead.

Tier for 2:

◇ Sweet
• Scones: Chocolate and Raisin (I love scones in general and @ocoffeeclubsingapore 's chocolate/ raisin scones are those that I'd go back for)
• Mini éclairs
• Cakes: Matcha and Tiramisu (while the matcha was very mild and we couldn't rly make out it's taste, I found the tiramisu good!!)

◇ Savoury
• Truffle Mushroom Vol Au Vent (the texture was not what we expected but we like it this way! And this was our fav of the items)
• BLT Sandwich (my sisters like this, they said even the bread was nice)
• Tarts: Egg Mayo and Tuna (we found the tart shell to be a lil too sweet to be tgt with the egg Mayo and tuna)

◇ Drinks: found this very limited: only Americano or Gourmet Tea are included. We chose Special Breakfast (which tasted like the usual English Breakfast) and Berries Blossom (which reminders me so much of Coffee Bean's).

All day breakfast:
Smoked Salmon Eggs Benedict
Eggs done nicely and my sisters love the Smoked Salmom.

Special mention to their service! We ordered an extra chocolate scone to takeaway and was asked if we wanted it then or later, and we opted for the latter. However, after our meal, my sisters were thinking of the cake their ordered for me, while I was thinking of heading Laderach.. and we totally forgot about the scone. Was on the escalator when the staff from @ocoffeeclubsingapore ran and handed the bag with our scone in it. Thank you @ocoffeeclubsingapore for being so attentive and alert :)

Who doesn’t love Maritozzo? The dough-based bun fully packed with sweet whipped cream in the middle. Also known as Sweet Roman Bun, this classic is found in every bakeries in Italy’s capital city.

There is a sweet tradition behind these sweet buns. The name Maritozzo derived from the word “marito” in Italian words means husband. In the 19th century, men would propose on the first Friday of March to the women they love, by presenting the engagement ring hidden inside a maritozzo. That is sweet ha…
The first Friday of March is yesterday, and I am one day late, and here presenting the maritozzo to my husband and daughter. ❤️❤️

We don’t think we could have survived this winter without soups, and this has become one of our favorites 😋
The Kway Teow soup in the picture is from Mrs. Kway Teow, a small and authentic Thai restaurant in Shuk Ha’Carmel with traditional Thai dishes like soups, Som Tam (papaya salad) and even desserts like sticky rice 😍
Kway Teow soup is a traditional (and hot! 🥵) Thai noodle soup, considered a whole meal on its own, and in this restaurant it comes with rice noodles, chicken dumplings, chicken stock, sprouts, canna (green Thai vegetable), scallions, fermented Thai chili pepper, chili jam, look chin gai (chicken balls), Wonton cracker and crispy garlic 🤩
אנחנו לא חושבים שנוכל לשרוד את החורף הזה בלי מרקים, והמרק הזה הפך להיות אחד המועדפים עלינו 😋

do you like lemons?
because I think they are sublime

pair this with rice and there goes a flavor explosion in your mouth 

chinese style lemon chicken 🐓 
INGREDIENTS
250g chicken breast,washed, pat dry and cut into bite-sized pieces
½ tbsp soy sauce 
2 clove minced garlic🧄 
1 egg🍳 
salt and pepper to taste🧂 
lemon zest🍋 
3 tbsp corn starch

for the sauce
1 tbsp of oil
2 cloves minced garlic
90ml water 
lemon juice from half a lemon🍋 
2-3 tbsp sugar🍬
1 tbsp soy sauce 
1 tsp vinegar
1 tbsp honey🍯 
lemon zest (optional)
2 lemon slices
cornstarch slurry(mix 2 tbsp water with 1 tsp cornstarch) 
 
for garnish
sesame seeds
chopped green onion🧅 

STEPS
1.marinate chicken with soy sauce, salt and pepper, garlic,ginger,egg and corn flour and mix well until chicken is well coated, set aside for an hour

2.in a pan, heat about 1 inch deep of oil and fry chicken for 7-8 minutes or until golden brown.set chicken aside

3.to make the sauce, heat 1 tbsp of oil in another pan and fry garlic till fragrant (not burnt) then add water ,lemon juice,soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, honey, lemon slices and lemon zest 

4.taste test now to check if sauce is too sour, if it is too sour, add in another additional 1 tbsp of sugar

5. remove lemon slices

6.at this point, add in your cornstarch slurry and boil for 6-7 minutes or longer and mix occasionally until sauce thickens

7.mix the chicken well with the sauce 

8.garnish,serve with rice and enjoy ☺️

hey there, donut scroll, keep on watching🥰🥺

what’s the healthiest part of a donut? 
the middle. 😙😙

these are one of my favourite donuts and I’ll always get them whenever I see a stall selling these😝

kuih keria 🍠 
malaysia sweet potato donut 
INGREDIENTS
250 g orange sweet potato peeled and sliced
pinch of salt for boiling potatoes 
1 tbsp glutinous rice flour
80-100 g all-purpose flour, depending on how wet your sweet potatoes are, so agar agar it and go by feeling

sugar coating
2 tbsp white sugar
2 tbsp water
flour for dusting at the end, to prevent sugar coating from dissolving when it cools 

STEPS
1.cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for about 10 minutes or until soft
2.drain the potatoes and mash them up 
3.mix in rice flour and all-purpose flour and knead till you get a dough, the amount of flour you add depends on how wet or dry your sweet potatoes are, you should get a soft and not so sticky dough
4.with greased hands, cut dough into 8 and roll them into balls
5.poke a hole in the center with your finger to create a donut shape, and repeat with the rest of the dough 
6.pour about 1 inch of cooking oil to a pan and fry the donuts for about 7-10 minutes, flipping regularly( if bubbles form on chopsticks, the donuts are ready to fry)
7.to another the pan, add sugar and water. 
8.stir constantly, until the sugar dissolves and the mixture becomes bubbly and thick, turn off the heat and add in the fried donuts and make sure they are well coated in the sugar mixture
9.sprinkle some flour over donuts and mix. now, the sugar liquid should have changed into a sand-like consistency.
10.let cool slightly before serving and enjoy☺️☺️

📍Cold Storage at Compass One
🚇 Sengkang

I'm really loving the refreshed Cold Storage at Compass One! It's not just beautiful, it's sustainable as well. Fun fact: Their counter fronts are made from reclaimed wood and most of the fixtures are clad in bamboo! 

For those who know me, you'll know that I'm calorie conscious 5 days a week, so that I can eat anything I like on my cheat days. Yong Tau Fu is definitely one of my go-to healthy meal choice. I appreciate that there are over 50 ingredients I can choose from the Fresh Yong Tau Fu Station so that I can be pick ingredients I like and watch my waist line at the same time.

Steam fish is one of my mum and grandma's favourite dish to cook as they believe it's nutritious and good for the body. They were happy to see the wide variety of fishes they can choose from. Plus, Cold Storage offers free prep services such as descaling, deboning, fillet and more. The staff over the counter were very friendly and helpful. You can just let them know what you're cooking and they will prep for you! 

Truly enjoyed my grocery run at the newly refurbished Cold Storage at Compass one! Come visit and have a great shopping experience like me!
.
.
.
.
.

description:
📍 Awfully Chocolate Bakery & Café 
⏱ 29 January 2022, 10am

Searching through my album and found these back log that I had yet to post.

I was offered by @awfullychocolatebakeryandcafe to try out their Bakery Club Brunch at 50% its usual rate.

It was an awfully awesome brunch that started chocolaty with their Really Fresh Chocolate Milk served first, made with awfullychocolate 100% Premium Dark Cocoa freshly frothed with premium chilled Hokkaido milk. 

It was followed by its Breakfast Fruit with awfullychocolate Cacao Granola. As always a fan of chocolate these are pretty much meant for me.

Next, we were surprised by The Bakery Club Fresh Bread, with Roasted Aubergina baked upon ordering and cut right on our table infront of our eyes. The aroma that got into our nose are overwhelming.

The Truffle Cream Eggs was then served immediately. 

Overall, we were really in love with their bread and I am so happy to see their “[Members Only] FREE Bread Tasting with our Head Baker!” email in my inbox this week that I am going to head there tomorrow. 😊

description:
📍Old Habits Café 
2 Telok Blangah Way SAFRA Mt Faber #01-04 S098803

Old Habits Café is located 2.4km away from Harbourfront MRT Station, hidden jn Safra Mt Faber.

This nostalgic café definitely gonna bring you back in times and stir up some of our childhood memories.

As I thought we will be just indulging in the unique vintage ambiance, their food surprised me too.

Here are what we had tried last night:

- Sesame Crusted Tuna Steak ($18.90)
This steak is crusted with sesame on the outside and rare in the centre. This made it warm with crisp on the outside, cooler at room temperature in the mid, easy to chew upon and almost feel like they melt in your mouth. Dipping the tuna in their homemade sesame sauce add on to the umami and elevate it to the next level.

- Classic Chicken Chop ($9.90)
Although its called the classic chicken chop, it’s definitely better than what you had in your western food stall. The chicken thigh was well roasted to char, coated with their homemade seasalt caramel sauce, each bite into it is tender, juicy and flavourful. 

- Old Habits Coconut Kueh (Pouffle) ($9.50)
First time seeing a “Pouffle” and decided to go for it. “It’s texture between a Bread Pudding and Souffle, hence "Pouffle". Aromatic Shredded Coconut, Topped with Vanilla Bean Ice-cream” as described on the menu. I can’t add on my description but this is how real it is and pretty much amazed us by how good it is.

Our drinks we had “Old Habits Float” & their “Home Brewed Kiwi and Strawberry Tea”.
Old Habits Float is actually Rum & Raisin Ice-Cream on Kickapoo. Kiwi and Strawberry Tea carries their flavours well. Both drinks are so refreshing.

We love our time here pretty much enjoying our delicious dinner with the nostalgic ambiance. Many thanks @oldhabitssg for the very warm welcoming service that make us feel really comfortable in your cosy place. 🙇🏻‍♀️

Thank you @getkobe for the invite and introducing this hideout to us.
.
.
.
.
.

Nu Er Hong Hotpot and Grill, a newly opened Korean seafood buffet restaurant in Tanjong Pagar Singapore, offering the largest selection of SEAFOOD on both hotpot and grill for just $39.80 ++ with over 80 varieties of seafood, meat, vegetable and side dishes.

description:
Save this place for your next bagel date!

Visited @monumentlifestyle a few weeks back and their extensive selection of New York-style bagels surely satisfied my bagel cravings.😮‍💨

The bagels (without fillings) came in five flavours - 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗶𝗻, 𝘀𝗲𝘀𝗮𝗺𝗲, 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱𝗱𝗮𝗿, 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗼𝗻. Along with the bagels came 3 different handmade schmears - 𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘄𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗿𝘆, 𝗴𝗮𝗿𝗹𝗶𝗰 𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗯 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗷𝗮𝗹𝗮𝗽𝗲𝗻̃𝗼 𝗰𝗵𝗲𝗱𝗱𝗮𝗿!🥯

I usually prefer savoury flavour profiles, but I fell in love with their crowd-favourite strawberry schmear. It had a sweet and pleasant tanginess that reminded me of haagen-dazs strawberry icecream.🍓We spent quite some time taking pictures so the bagels naturally became a little tough to chew (please don’t be like us…)

We also tried out a tasting platter for their signature sandwich bagels - 𝗹𝗼𝘅, 𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗸𝗲𝘆 𝗵𝗮𝗺, 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗶 𝗺𝗲𝗹𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗲𝘄 𝘆𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿. My favourite out of the lot is the 𝗹𝗼𝘅, which came with generous chunks of smoked salmon and tangy cream cheese that was light on the palate. The fillings were also packed really neatly so there’s no need to worry about the mess that usually comes with stuffed bagels.🥺

From now till end Feb, quote “thefluffypao” to enjoy 10% off food items till the end of Feb! You’ll have to follow both my account and @monumentlifestyle to enjoy this offer.‼️

Thank you @monumentlifestyle for the warm hospitality and @hungryshuen for extending the invite!!

Here’s an underrated burpple gem tucked away in lavender! 😮‍💨 

Visited @oberstrassesg last Friday and ordered their 𝗼𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 that came with a cushion of creamy and buttery scrambled eggs. I really enjoyed the silky texture of the eggs, but it wasn’t as fantastic flavour-wise. It felt a lil bland after a while and could definitely be elevated with some seasoning. 🍳

On the other hand, the chorizo was juicy and the mild spice made it even more flavourful (tasted like otah tbh). Bacons were also crispy with a good fat to meat ratio. Rosti hash was slightly disappointing though as it disintegrated easily and was also pretty thin. The veges had a nice crisp and were paired nicely with sesame sauce (yes, I wiped the whole plate clean despite being a non-vege lover😳). 

Overall, this was a pretty hearty lunch and portions were just nice!! The vibes were also laid-back with limited seatings available in the cafe. Total damage was slightly under $15/pax after burpple’s 30% discount. Definitely not the best deal out there but it’s pretty decent for the quality! This cafe is also less than a minute walk away from thai baàng so you can get your bread fix too while cafe hopping. 😆👌

‼️AFFORDABLE cinnamon rolls and fluffy brioche donuts from a not-so-hidden gem in the east! It’s my second time trying bakes from @puffandpeaks and I found my second experience to be a lot better than my first!! 

Ok firstly, the brioche donuts were HUGE and had an ideal 7:3 filling to dough ratio. I’m honestly pretty impressed that they held their shape really well and weren’t oily even after a day in the fridge. That made my life WAY easier when it came to taking pictures.😮‍💨 

I got the donuts in the following 4 flavours - 𝗱𝗮𝗿𝗸 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗲, 𝗹𝗲𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗰𝘂𝗿𝗱, 𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮, & 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮, but I only tried the latter two. Fillings wise, the 𝗰𝗮𝗿𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗯𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗻𝗮 stood out more to me! It tasted like an upgraded version of goreng pisang but without the greasiness. I was expecting a bittersweet umami filling from the 𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗰𝗵𝗮 donut but it was evidently absent. 😰

I know they’re most known for their donuts but their 𝗰𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗮𝗺𝗼𝗻 𝗿𝗼𝗹𝗹𝘀 take centre stage for me. They’re really fluffy and moist on the inside. And it was packed FULL of cinnamon flavours without being cloying. A pity that no one really raves about this. 🥺

Overall, I found them to be really affordable for their quality (~$3.50 each). Puff and peaks is located REALLY far from me but I’m thankful that group buys exist! I wanna try their black ssm friand too but it’s always not available in group buys.. 🥲

I have been eyeing on Gyunami ever since their old days at Amoy but they have relocated to Orchard!! I ordered their signature 𝘄𝗮𝗴𝘆𝘂 𝗯𝗲𝗲𝗳 𝗱𝗼𝗻𝗯𝘂𝗿𝗶 and it came with a glorious volcanic sous vide egg! 🍳

First off, the presentation was already a solid 10/10 for me. Taste wise, I liked that the beef slices were well seasoned and roasted medium rare. The egg yolk was flowy and it gave a creamy dimension to the overall dish. The yogurt sauce provided a slight tanginess but somehow the rice still tasted a lil bland. Maybe a truffle-infused rice might do the job. 🤪 

Overall, this donburi was good and reasonably priced, though nothing too mind blowing in terms of taste. The service was efficient but I didn’t particularly enjoy the ambience. There were pretty limited seats and it honestly felt even more cramped with all the soft toys surrounding us. 🥲

They are on burpple so the bill amounted to $12.50 for a donburi along with miso soup! It’s definitely a fuss-free meal option in town but don’t expect too much!!

You know CNY is coming when cafes start to introduce items with ORH NEE! 🤤 Tried @simple.cafesg’s yam swiss roll and yam nian gao donut and both CNY specials were pretty impressive!! 

𝗬𝗮𝗺 𝗦𝘄𝗶𝘀𝘀 𝗥𝗼𝗹𝗹
Tried A LOT of orh nee swiss rolls and this is surely one of the more memorable ones that I’ve had! There were rectangle chunks of orh nee embedded in the fresh cream and the cake itself was light and fluffy. The cream was also generous and it didn’t taste too overwhelming! 👌👌

𝗬𝗮𝗺 𝗡𝗶𝗮𝗻 𝗚𝗮𝗼 𝗗𝗼𝗻𝘂𝘁
I think this is the first time that I have seen nian gao in donuts and this combination surprisingly went pretty well!! The sticky, chewy texture of nian gao definitely gave more dimensions to the smooth and fragrant orh nee fillings, though it still got a lil jelak towards the end. Additionally, I liked that the donut wasn’t oily, but I wished that it was fluffier!! 

Also, I really liked the minimalistic interiors in this Taiwanese cafe with chill Mandopop music playing in the background. They do carry a humble selection of other Taiwanese-style bakes, and I’ll be back to try their signature sweet potato swiss roll! 🍠👊

Spiced chicken slices with lemon, garlic and zucchini. Topped with fresh parsley and chilli flakes.

We would definitely come back here again for more!😉

📍 Home 

Trying out my new thicccc peanutbutter spreads 🥯🥜 from @clerlife.malaysia ! I got all 4 types:

📌 Classic crunchy 
📌 Pure crunchy 
📌 Classic smooth 
📌 Pure smooth 

They were yummy and super peanutty 😍 The crunchy version had peanut bits in it for extra texture - perfect for eating/spreading on its own. The smooth version was glossier and good for using as a base to mix with other ingredients (like what I did with my toasts). 

The peanutbutter came with the option of classic or pure. The classic ones were sweeter and more flavorful in my opinion. The pure one was sugar-free and definitely a healthier option if you’re craving peanutbutter but also maintaining that diet 👀

I personally preferred the classic smooth peanutbutter as I like to have it on toast with either fruits or jam - and also because I have a sweet tooth 😋🍼

Overall, I loooved the peanutbutter from @clerlife.malaysia so do check them out! You can order yours today using the Shopee link in my story ⬇️⬇️:
