[📝 Review] Neptune’s Big in Japan (Scones) ($16.90)

✨ Soft warm bites ✨

Unlike other combinations, these came with both sweet and savoury dippings. For sweet, there’s the tangy sweet yuzu jam and honey mascarpone. For a cold refreshing savoury touch, there’s the cold shrimp and salmon in dill sauce. 

The Grana padano scone was buttery and oh so soft. Each bite broke off the slightly crisp exterior to reveal the warm tenderness. 

Rating: 8.8/10

P.S. Coffee is always good here!

[📝 Review] Rumour’s Beach Club Food Galore 🍕

✨ A place to chill & unwind by the beach ✨

Apart from the inevitable scorching sun, I would gladly spend my weekends at the beach sipping on wine while indulging in these delectable spread. 

🌶 Balinese Mixed Rice
Classic, a must get for me. The pieces of shredded chicken were well marinated. Beef chunks were tender and melty!

🍕 Rumours Pizza
Bigger in real life, it was riddled with beef salami, mushroom, basil, cherry tomato and black olive. It’s creamy and dripping in sauce. 

🍤 Calamari 🥠 Nachos
These are the perfect finger food to chill by the beach!

🍚 Indonesian Fried Rice
The concoction of shrimp paste sambal was extremely addictive. Dipped the crispy fried chicken and garlic crackers with it and there was no turning back. 

🍷 White wine
🍸 Margarita 

P.S. Food was great and I would love to go back again!

Overall Rating: 8.5/10

[📝 Review] Knockhouse Cafe’s FRENCH TOAST ($12)

✨ Fluffy soft pillows ✨

Beautifully presented, the toast was drizzled in salted caramel and sugar dusting with ice cream and seasonal fruits on the side. Each bite was greeted with a soft pillowy mouthfeel as the light buttery fragrance permeated through. 

P.S. It was so soft and light! Didn’t feel surfeiting at all!
Wished that there were more slices!

Rating: 8/10

✨ Ninja Foodi Dual Zone Air Fryer Review✨

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

The Ninja® Foodi® Dual Zone Air Fryer is the first air fryer with 2 independent 3.8L baskets that let you cook 2 foods, 2 ways, at the same time, not back-to-back like a traditional single-basket air fryer. 🔥

6 customisable programs: Max Crisp, Air Fry, Roast, Bake, Reheat, and Dehydrate.

I tried all the functions over the past week and look at all the things I made! 😍

I was blown away especially by the Dehydrate function. I used to buy dried pineapple rings and now I can make them myself! It turned out EXACTLY LIKE THE STORE BOUGHT ONES. Without any additional sugar or additives. Just pure, dried pineapple 🍍 rings! The perfect healthy snack 😜

Thank you to @ninjakitchensg for letting me review this amazing gadget as I can’t live without this in my kitchen now ❤️

Mono foods aims to reduce food waste by redistributing surplus food from distributors and redirecting them to those that needs it. I ❤️ that they also give back to the community by donating food to the less fortunate! 

As storage and logistics costs are high, giving them a like and subscribing to their channel would mean alot to their funding too! They also regularly stock new items and sell them at deep discounts! Up to 90% 😱

Some foods are approaching their best before dates and some are already past but are still perfectly edible just that stores are unable to stock these anymore and would have been discarded to the landfill.  Best Before dates are also usually printed on items with longer shelf life like packaged foods and cereal.

Only the 3 packets of snacks in this bundle is past the BB date but I have tried it and it still tastes crunchy and flavourful! THE SNACK REALLY TASTES LIKE CHURROS OMG

* Giveaway ends this Sunday 6/3 and winner will be invited to collect the bundle at their HQ at bukit merah. Feel free to shop around when you are there! 😉

Definitely one of the BEST tendon I have ever had!

[TASTING]

AUTHENTIC RUSSIAN DELIGHTS IN TANJONG PAGAR!

Despite the ongoing conflict, Dumplings.Ru @dumplings.ru are certainly doing things right by acquainting more Singaporeans with the wonders of Russian-Ukrainian food.

Highlights of my meal would definitely include the Dumpling Combo Platter ($19.90+). 

12 X dumplings, 12 X different fillings such as Paneer Cheese and Minty Ram. Super IG-worthy also la, for  the dumplings like rly colourful all👍

Another star would be the Ukrainian Borscht Soup ($9.50+). 

Wah, the soup really very power, it’s like thick and creamy yet so light on the tongue, v easy to swallow. Inside got stuff like pork, beetroot and tomato, and they all come together to form a crazy-good flavour combi.

The Cheese and Pork Chebureki ($12+) remind of 1x mahssive curry puff, minus the curry. Airy, crispy + savoury af, wah shiok!

If u aren’t already fawning over how amazing their star dishes are, try the Salted Herring or Seledka ($12.90+) or their interesting drinks, Kompot and Kvass (from $5.50+) , that u won’t find in any kopitiam I swear

We recommend: Combo Platter, Chebureki, Seledka, Borscht Soup (wish they had a buffet for at least some of their menu items istg🤩)

Main gripe: Prices for some dishes can be a bit high 

Overall: 4.25/5 (this place definitely needs more clout, we’d return again again and again)

Thanks @protegieconsultancy for helping to coordinate this as well!

[HOME-BASED TASTING]

CREAMY BASQUE BURNT CHEESECAKES BY ONE LAST LICK!

There was legit a time where I saw the recognisable burnt cheesecake show up on everyone’s story and it was trending for a bit until ppl got jelak and sian of it then suddenly disappear 

One Last Lick’s version has to be one of the better ones out there frfr, bc they managed to get wonderful balance in their cakes la

Flavours wise, the cheese really can taste one ah say serious, balancing out the sweet well ah sweechai butterfly…

Then textures also can taste the contrast, even inside the cake sia… what we mean by this is that the cheesy inside has both gooey and harder layers that you can actually taste. The exterior also got a bit of caramel taste, q happy can taste a bit of the burnt taste too. 

The high quality of ingredients used definitely justifies the price tag of $38.90! It’s more better and way less pricey than your usual Burnt Cheesecake for sure!

We recommend: the whole thing la just get, it’s that good!

Main gripe: As with most cheesecakes, it can taste a bit jelak and repetitive after a while 

Thank you again @onelastlick.sg for sending over your wonderful Basque Burnt Cheesecake!

MICHELIN BIB GOURMAND SRI LANKAN DELIGHTS AT JALAN BESAR!

Kotuwa @kotuwa.sg blew my mind sia…

Pic 1: The Chicken Kottu ($22++) was really PACKED with a multitude of flavours and textures. 

Starts off with a lil bit of spiciness, savouriness and then the aromatic spices just hits u right outta nowhere. 

A mesmerising dish that you have to try for yourself to legit know what I’m talking about frfr

Pic 2: The Watalappam Tart ($16++) clearly had us like🤨🤨at first but it was rly built different ah… 

A rly rich coconutty custard balanced out the rly distinct taste of cardamom in the tart, which was  such a refreshing combi!

Pic 3: Mix of Mutton Rolls and Crab Cutlet. Just get them ah, no questions asked. If u don’t, confirm regret one. 

If we’re talking SUPER CRISPY fried panko breaded and generous mutton and actual crab fillings, look no further already ah..

We recommend: literally anything on the menu just go try ah serious

Main gripe: some of their dishes might be on the spicier side, so I suggest u lower ur ego and politely request and hope they bring down the spiciness level of your dishes (if possible)

Overall: 4.5/5 (absolute MUST-TRY, no gimmicks here, just pure awesomeness!)

DRY SCALLION OIL NOODLES WITH FRIED PORK CHOP UNDER $15 AT HOLLAND VILLAGE!

Mian Jia Noodle Bar @mianjia_sg has these hearty, savoury scallion oil noodles that I’m straight up dying for rn. 

Topped with bonito flakes to give the dish an extra OOMPH, the noodles are flavourful throughout and their portion size also quite big.

The juicy pork chop also q generously given, with a solid crunch, gelling well with the noodles!

We recommend: Five Spice Crispy Pork Chop with Special Sauce Dry Noodle ($10.90+)

Main gripe: you might get this dehydrating feeling after a whole bowl of noodles, remember to hydrate loads too!

Overall: 4/5 (one of HV’s hidden gems!)
location: Mian Jia Noodle Bar 麺家料理

description:
WAGYU BEEF RICE BOWL, TOM YUM SEAFOOD PASTA AND COCONUT KUEH POUFFLE AT TELOK BLANGAH!

The ambience of Old Habits Cafe @oldhabitssg is retro  and super nostalgia evoking, as you see all sorts of knickknacks from the past when you walk in

I’d personally just return for the vibes central, transporting me back to the era of Kids Central, Anything and Whatever (IYKYK)

The Wagyu Beef Rice Bowl ($18.90) immediately caught my eye, with flamed and torched wagyu beef resting on a bed of butter rice, together with a selection of greens. 

Wah, so healthy ah, was the first thing I thought, but the healthy part was balanced out by the sinful homemade sauce served too. 

Tho I couldn’t pinpoint exactly what the sauce was, it tasted mayo-like with the umaminess from mentaiko sauce, which I didn’t mind at all.

The beef was on the chewy side but still robust and juicy enough for me to savour it, with their generosity being a plus point

In all honesty, the Tom Yam Seafood Pasta ($18.90) will be better known for the large amount of seafood given, rather than how appetising it was.

The sauce did have a slight sting but it lacked richness in flavour, so it was p much watery with hints of sour and spicy here and there

However, the Coconut Kueh Pouffle was a big W in our opinion

The creamy vanilla ice cream gelled well with the decadent pandan coconutty taste of the pouffle. 

A+ for creativity tho because it’s literally the first time we’ve seen a fusion of bread pudding and soufflé in a dessert🔥🔥🔥

We recommend: Wagyu Beef Rice Bowl, Coconut Kueh Pouffle, coming for their AMBIENCE

Main gripe: not exactly super near an MRT, still need take bus for 10-15 mins

Overall: 3.9/5 (return for the super retro vibes and interesting menu!)

PGPR - student residence at NUS campus. My first  student dorm experience in life being 28 years old. 
The residence looks so-so outside, but well equipped and comfortable inside. 
Due to the covid - no interactions with neighbors, but it's calm and quiet, even on weekends. 
Common kitchen and bathroom that girls leave really dirty sometimes, but daily housekeeping. 
Affordable price, but takes so long to get to the city center by public transport. Also classes are online, so it doesn't make a lot of sence to stay on campus. 
No conclusion yet.

🇨🇿 捷克布拉格酒窖餐廳｜Pivnice U Rudolfina
...
✍🏻 德奧匈捷旅程的啤酒配肉食就是日常，這次來到捷克布拉格的啤酒餐廳—Pivnice U Rudolfina，入口的是捷克在地特色酒精飲料 Pilsner比爾森啤酒，吃進肚裏則是一把刀插著帶有視覺刺激口味也不賴的野人豬蹄（腳），最後配一些下酒菜炸豪達起士。有力氣的話，吃飽喝足再去將布拉格百萬夜景查理大橋及布拉格城堡收入回憶寶盒，完美的一天。
...
🌟 Pivnice U Rudolfina，近百萬夜景查理大橋的啤酒餐廳，在這裡大口喝啤酒、豪氣大口吃野人豬腳，適時再來一些炸豪達起士下酒菜，耳邊出來聽不懂的東歐語言，有一種融入的迷樣氛圍。消費相對可愛，與大家分享。
🌟 Pilsner 比爾森啤酒，這是一種低層發酵且使用淺色麥芽及較苦啤酒花所釀造的窖藏啤酒，源自1839年捷克比爾市的市民釀酒廠，取經自德國的底層發酵法，讓酒的顏色保清澈猶如黃金閃耀，不得不說這金黃色與我們印象中的黃金布拉格城堡及查理大橋的日落金黃有幾分貼切。

✍🏻 第一天飛抵都柏林，尋找旅館過程中錢包被偷，但在Abigails Hostel 旅館人員熱心幫忙下，還是順利調閱CCTV及到警察局完成備案，更感激是旅館幫忙刷友人信用卡換現金，這樣旅程才不至於中斷，順利完成愛爾蘭蘇格蘭之旅返台。文中記錄錢包被偷該如何處理、地理位置便捷的旅館圖文分享等。Luck of the Irish，只要人平安，一切都可以找到方法解決的。
...
🌟 Abigails Hostel，從都柏林機場搭乘一趟巴士即可抵達市區，之後步行即可抵達旅館，位於Temple Bar、利菲河附近，走路1分鐘也有超市，8人女生宿舍（帶私人衛浴）每床每晚30歐有找（含無線網路及早餐）。因錢包被偷旅費拮据，在都柏林的晚餐都靠超市微波食物，旅館可微波，每款不到3歐的奶油蘑菇、白醬菠菜及普羅旺斯燉菜其實味道還OK。
🌟 錢包被偷怎麼辦，因旅館大門實在太不顯眼，繞到後巷錢包財物就被偷了，所幸護照被扔出撿回來。旅館人員幫忙調閱CCTV及記錄案發過程，接著帶著旅館文件到附近警察局備案。回到旅館，用SKYPE電話辦理海外掛失信用卡、旅館幫忙刷友人信用卡換現金，接下來8-9天旅費才有著落才可繼續。返台，將備案文件等備妥，與保險公司申請旅平險理賠。 🌟 The Luck of the Irish、Saint Patrick‘s Day、綠色 、三葉草，都是愛爾蘭文化印記。

description:
📍French fold

I went there because there was a 50% discount at their new outlet at Orchard.
This means it is a major throwback. Sorry, I'm not sorry.
Anyway, out of the 4 crepes I had, the only one worth eating is the sweet crepes. The gelato was from birds of paradise. So it's decent. 
The galettes tasted a lot like burnt chapatti. I had a hard time swallowing it down. But even with 50% off, it isn't worth it. I don't know how there's so much positive review on this. But it's clearly not for me.

📍wtv food
Ｄｏｃｈｉ. Donut mochi.
Won't exactly say it's lit. But not bad.
The osmanthus one had a bitter after taste I wonder why. The oreo ones were good cause its oreo afterall. My friend liked her choices so much. She finished her boxes all in one shot.
It's currently on pickupp, which acts like grab food. But most food on the app are bakes. Aka desserts, sweet stuff.
They have monthly grpbuy that rotates for the different regions. 
It's pretty convenient. And the delivery cost is reasonable.
Use my code"𝗙𝗢𝗢𝗗𝗬𝗟𝗜𝗖𝗜𝗢𝗨𝗭" for 5 bucks off. Min basket $14. Which means most shop delivery is free. 
Ps. I bought this myself from a grpbuy. But use @pickupp.sg for right to door step convenience.

A place with lovely view.
The drinks were really pretty, BUT taste wise, still ok.
Their food was really good.  Expect a higher price tag.
Perfect for dates.

📍Tipsy Bird
Featuring the highly raved beef cube by xaixue. Its super good.
Another surprise find was the truffle fries. It actually tastes way better than PS cafe version. Try it for yourself.
The horfun was good too. Basically all the food featured was good. Decent selection of alcohol too. Definitely a great place to hang out.
Oh but got to say. Not all tipsy outlets are the same. The tipsy flamingo food. Nah wasn't the same level.
Been missing for awhile, cause I hate ig algorithm. Hehe

📍Park Bench Deli

Finally tried something from them. Walked in super late. But  the boss said they can still do our special order for ricotta pancakes if we want.
So there you go. Lemon curd with maple syrup ricotta pancakes.  It's really huge and airy. Not exactly really photogenic. Plain in its own. But perfect to go with lemon curd and plenty of maple syrup. 
Cucumber gin tonic with pancakes. Cheers to the holidays.
I hate Instagram reach lately. Pathetic.

Valentines Day 5 Course Dinner @ Hopscotch (Stamford Rd) @hopscotch_sg 

See last pic for options 

1. Lobster kueh paiti
With pork floss 
- crispy kueh paiti with a good burst of lobster umami

2. Soups 
Left - French onion soup with beef cheeks - really flavourful soft tender generous beef and delicious bread
Right - Kombu consommé with scampi ravioli. Soup is meh taste like soya sauce and water but the ravioli is goood! 

3. Appetisers
A) Crabcake and guacamole
- delicious! Great combination with Thai flavours plenty of crab that is fresh in the crabcake.
B) Foie gras in hoisin glaze, hawthorn peach puree and reisling jelly
- also really delicious best part of the meal so far
- Amazing explosion of flavours

4. Mains (see photo 1 and 2)
A) Butter poached boston lobster
- very dry there's definitely not adequate butter
- chewy and not fresh
- only half a lobster and no claws provided 
Overall an extremely poorly executed lobster 

B) Herb crusted tenderloin
- herbcrust is tasteless, taste more like stuffing
- tenderloin isn't tender in the least absolutely poor marbling
- caramelised onions taste like chutney
- brandy bachamel dip was good and it saved the steak
- black garlic mash was good too but too little

5. Desserts
Left - Pandan Panna Cotta
- really good too!!! Love the gulamelaka!
Right - Cempedak keylime tart
- yumms!!! Delicious tart with fruity and citrusy notes (: delicious ending to a good meal

Overall nice atmosphere, love the rose on the table, friendly staff chill vibes. Good service. Food actually excluding the mains were really good and an amazing gastronomic experience. Unfortunately the mains are terrible ): 

Nevertheless their cocktails are really good!!!

Sweet, savoury and flavourful gravy are the key to have tasty mee rebus.
Mee Rebus in Singapore have thick gravy normally but I prefer not so thick one. Instead of using dried shrimp I choose to use fresh shrimps to make more rich taste gravy.

.
.
.
.

To make the gravy
About 400gr-500gr fresh shrimps, wash and rinse clean.
1/2 cup finely grounded roasted peanut
80-100gr gula melaka, chopped.
1/2tbsp oyester sauce
2ltrs water
3pcs lemongrass  cut and smashed
2pcs kefirlime leaves
2pcs bay leaves
1pc cinnamon stick
2pcs anise star
5pcs cardamom pots

Paste to make:
10pcs shallots
5pcs garlic
4pcs candle nuts
1inch fresh gallangal
1inch fresh root ginger
1inch sand ginger
1tsp balacan paste
1tsp sweet cumin powder
Salt and pepper to taste

Instruction:
Place all ingredients in a blender, add some cooking oil. Blend until you have a fine paste.

In a large pot, add 2ltrs water, lemongrass, kefirlime leaves  cinnamon stick and the fresh shrimps. Bring to boil over high heat.

Heat some cooking oil in a sauce pan over medium fire, add the blended paste, bay leaves, anise star and cardamom pots. Fry the paste mixture until fragrant and cook for about 8-10 minutes.
Transfer the fried mixture into the hot boiling water, stir well  and continue cooking. Add the chopped gula melaka inside. Mix 1/4 cup of cornt starch + 1/4cup sweet potato starch dilute with little bit water. Reduce the heat to medium fire. Pour into the gravy and stir gently until it's throughly combined into a sauce like gravy. Next add the grounded peanut and season with oyester sauce.

To serve Mee Rebus:
Blanch Yellow noodles and beansprout (if you like) and transfer into a serving bowl.
Pour some gravy over the noodles. Add the garnish; fried tofu, boiled potato, sliced green chilli, chopped tomato, sliced spring onion and fried shallots. Top with hard boiled egg, keropok and calamansi lime halves.
Eat while warm and hot. 😋😋😋
.

Dessert of the Day, a comforting bowl of Tang Yuan with black sesame paste filling. 😋😋😋
Simple yet delicious dessert you can make in thirty-minutes.

.
.
.
.

Black Sesame Tang Yuan

Fir the filling:
120gr HollyFarms instant paste sesame powder
50gr butter, room temperature

Place the sesame powder in a small sauce pan over low heat, add the butter and stir until the butter is melted and mix well with the sesame powder.
Off the heat, roll the paste into a small ball size. Put aside.

For the glutinousrice dough
150gr glutinous rice flour
140gr warm water
Pinch of salt

Put the glutinousrice flour anf salt into a mixing bowl  slowly and gradually add the warm water while mixing. The dough should be soft and a bit sticky. Add 5gr coconut oil to keep the dough moist.
Divide the dough into 20pcs.

Bring a pot of water to a boil while preparing the tang yuan balls.

Flatten the dough with your thumb, add the filling. Gently pinch and wrap the dough. Roll into a ball shape. Gently drop the tang yuan ball into a hot boiling water, boil until the it cooked. The tang yuan balls will fliats on the surface when it cooked.
.
.
.

~ Rachelrax Cakes ~
📍Address: 12 Lim Tua Tow Road, Singapore 547735

@rachelrax has always been on my never ending list of “to-go” places but, I’ve never got a chance to try their tarts since its quite far for me.😢Really glad that my friend managed to help pre-order the earl grey lavender one for me!!!🥰

The tart consists of the Earl Grey Lavender Tea☕️ thats infused in White Chocolate Ganache.😍I really loved how the amount of flavour inside the earl grey lavender tea was just right and not too overpowering for me.☺️ The taste of Earl Grey Lavender Tea is basically a black tea thats infused with the essence of bergamot (an intensely floral orange) and some lavender which has a floral taste with some hints of mint and rosemary.😍 However, one gripe I have about this is, the mixture was not that firm??? and the tart crust although its crumbly and sweet, it was quite soft alr and it didnt have that firm cookie-like texture.😭Maybe cos it was out from the fridge for a little too long despite it being in the cooler bag.😢

Overall, I feel that the tart was pretty mediocre but the flavour was nice, I enjoyed it and it was worth a try.☺️ Its also a tad pricey I feel, given how the flavour though its my all-time favourite, was a bit of a let down for me.😭

Thanks @lim_jiaks_and_foodtrails for helping me get the tart!!!😋🥧

rating: 6.5/10
pricing: $8.90 (premium flavour)

~ Ah Tas Muffins ~
📍Address: 51 Old Airport Road, 01-49, Singapore 390051

I’ve always seen @ahtasmuffins through my friends IG feed but I never got a chance to try their muffins.😭However, last week, I finally managed to!!☺️So, these are the flavours that I got:

1️⃣ Dark Choco Banana🍫🍌(7/10)
This is one of the stall’s bestsellers and it’s one of my fav too!!!😋It’s one of the more richer-tasting muffins on the menu, probably because he uses a velvety, gooey combo of choco chips and banana.😍 I really loved how the sweetness of the banana helped to lower down the slightly bitter profile of the choco, so it doesn’t get too gerlak.🥰

2️⃣ Classic Banana🍌(6/10)
This tasted just like the banana walnut muffin, just without the walnuts in there.😂The scent for this muffin was soo prominent that the smell was still lingering in the air when I was otw home.🤤However, when I took a first bite of this muffin, it tasted more like a plain muffin with very subtle hints of the banana.😢😢

3️⃣ Banana Walnut🍌🥜(6.25/10)
For this muffin, there were subtle hints of creaminess of the banana, against the crunch from the walnut!!🥰 The scent for this muffin is largely overpowered by the banana, so if you’re a fan of this fruit, its a great option. However, one gripe I have about this is that, when I took a bite of this muffin, the ratio of walnuts to banana wasn’t that equal?? I hardly tasted any bananas in there and what I had were mostly the walnuts.😢This was a bit of a let down for me as I had high hopes for this.😭

4️⃣ Blueberry granola🥣(7.2/10)
This is another of my fav from this stall too!!!😍The granola gives some crunchiness?? to the slightly sweet blueberries that are scattered throughout the muffin.😋 It’s quite delicious, and a great option for those who fancy something more wholesome in their muffins.☺️

Overall, I feel that their muffins are pretty decent and also a tad bit more pricey than those from other hawker bakeries. I wouldn’t travel all the way to oarfc just to get them.😬However, if you’re already having lunch at OARFC then its worth dropping by their stall to get some for a tea-time snack/sweet treat.😊

~ Amoy Street Food Centre ~
📍Address: 7 Maxwell Road, Singapore 069111

1️⃣ Noodle Story🍜 (7/10)
I’ve seen soo many reviews and hype about @anoodlestory on my feed that I’ve finally got to try it for myself. They are a Michelin Bib Gourmand listed-stall that sells Singapore Style Ramen Noodles. Its basically a modernised take on HK- styled wanton noodles with each bowl priced at $9/12/$16. I got the small portion of noodles at $9 and it was already very filling.😬

There is a slight wanton mee taste in the sauce, with some sambal chilli to give it a slight hae bee (dried sambal) kick!!! I found this bowl of noodles to be really delicious😋 and I loved the presentation too!!!🤩 The noodles were springy, chewy and bouncy and it went really well with the sauce. For the toppings, there is a really tender, mOist and mouth-watering piece of char-siew that melts in your mouth🤤, generously filled HK-styled wantons🥟, prefectly cooked onsen egg🥚 and their iconic super-crispy fried potato wrapped prawns.🍤The noodles are served with a side of soup that is packed full with flavours.🤩 I felt their fried potato wrapped prawns were really interesting as it literally just tastes like mamee noodles.😂

Overall, I think the amount of creativity and the small little details that went into recreating this bowl of wanton noodles is really amazing and its definitely another class of its own!! I feel this is worth giving a try.😋

2️⃣ Coffee Break☕️ (8/10)
I’ve always wanted to try @coffeebreakamoy coffee as I found their flavours to be really interesting. I got the Iced Sea Salt Caramel Latte which costs $4.50 and it was really good.😍I loved how the flavours are soo balanced because you can taste a bit of the saltiness from the sea salt and some sweetness coming from the caramel!!! The coffee also wasnt too rich for me.☺️I would definitely wanna come back to try their other flavours.🥰

📍Doughnut Shack 

I’ve seen soo many posts about @doughnutshacksg doughnuts and bombolonis all over my IG feed that I just HAD TO TRY THEM!! I got the box of 6 which costs $16.90 and it consists a mix of both doughnuts and bombolonis. These are the flavours:

1️⃣ Hojicha Ganache☕️(8.95/10)
This was my fav out of everything!! When I saw that they sell hojicha bombolonis, I had to try it. I preferred these to the ones at Sourbombe as the cream filling was not only smooth and rich, but also I felt they nailed this flavour super well!!😍 I could really taste the roasted tea leaves in this Hojicha bomboloni and it didn’t come across as too rich and overpowering for me.🤩

2️⃣ Dountella🍫(6.25/10)
This just taste like your normal nutella that’s filled inside the bomboloni.😋They’re soo generous with the filling such that when we cut it open, the filling literally just flowed out.😍

3️⃣ Crème Brûlée🍮(6/10)
I loved how they recreated the burnt sugar part of the crème brûlée such that it gave that sweet and sticky texture on the doughnut.😋However, I only tasted like sugar in this? or maybe cos we were out the whole day and so some parts melted alr. I also felt this was wayy to sweet for my liking.😬

4️⃣ Thai Milk Tea🥤(8.5/10)
This was my 2nd fav!! I thoroughly enjoyed this as I felt they hit all the notes that a thai milk tea should have!☺️ It wasn’t like those overly sweet thai milk tea and there was a good balance of flavours in there.🥰

5️⃣ Peanut Butter Jelly🥜(6.5/10)
The peanut butter inside here was soo THICK!!😍 Its more towards the earthy side with a mild savoury taste. I could taste both the peanut butter and abit of the jelly inside. However, I felt that the peanut butter kinda overpowered everything such that I couldn’t really taste the pbj flavour as a whole.😢

6️⃣ Matcha Pistachio🍵(5.75/10)
I didn’t really like this flavour as I felt the matcha pistachio taste wasn’t even there.😢 It was pretty underwhelming as I had high hopes for this.😭

Overall, I enjoyed it as their flavours are p legit!!! Also, they’re really affordable as compared to others that I’ve tried. It’s definitely worth taking a trip down to give this a try.😍

~ Hamburg Steak Keisuke ~
📍Address: 72 Peck Seah Street, Singapore 079329

I’ve seen soo many IG posts about this place on my feed and FINALLY, I went down to try it!! As I’m a huge fan of cheese🧀, I had to try the Triple Cheese Prime Hamburg Steak Set.😋

The set came with a really gorgeous and mouth-watering piece of prime beef hamburg steak thats filled with cheese🧀, deep fried tofu, fried ebi tempura🍤, tofu with spring onion, rice and miso soup.😋As for my choice of sauce, I got the Keisuke Original Sauce (soy based) to go along with the hamburg steak. I tried abit of the Teriyaki Mayonnaise sauce from my friend’s one but I preferred the original sauce as it complemented well with the hamburg.🥰

I felt the hamburg steak was pretty good as it was super tender and well cooked!!😋In the middle its stuffed with cheese that will ooze out once you cut open into it!!😍It went really well with the cheese and I guess thats because the hamburg soaked up pretty much almost all the cheese.😂As for the sides, both the tofus were pretty decent!! I loved the ebi tempura the most as it’s so fresh and the batter was still really crispy even when I only started eating it towards the end of my meal.😍 One gripe I have about the hamburg steak is, I felt that the cut wasn’t very spectacular for me and when I cut the hamburg, the cheese also wasn’t as flowy as how I would’ve preferred.😩

What I liked about this place is that, with every order of their mains, you can get free flow eggs and vegetables at the salad bar!!!😍 There is decent selection of eggs to choose from such as tamagoyaki, scrambled eggs, etc. As for the salad bar, there is a WIDE SELECTION of vegetables like red cabbage, broccolis, cauliflower, radish, etc. You can also get other side dishes like pasta, sweet potatoes with lemon, tofu and many other items!!😍 Just note that due to the current pandemic, the staff would have to take them for you!!

Overall, I felt the food here was pretty decent and it was worth a try. The plus point for me was definitely the freeflow eggs and salad bar!!!☺️

pricing: $22.90
rating: 7.2/10!!

Definitely need a second stomach to try all these pretty  cakes 🥺 [Toby’s Kopi Toast Bakery part 2/2] 

𝙊𝙣𝙙𝙚𝙝 𝙊𝙣𝙙𝙚𝙝 𝘾𝙖𝙠𝙚 ($7.90)
I love the gula melaka in this cake! It’s very distinct and yet not overly sweet 👍🏻 The cake was soft and the coconut shavings added extra crunch to the cake 🤤 Also isn’t this cake so pretty 🥰 the green really pop out in the photo

𝙈𝙖𝙣𝙜𝙤 𝘾𝙖𝙠𝙚 ($7.90)
I like fruit cakes so I was looking forward to this 🥰 The mango was fresh and sweet and goes really well with the soft cake and super light cream 😋 This was less sweet compared to ondeh ondeh so I would recommend getting this if you’re not that into sweets!

𝙊𝙧𝙝 𝙉𝙚𝙚 𝘾𝙖𝙠𝙚 ($7.90)
I don’t usually eat Orh Nee so can’t comment much 🤭 but this cake contained real chunky orh nee pieces! For further details I shall direct you to orh nee lover @dazeliciousss future post 😂 

They currently have tea time special promotion which comes with one slice of cake🍰+ drink☕️ from $6.90 onwards (depending on the price of chosen cake) which is very affordable 👍🏻☺️ so do drop by after 2pm to try their cakes~

Thanks @tobys_kopi_toast_bakery for the invite! Enjoyed the cakes a lot 🥰🥰

Look at that yellow golden curry rice 😍😍 [Toby’s Kopi Toast Bakery part 1/2] 

𝘾𝙝𝙞𝙘𝙠𝙚𝙣 𝘾𝙪𝙩𝙡𝙚𝙩 𝘾𝙪𝙧𝙧𝙮 𝙍𝙞𝙘𝙚 ($6.90)
Let’s start with the curry ☺️☺️It was a little sweet but also had a spicy kick to it which i liked~ The star of this dish is definitely the cutlet! It was still very crispy even after we spent an eternity snapping photos 🤣🤣 The batter was light but it soaked up the curry well 👍🏻 oh the dish also came with sweet cabbage which complements the curry 😋

𝘽𝘽𝙌 𝘽𝙖𝙗𝙮 𝙍𝙞𝙗𝙨 ($10.90)
These baby ribs were sooo tender 🥺 I could peel the meat off the bone with just my fork. The sauce was yummy too! It tasted like a combination of ketchup, bbq and some pepper 😋

𝙆𝙖𝙮𝙖 𝘽𝙪𝙩𝙩𝙚𝙧 𝙏𝙤𝙖𝙨𝙩 𝙎𝙚𝙩 ($3)
Yesss $3 toast set for dine-in 🤭 superr affordable! The kaya seems like more of traditional kind and it wasn’t too sweet. The bread was toasted nicely too ☺️

Overall, food was great! Affordable and the portion was big. They also sell noodles (made in-house!) which you can get as buddy meal tgt with the curry rice! But we didn’t have enough stomach space for the noodle 😔

Thanks @tobys_kopi_toast_bakery for the invite! ☺️☺️

Loveee tempura 🥰❤️ and everything fried 🤭

𝙋𝙧𝙚𝙢𝙞𝙪𝙢 𝙏𝙚𝙣𝙙𝙤𝙣 ($11.90)👍🏻
This bowl came with 2 prawns, squid, kani, pumpkin, lotus root and french bean. The tempura batter was light and not too oily! The ingredients weren’t the freshest but I would say it’s quite worth for the price and you still get a variety of tempura 👍🏻😆

𝙎𝙥𝙞𝙘𝙮 𝘾𝙤𝙡𝙙 𝙐𝙙𝙤𝙣 (+$6?) 🤤
Obviously I can’t skip out on anything spicy 🤩 and no regretz!! The spicy sauce was a flavor bomb + umami flavor from sakura ebi 🥺 mixed everything tgt and slurped that cold chewy udon 🥰 Oh the udon felt a little undercooked but I like my maggie mee undercooked so it was good for me 👍🏻

The brownies were the star in this box! Rich bittersweet chocolate cream on top with fudgy cake layer at the bottom 🍫

𝘽𝙡𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙢𝙖𝙣𝙜𝙚 𝙍𝙤𝙡𝙡 𝘾𝙖𝙠𝙚 🤤

𝙁𝙖𝙞𝙧𝙛𝙖𝙭 𝙎𝙖𝙣𝙙𝙬𝙞𝙘𝙝 + 𝘽𝙖𝙘𝙤𝙣 🤤

𝙎𝙡𝙪𝙩 😋
Definitely needed to get both that egg yolk and the potato puree in each dip! 🥰 It’s really good but once the egg yolk ran out, the potato puree felt too buttery on its own 🤔 gotta ratio out that yolk and the potato when dipping

𝙏𝙧𝙪𝙛𝙛𝙡𝙚 𝙃𝙖𝙨𝙝𝙗𝙧𝙤𝙬𝙣𝙨 👍🏻

Truth be told that I like the rather quirky location, but not so much the food. My understanding of yakotori is that it's skewered, and grilled. The yakitori served here does not come with the familiar sight of the bamboo or metal skewers, neither do they have the the aroma of being charcoal grilled. In fact, I could almost swear the chicken skin, which came in a big piece, was deep fried. Don't get me wrong though, the food is not bad. It's just not what I would classify as yakitori. #sgrestaurant #sgfood #singaporefood #singapore #singaporerestaurant #sgfood #sg #sashimi #grilledmeat #grilledchicken #chickentail

I booked this months ago when I tried the lunch here, which left me wanting for more. I wasn't disappointed.

I'm starting to get sick of so-called Japanese restaurants helmed by non Japanese chefs, that has an "omakase menu" and tries to put an abundance of uni, caviar and/or truffle.

This, is what I yearn for. Dishes that takes much skills, cannot be easily replicated, uses seasonal and fresh ingredients which the cooking pays a lot of respect to.

The ponzu uni sauce was a stunner to begin with. To be honest this is the first time I've had shark's fin in Japanese cuisine. Combined with the abalone, the clash of the textures and flavours was just heavenly.

The deep fried hairy crab leg was another representation of perfection. From the thickness of the batter to the degree that it was fried to and the snow flakes like salt which not only add on to the aesthetics but also bring out the sweetness of the crab meat. It was so well thought out and put together.

I've always loved to learn about new ingredients and 2 stood out - nodoguro, which is a blackthroat sea perch and the hana sansho, which is a pepper flower that is available only for a couple of weeks every year. 

This, is the kind of restaurant that I look forward to going to.

#japanesefinedining #japanese #japanesefood #japfood #sgjapanesefood #sashimi #kappo #abalone #omiwagyu #nodoguro #hanasanshou #sanshou #uni #singaporefood #singaporerestaurant #singapore #sgfood #sg

每天早上，這檔“翠記熟食“幾乎都會有不斷的人龍排隊。確實，這年頭要吃一頓少於$2早餐的地方已不多見。

但對我而言，這檔口的魅力不在價廉物美的早餐。當然，我常吃的芋頭糕+豬腸粉是很美味。更吸引我的是老闆娘散發的那股對生命的熱忱。年約七旬的安娣總會滿懷笑容的開朗的問 ”全部都要吼？辣椒要多一點嗎？謝謝！”在他身旁的老公卻總是不苟言笑的，淡定的準備食物。

不禁讓我想到，他們的性格迥然，卻能長相廝守；他們不富裕，卻不埋怨於生活。比起現在的人，動不動就離婚，一點點不順心就自尋短見，這，才是活著該有的態度吧。

#cheecheongfun #ccf #yamcake #breakfast #cheapeats #singaporefood #sgfood #singapore #sg #hawkerfood #hawkercentre #hawker #ourhawkerculture #zestforlife #芋頭糕 #豬腸粉 #早餐 #小販中心

It's not easy to judge a good bowl of mee rebus by its looks, so it's usually a trial and error, hit or miss situation. 

To me, a good mee rebus is almost a perfect balance - the noodles should be cooked just right and not soggy, the bean sprouts blanched to a crunch, and the most important component, the gravy, be in that middle point of being sweet and savoury, not overly thick and starchy and soupy enough to slurp it up. Bonus points with the green cut chilli and dark soya sauce (not every stall provides them, mind you).

This time, the trial and error was a big hit. Back for the second time in a week.

#meerebus #noodles #noodle #malayfood #hawkerfood #hawkercentre #hawker #ourhawkerculture #singaporefood #sgmalayfood #sgfood #singapore #sg

description:
[puff & peaks @ tampines] @puffsandpeaks needs no introduction and i’m constantly and consistently impressed by their fluffy brioche doughnuts! only sad thing is that they’re located so far in the east so thankfully @pickupp.sg brought it over to me 🥰 with $5 off as well using my promo code <DAZELICIOUS> hehe

but yes these doughnuts are srsly soft and chewy and fluffy and not oily at all, and most importantly they’re filled so generously with fillings 😍 and even after a few days in the fridge they still taste as good 😋 at $3.80 each it’s rly quite the steal! do try it out if you haven’t 😛

this box came with a variety of their usual flavours: vanilla bean, lemon, matcha, kopi siew dai, blackcurrant peanut butter, chocolate and ofc my fav EARL GREY 🤪 i think the fillings + sugar coating cause the doughnuts to be sweeter than they need to be, but they aren’t TOO sweet either so it’s definitely good for dessert HAHA personally wasn’t a fan of the blackcurrant one cause the tartness didn’t blend well with the nutty peanut butter, but everything else was 💯

[sevens kissaten @ tiong bahru] here are the matcha desserts we tried at @sevenskissaten! 🍵 check out my prev post for my review of their chicken stew toast hehe

[matcha monaka ($12++) - 4.5/7] this was quite an interesting dessert HAHA it’s a japanese rice cracker shell that encloses a scoop of matcha ice cream, set on top a thin sheet of mochi crepe and a bed of red bean paste! the matcha ice cream is q rich and bittersweet, tho it does feel a little powdery 😌 the tea notes are sufficiently brought out, but imo it could afford to be a little more bitter! this is prolly cause the red bean paste was very smooth but imo too sweet 😅 the mochi crepe had a weird texture LOL and actly the rice cracker didn’t quite retain its crisp so it quickly got a lil soft to chew so i wasn’t a fan 🤭

[7s parfait ($12++) - 5.5/7] for this parfait you can actly choose which ice cream you want (matcha/vanilla/salt) but ofc we went for matcha 🤪 same ice cream as above, this was paired with blueberries, raspberries, strawberries and chestnuts! everything was rly sweet except the sour 🍓 HAHA also had some coco crunch ball thingy which provided a nice crunch LOL it was topped (and bottomed..?) with light cream and imo i think it made everything sweeter than i’d like it 🤭 but ok ah as a sweet indulgence i did enjoy it and i wouldn’t mind having this again 😛

[sevens kissaten @ tiong bahru] caught up w some friends at @sevenskissaten over the weekend! it’s a jap teahouse so i’d definitely be back for the weekday matcha afternoon tea set, but it’s just brunch for now 😛 

[chicken stew thick toast ($19++) - 5.5/7] this is a huge bread bowl filled with chicken stew, and it reminded me of taiwan’s coffin toasts! 🍞 the stew itself is comforting, not too thick or salty, just light and creamy enough and has a hint of sweetness ☺️ filled generously with broccoli, carrots, potatoes, cheese (i think, there were some chewy yellow strips that reminded me of non-battered mozz sticks) and errr alot of mushrooms HAHAHA 🤨 the bread itself gets soggy quite fast so it was a pain to cut and eat but i managed so it’s no big problem 🤣  loved the crisp of the 2 toast sticks at the side tho!! the toast also comes with a refreshing side of shredded cabbage and miso soup! 🍲 

other items that my friends got in the last pic were the omurice ($16++) and tori teriyaki don ($16++)! i tried a little and they’re pretty standard imo HAHA

[jiababa @ home] another round of healthy taiwanese bagels from hbb @jiababa88! 🥰 got them off @pickupp.sg’s groupbuy this time so it was free delivery ($5 off) with my promo code <DAZELICIOUS> hehe

[matcha set of 2 ($14)] this set came with 2 different fillings sandwiched between matcha bagels in a pretty shade of green 💚 the bagels have a nice soft and chewy texture, but i guess it’s difficult to truly infuse them with taste cause there’s only a hint of bitterness and tea notes from the matcha 🍵

the fillings were red bean + taro and red bean + mochi, and in both cases the ingredients used tasted rly natural and healthy so they definitely would appeal to purists 😛 sweetness was basically non-existent HAHA and personally they were a lil bland even for the 0% sugar me 😅 granted im not the biggest fan of red bean, but even the taro felt abit muted as compared to when i last had it in their earl grey bagel 😌 i preferred the mochi (i mean everyone loves mochi) cause it was sticky, chewy and most imptly slightly sweetened so there was more taste 🤪

[brotherbird bakehouse @ bugis] hi i’m back with my @brotherbird_bakehouse croissants and their february specials 🥐 omg it’s been a while and now got charge gst liao 🥲 and also getting my mentaiko prawn ($6.50+) again cause it’s srsly the best HAHA generously filled with mini prawns slathered in mentaiko sauce YES PLS 🤤

[ispahan ($6+) - 4.5/7] this is a pretty pink escargot pastry for vday 💕 also i’m a fan of this combi of lychee, rose and raspberry but imo this one wasn’t v impressive cause the flavours weren’t that strong 😌 like there were hints of the fruity lychee and sour raspberry scattered throughout, and a slight whiff of rose, but most of it felt abit muted 😅

[s’mores ($6+) - 5.5/7] this was my fav among the 3 tho i’m biased cause torched sticky marshmallow is always nice, and there was like 3 of them in a croissant 🤪 surprisingly wasn’t as sweet as expected, plus appreciated the addition of cocoa nibs for the slight bitterness and textural difference 😋 there was also graham cookie cream but i didnt rly taste it oops

[lemon meringue ($5+) - 5/7] ok so funny story i thought this was a feb special but actly it’s the passionfruit meringue 🤦🏻‍♂️ but it’s fine cause i prefer 🍋 anw and more imptly i like the torched meringue cause it’s like eating a soft and airy cloud and it’s not too sweet also ☁️ the lemon curd is creamy and tangy, but also sweet enough so that you don’t go 😵‍💫 when you eat it HAHA but yes this croissant, as with most of their sweet ones, tends towards the sweeter side 😌

A satisfying lunch at Dancing Crab with my boys last week.  While most people come here for their seafood boil, some of their dishes in the menu are well worth your attention too. 

We particularly enjoyed their gumbo and the exploding crab fried rice. 

The gumbo is a meal on its own I can have it all to myself.  Delicious.  An explosion of seafood flavour.  The gravy has an intense umaminess 😋. I will come back for this.

The exploding fried rice has an intense wok hei and generous amount of crab meat.  The egg is a bit overdone though.  It would have been perfect if the egg yolk can drizzle over the rice grains but we love this plate of goodness nonetheless. 

The caesar salad was pretty darn good too.  Not overly dressed just perfect and I love that they grated the egg over it together with the parmesan cheese. 

My son enjoyed his fish and chips too.  Nice and crisp batter, decently seasoned and size is perfect.

Its been a while since our last  visit here at #tsuiwahsg and having said that, it’s been over a couple of years since our last trip in Hong Kong.  We miss Hong Kong.  Oh to travel again is the next best thing! 

So we feasted on:

Lamb Chop Curry 

What I love about this dish is that they grilled the lamb chops first then smothered them with that delicious curry sauce.  This curry is very good with perfectly cooked meat, tender and not too gamey.  Best with roti or steamed rice.

Crispy Bun with Condensed Milk 

A must if you are a first timer at Tsui Wah.  This is their signature toast and we love it.  We first had this in Hong Kong and became our favorite since. 

Crispy and soft at the same time, this buttered toast bun is generously drizzled with condensed milk.  Yum!

Kagoshima-Style Braised Pork Cartilage with Tossed Instant Noodle 

My son enjoyed this bowl of goodness so much so that he finished everything except the cartilage 😆. The meat just falls off the bone, soft, easy to eat and very tasty. 

King Prawns in Mala Soup with Mixian 

Our first time trying this noodle dish and this is now one of my favorite noodle dish here. 

This is not the mala we are more exposed to.  This bowl of goodness has a mild to medium mala heat yet you will only get that hint of spiciness and numbness a little later.  The prawns are fresh and crunchy that adds contrast to the mala soup. My only issue here is that the serving seems small.  I could probably have 2 orders of this. 😋😋😋

Amaranth with Fish Soup - We need vegetables in our daily eating life too.  Love the fish broth on this vegetable dish and the amaranth greens is the perfect vegetable for this soup.  Crunchy and hearty.

I love the lotus nut paste or lian zi suan dessert at Soon Heng Hot & Cold Desserts 順兴清甜五味汤 😋😋😋. 

Lian zi suan (莲子爽) or lotus seed in thickened syrup which is not commonly available in sweet soup stalls.  So in my opinion, this is a rare bowl of dessert.  I love that its not overly sweet and with generous amount of lotus nuts.  At $2 its pretty worth it. 

On the other side of the table, hubby had an iced cold dessert and it is named “Special Cocktail” of peaches, aloe vera jelly, nata de coco and assortment of fruits and sago which according to him was pretty good and refreshing. 

If you are at Tanglin Halt Food Centre do try this bowl of goodness and other old school Teochew desserts they have to offer.

A #latepost of my birthday brunch with my best half at Bearded Bella over a week ago.  It was our first time here and overall meal was a pleasant one. 

On the table:

Salmon Pistachio Rosti $22
A generous plate of goodness.  For brunch, this meal will keep you satiated until tea time 😃. I love the citrus mint mayo and pomegranate that goes well with everything on the plate it balanced out the richness.  The salmon is perfectly done, rosti just crisp outside, soft and moist inside and I love the generous amount of pistachios. 

Epic Brekkie $25
Green tomato relish, maple bacon, harrisa chicken sausage, confit portobello, avocado, sweet potato rosti, arugula, 1 egg your way.  The perfect plate of brekkie when you are hungry.  Quite a big portion and pretty good actually.  Although I feel it is missing a sauce or gravy of some kind on the side and perhaps a light dressing on the arugula. 

Oh and they have awesome coffee too!

Iced White $6.50
Coffee Slushie $7.50 ❤️❤️❤️

[ Hiro’s Food Diary ]
Do you prefer tuna sushi? medium-fatty tuna or fatty tuna 🍣? I like fatty tuna the most 😋!

The most special cuisine in Sushi Nanba is not other than the combination of ‘Omurice’ (rice topped with omelette) and Chirashi sushi (scattered sushi with conger eel). It’s definitely an innovative version of sushi.

Looking forward to the next visit to Sushi Nanba in May 🤩!

description:
[ Hiro’s Food Diary ]
It’s my 1st visit to Bistronomie Le Quart, a new French 🇫🇷 restaurant located around 100m from my house 😊. It’s a fun and excellent Christmas Eve dinner with my dear foodie friends!

The roast chicken 🍗 was a perfect menu for Christmas Eve! It’s prepare in French culinary technique, with delicious sauce made of butter, egg yolks and white wine vinegar and flavoured with herbs 🌿. Black truffle gave extra fragrance to the yummy 😋 dish!

Fresh and half cooked langoustine, with scallop and salad 🥗 was another highly satisfying dish 🤩.

Menu:
Gougère / Petit croque-monsier
グジェール / 小さなクロックムッシュ
Gougère / Little ham & cheese sandwich

Roast chicken with bearnaise sauce, topped with black truffle

📍Orchard, Singapore 

One of our most unique petit fours. Made with carrots and sea snails served on mussel shell 🥕🐌

Lick it right from the shell, just like candy!🍬

The ocean flavour is strong and sweet with this one 🌊

🧜🏻‍♀️🧜🏻‍♂️Come with us on our gastronomic journey, as we unveil more in detail about how impressive @koks_restaurant @poulandrias is 🌅

Looking for something BOLD and delicious to treat your loved ones? 💘 Get Van Houten at your favourite supermarket guys! They have been around since 1828 so the taste and quality is definitely UNDOUBTED ✨

description:
La Belle Epoque is a brand NEW European Restaurant & Bar. It opens its doors in the heart of Singapore’s vibrant dining belt, Boat Quay. 

Helmed by dynamic, creative and passionate Chef Firdauz Nasir, La Belle Epoque specialises in contemporary European cuisine using fresh ingredients seasoned with natural herbs. 

We tried a mouthwatering array of regional delicacies : 

🔹️Skins (gluten-free)($8++)
Delicious crispy fish, chicken, seasonal vegetables & pork skins served with black garlic aioli   

🔹️Poulet (keto)($14++)
Roasted Chicken served with purple pommes potato, braised & grilled purple cabbage & sundried tomatoes 

🔹️Hummus Taco (vegetarian, keto)($10++)
Smoked chickpea mashed & blended with tahini, lemon juice and garlic served in corn taco shell, roasted capsicum, romaine lettuce & pickled shallots  

🔹️Cauliflower Steak (vegetarian, gluten free) ($12++)
Smoked & cured cauliflower pan seared with vegetable butter herbs, served with purple pommes potato, braised & grilled purple cabbage with vegetable demi glace  ($14++) 

🔹️Oyster & Iberico (keto) ($26++)
3 pcs Oysters lightly torched, topped with crispy iberico ham, tomato salsa and Avruga caviar 

🔹️Charcuterie Platter (Any 4 selection of cold cuts and cheeses at $28++)
▪︎ Prosciutto di Parma Ham (aged 16 months) ($8++ per serving)
▪︎ Rosette "Duc de Coise' ($8++ per serving)
▪︎ Parmigiano Reggiano DOP "Fiordimaso" 12 months ($10++ per serving)
▪︎ Taleggio DOP Cheese ($10++ per serving) 

🔸️Guerre Stellari ($10++)
Dark chocolate shell stuffed with rum chocolate mousse served with raspberry sorbet 

🔸️Chocolate Mousse ($10++)
Pure dark chocolate mousse cake served with orange segments 

🔸️Tiramisu ($10++)
Coffee & mascarpone cheesecake served with marsala wine infused berries salad 

These unique and creative dishes were not only pleasing to the eyes but to the stomach too! 

📍La Belle Epoque
63 Boat Quay 
Singapore 049851
🕒 3pm - 11.30pm (Mons-Sats)
📞67321687 (for reservations)
🌐 Book online on:
https://cho.pe/c70ki95n0 

Thank you @jenniferyeoconsultancy for the invite and @LaBelleEpoqueSG for the warm hospitality!

Healthy living is not a dream; it is about eating healthily! 

@qwangsg is a new Vietnamese food concept in Singapore that serves Vietnamese Rice Noodle Salad with a healthier twist at affordable prices! 

Featured here were: 

🥗Beef Bowl ($16.80)
🥗Pork Bowl ($10.80)
🥗Chicken Bowl ($9.80)
☕️ Chilled Vietnamese Coffee 

Other options:
🥗Pork Belly Bowl ($10.80)
🥗Vegetarian Bowl ($9.80) 

The delicious noodle salad comes in 3 options of tasty proteins: beef, pork, or chicken; with a mixture of fresh greens such as premium Vietnamese rice vermicelli noodles, fresh Romaine lettuce, pickled carrots and daikon, Japanese cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, refreshing mint and basil and chopped roasted peanuts. 

Each hearty bowl comes with no oil and MSG, less sugar and salt. Drizzled with their unique savoury and tangy Vietnamese salad dressing, a Qwang bowl is just what you need to enjoy a satisfying meal that feeds your senses, body, and soul all at the same time. 

It is the perfect choice to enjoy authentic Vietnamese tastes and flavours without guilt. 

Check them out and follow @Qwangsg's IG page to receive a 《𝐁𝐮𝐲 𝟏 𝐆𝐞𝐭 𝟏》 promo code in your inbox.

Craving for some burgers/wraps but wanting to eat healthily? Let me share with you the perfect guilt-free burgers, wraps and bowls!🥙🍔🥗 

@QuickGreens.World ~ Singapore's all-new vegan quick-serve concept that is suitable for flexitarians, vegans and vegetarians alike, serving great tasting 100% plant-based wraps, salads and burgers at affordable prices. 

Quick Greens's food is fresh, fast and guilt-free and packs a punch with their flavourful hero products - vegan Kebabs, Burgers, Kibbeh and Falafel. 

What we tried: 

🔹️𝐂𝐇𝐈𝐏 𝐂𝐇𝐈𝐏 𝐂𝐇𝐈𝐏𝐎𝐓𝐋𝐄 𝐁𝐎𝐖𝐋🥣🌶 (𝐎𝐑 𝐖𝐑𝐀𝐏🥙)
Signature Quick Greens Bowls ~ Vegan Kebab, Quinoa, Purple & White Cabbage, Broccoli, Cucumbers, Carrots, Pickled Tomatoes and Olives, Crunchy Seed Mix Finished With A Chipotle Dressing. 
I didn't expect the vegan kebab to taste so good and loved the Chipotle dressing that paired well with the salad. 

🔹️𝐕𝐄𝐆𝐀𝐍 𝐀𝐕𝐎 𝐒𝐓𝐀𝐂𝐊 🍔🌶 
Vegan Burger ~ Vegan Patty, Avocado, Lettuce Mix, Pickled Porcini, Harissa Dressing. It tasted good with Harissa dressing. 

🔹️Natural Benefits Beetroot Fresh Cold Pressed Juice 

🔹️PS Organics Ginger Probiotics Kombucha 

If you’re looking for a delicious plant-based meal on-the-go, check out Quick Greens at Funan Centre; it's grab and go ready.

Unit # 02-04, Funan,
107 North Bridge Road,
Singapore 179105
Daily 11am - 9.30pm

Have you tried the newly launched PERi-PERi Bowls from @NandosSG that are created just for Singapore with local flavours and Asian favourites? 

It’s the classic Nando’s you love, bowled out in a new format – with new ways to enjoy flame-grilled PERi-PERi deliciousness. Customise and build YOUR own bowl from just $10.90 nett! Choose from 4 Bases, 4 Mains, and 7 Side-Kicks to match your preferences. 

What we tried: 

🐓 ¼ 𝐂𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐤𝐞 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐏𝐄𝐑𝐢-𝐏𝐄𝐑𝐢 𝐖𝐞𝐝𝐠𝐞𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐠𝐫𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐕𝐞𝐠 ($𝟏𝟓.𝟗𝟎) ~ Nando’s chicken are freshly grilled-to-order, cooked to juicy perfection, and spiced up with the fiery heat of PERi-PERi – a unique Nando’s breed of African Bird’s Eye Chilli. The portion was huge and served with Peri-Peri wedges and chargrilled veggies for the sides. 

🍛 𝐄𝐱𝐭𝐫𝐚 𝐒𝐡𝐢𝐨𝐤 𝐁𝐨𝐰𝐥 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐞𝐱𝐭𝐫𝐚 𝐡𝐮𝐧𝐠𝐫𝐲 ($𝟏𝟗.𝟗𝟎) ~ Signature rice with two boneless thighs in PERi-Laksa Styled plus grilled broccoli, PERinaise egg salad and cheese crisp. The boneless thighs in hot laksa sauce were tender and juicy.  I enjoyed the sides, especially the cheese crisp! 

@NandosSG offers great value and affordable pricing across the entire menu with nett pricing and no service charge

TGIF! It's Friday! 🥳 

Was taken by a friend to experience a super cool and mysterious bistro bar at Central Mall recently! 

@Chapterscosg, a bistro bar hidden behind a bookshelf. You will never find a door to enter the bar. All you can do is knock on the bookshelf and wait for the staff inside to activate the sliding bookshelf door for you. Isn't it mysterious and secretive? 

You will see a sports car 🚘 sitting in the middle of the bar, and their dining areas are designed with different IG-worthy themes, exploring different chapters of life. Each theme has its own unique style; the most unique theme to me was the wall printed with all the mahjong tiles and a big neon green light "發". 

Check out my 🎥 video on reel!

Featured here were what we tried: 

🔹️Canadian Fresh Oyster with Ikura and Carviar 

🔹️ Signatures Tapas Platter 
▪︎ Stir-fry Beef Cubes
▪︎ Fried Soft Shell Crab
▪︎ Black Pepper Chawanmushi with jumbo crab meat 

🔹️Vegetarian Rosti 

Are you keen to find out more? 

Chapters Co is the next instagramable place that you should visit and experience! 

Thank you @liveloveatwithjie for the jio and @Chapterscosg for having us.

Carrot cake with heaps of chye poh! 

Among the stretch of HDB blocks at Yishun, you’ll find @618simcarrotcake , a hawker stall serving carrot cake (Chai Tow Kway) with a unique twist. 

Carrot Cake | $3.50
The carrot cake is soft on the inside and crispy on the outside. They were generous with the amount of eggs added, which allows the carrot cake to hold together as a piece. 

Unlike the usual carrot cake, chye poh is added to the side to provide the additional flavour and juicy crunch to each bite. It is not overly salty and brings a tinge of sweetness in it. We find that the carrot cake itself was lacking flavour. But it makes sense when you eat it together with the chye poh, which struck a balance between the taste. 

The portion is huge which is good for sharing even though we ordered the small one. 

Would you prefer black or white carrot cake?

Looking for fresh, authentic sushi and sashimi? Popular Osaka Conveyor Belt Sushi Chain Chojiro could be the best option for you! 

Chojiro opened its first franchised branch in Singapore at Gochi Japan Kitchen inside Capital Square which houses five other Japanese eateries.

SEASONAL ITEMS

Kani Kyoto style steamed sushi | $20.90
Unlike your usual sushi, this sushi rice is packed into a wooden bamboo crate and topped with generous amount of kani, ikura and tamago. It is served with a fire lit at the bottom to ensure the rice is steeped with all the flavours from the toppings, making each mouthful filled with unaminess. This is definitely a highlight in the restaurant!

Kyoto Pickled Turnip Sushi | $3.90
Not the usual pickled vegetables you’ve tried. The turnip is well marinated - not too sourish and gives a refreshing crunchy bite. Definitely a good appetizer to set off the meal with! 

STANDARD ITEMS

Spicy Maguro Roll | $8.20
Consists of tuna, avocado, cucumber and sushi rice with spicy sauce. 
They have a wide selection of rolls here and are really affordable. The chopped maguro is mixed with the spicy sauce and topped on the maki. They also added ebiko on top, which burst into flavours when you bite on the maki. The spicy sauce is bearable which can be easily enjoyed by all. 

Chojiro Sashimi Set (8 Kinds) | $49.90
Sea urchin, salmon roe, tuna, salmon, yellow tail, squid, botan ebi and scallop sashimi
This sashimi set is of highest freshness and quality! Something unique to be mentioned is the deep fried ebi head, the best part of the prawn where the briny juices are all concentrated there, in a crunchy form.

Crab Shrimp Creamy Gratin | $12.90
This stuffed crab shell is filled with fresh crab and shrimp meat mixed with creamy cheeses. It is perfectly grilled to give a crispy exterior and slight char. The overall taste is appealing and not too jelak. Not to be miss is the eye catching cheese pull!! 😍

Thank you @chojirosg for the kind invite and warm hospitality!

Modern Peranakan Cuisine located at Singapore Chinese Cultural Centre in Tangjong Pagar area. They serve craft cocktails which is an ideal place to unwind after your daily work!🍻🥂

Enjoy Artisanal Japanese Pizza freshly made by Hokkaido Chef in the comfort of your home! @pipipizza.sg deliver unique and sweet thin crust pizzas with a Japanese twist. 

🍤 MENTAIKO ABURI SEAFOOD | $32
Sashimi Grade Squid, Wild Caught Tiger Prawn, White Clams, White Fish, Mentaiko
Fresh seafood immersed in mentaiko sauce are baked to bring out rich umami taste and prominent charred fragrance. There are also generous amount of ebiko mixed with the mentaiko sauce which burst into flavours in your mouth. The drawback for this pizza is that the prawn and clams are not deshelled. Some of the clam shells are hidden inside the mentaiko sauce which we unnoticeably bite into them and had a hard time taking them out. 😅Nevertheless, it is still a delicious pizza to munch on. 

🍕SPAM & TAMAGO YAKI | $28
Pan Seared Spam, Yaki Tamago Egg, Tare Sauce, Bonito Flakes, Umami White Sauce.
Generous ingredients loaded on this thin crust pizza, even the cheese is thicker than the crust itself! We love the addition of yaki tamago egg which gives a chicken-like chewy texture, creating an impression of an overloaded carnivorous pizza. We would prefer adding more white sauce to enhance the overall taste of the pizza.

They provide Islandwide Delivery at only $8! Hurry place your orders if you have not plan your food for this weekend gathering/dinner. 
Thank you @pipipizza.sg for sending over these yummy pizzas!😍

📍@breadtalksg 🍰

My order 🧾
🍰 Granite, $5.80
🍰 Matcha No Keki, $6.50

Granite 🍰◼️
Saw a few good reviews about this so decided to try it 😁 It is an ensemble of black sesame mousse, vanilla chiffon, Oreo black sesame crumbs and a New York Cheesecake style layer. I like that the mousse is creamy without being overly rich or sweet. The black sesame taste is prominent and not too overpowering because of the addition of chiffon cake and oreo crumbs. The crumbs also give that grainy texture to the cake. I like that the cheesecake layer gives a slight saltiness to balance the overall cake flavour. Overall, not bad for the price imo 😊

Matcha No Keki 🍰🍵
Slightly pricier than the black ssm. Didn’t quite enjoy this tbh because the matcha chiffon is firm and not soft and fluffy. The matcha taste is also very mild with just a hint of bitter aftertaste which totally got overpowered by the sweet red beans. The cake is not that creamy and the red beans are also solid and not the pasty kind

.

description:
📍@queic.singapore 🧀

Visited @oliviarestaurant_sg awhile back to try their famous burnt cheesecake (#dtxolivia) and so happens that it’s also my first post here at @dtfoodaffair 😉

The restaurant doesnt allow dining in for desserts only and I’m glad to know that they have opened up a shop nearby to serve their desserts now 

Our orders 🧾
🧀 Olivia’s Homemade Cheesecake, $15+
🧀 Olivia’s Chocolate Cheesecake, $17+
🧀 Parmesan Cheesecake, $10+

Olivia’s Homemade Cheesecake 🧀⭐️
Still the star of the show and one of the best burnt cheesecakes around! Instead of the usual slice that is served at the restaurant, you get a whole 4” tart now. Oozy blue cheese centre with a crispy tart base..mm..yummy! 😋👌🏻

Olivia’s Chocolate Cheesecake 🍫🧀
If you are not a big fan of cheese, you could try their chocolate cheesecake which is richer in chocolate and comes with hazelnut praline. The dark chocolate cream is thick, creamy and not that sweet. I prefer cheese and oozy filling so I’ll pick the original any time 😁

Parmesan Cheesecake 🧀
Another option for cheese lover. The parmesan cheese is rich, creamy and pretty strong. May get a tad cloying since it’s rich and creamy. Better for sharing!

.
.
.
.

description:
Sourdough Croissants from
📍@sourbombebakery 🥐

Having tried their bombolinis previously (#dtxsourbombe), I was curious about their sourdough croissants and got myself a box to try end of last year 😁

Signature Box 🎁
🥐 Ispahan
🥐 Kaya W Soy Caramel
🥐 Pistachio Mango
🥐 Black Sesame Mochi
🥐 Passionfruit Meringue
🥐 OG Croissant

They come up with new flavours pretty regularly tho so some of these flavours are no longer available 🙈 I think only the kaya and pistachio still remain in their current lineup 🙊 and ofc, the plain one as well

Anyway, before I move on to the fillings, gotta say the texture of the croissants didnt quite hit the mark for me as they are not buttery or flaky even after reheating. Not sure if that’s the case for sourdough croissants 🤔

Ispahan 🥐🌹
Light floral and lychee fragrance. The lychee custard is a bit sweet with a hint of tanginess from the raspberry rose jam

Kaya W Soy Caramel 🥐
The kaya custard is quite fragrant with a hint of coconut fragrance. A bit on the sweet side

Pistachio Mango 🥐🥭
Slightly crispier and more flakey since it’s flatter than the rest. Pistachio frangipane filling with actual mango bits. The pistachio is pretty light in flavour

Black Sesame Mochi 🥐
Oozy black sesame custard filling that is milky and mild. Not much roasted fragrance and black sesame taste. This is topped with hojicha creme that is also milky but at least has a slight roasted flavour

Passionfruit Meringue 🥐
The passionfruit curd is sourish and doesnt have that citrusy fragrance. The meringue is dense and a bit cloying

OG Croissant 🥐
Slightly flakier than the rest but still not buttery. There is a slight tang from the sourdough

Tbh, I prefer their bombolinis over the croissants 😬

💸: $39 (excluding delivery fee)

.

.
.

📍le matin patisserie • wagyu & bone marrow sausage roll🥢
A moment of sheer indulgence with this < Wagyu & Bone Marrow Sausage Roll > from < Le Matin Patisserie >. One of the 4 items in its Savoury Box: Assemblage ($58), now available separately.
.
Wagyu Beef mince rolled up in flaky puff pastry, topped with bone marrow, glazed with black garlic and garnished with a thyme stem. Warmed up in the #balmuda toaster to a decadent and aromatic deliciousness before we dug in.
.
The simple, grand magic of Chef Mohamed Al-Matin, who was head pastry chef at the former 2-Michelin-star Restaurant Andre, before he moved on to 3-Michelin-star Noma in Copenhagen - ranked TOP world’s 50 best restaurant. Chef Matin returned to Singapore and opened his eponymous < Le Matin Patisserie > last year, which by a stroke of serendipity, means "the morning" in French.
..
Minimalistic vibes with 1616/Arita Japan tableware, a perfect canvas for this beauty.
.
.
.

| cny 2022 • lo bak gou 萝卜糕🥢
'Lo Bak Gou' or Radish Cake is our traditional Cantonese Dim Sum favourite, be it steamed or pan-fried.
.
We look forward to it especially during the Chinese New Year, as a savoury snack to be enjoyed during afternoon tea, and served to guests besides the sweet goodies.
.
This year, we made our own instead of getting it from Canton Paradise. Pan-fried with egg and served with spicy ABC garlic chilli sauce, cravings satisfied.
.
.
.
.
.

| cny 2022 • 人日 ~ 大年初七 🎏
Today marks Day 7 of the Lunar New Year. Typically, a 
< Prosperity Raw Fish Salad or 发财鱼生 > is tossed and eaten to celebrate 人日 or 'The Common Man's Birthday'.
.
Other than the Cantonese < Lou Sang 撈生 >, we usually enjoy an array of < Japanese Sashimi > to usher in surplus and abundance, year after year 年年有余.
.
In frame: a home-assembled < Chirashi Don >  comprising seven varieties of seafood: Maguro (tuna), Sake (salmon), Kanpachi (yellowtail), Hotate (scallop), Ebi (sweet prawn), Tako (octopus) and Ikura (salmon roe). Fresh and tasty, Japanese Sashimi cravings satisfied 🍣.
.
Happy 人日 everyone !
.
.
.
.

| cny 2022 • homestyle cheeseboard 🧀
In our house, grazing platters / cheese & charcuterie boards are a pretty regular thing.
.
Today's CNY Day 2 < Cheese Platter > with prosciutto ham, brie cheese, crackers, juicy strawberries, sweet grapes and smoked almonds. A simple cheese board, glad that everyone loves it 🤍
.
With a bottle of white which was too clunky for the pix. So I rolled out the cooking wine for illustration as usual, simple and unobtrusive 😝

I was pretty curious when I found that @thekindbowl_sg ‘s The Kind Pho was ranked the number one dish in @abillion 50 Best Vegan Dish in Singapore. Priced at S$9.80 it was similarly priced compared to the usual pho in Singapore. Flat rice noodles in a peppery broth topped with sliced seitan, sliced oyster mushrooms, raw bean sprouts, and fresh herbs with a wedge of lime and sliced chilli padi served by the side. Great for a cold day although wish there could be more depth in the broth.

The Crazy Baguette A.K.A BÁNH MÌ (S$9.80) was another popular item which was ranked #11 on the chart. Love the crispy crusted baguette which was packed to max with pickles, grilled seitan, fresh herbs, mushroom pâté, egg (not sure it’s egg or tofu), herbs and homemade sriracha mayo. Messy to eat but super yummy. And filling.

Also, abillion will give you US $1 to donate one of 64 causes when you leave a food review on abillion app! Check out my reviews on the abillion app where I have written as alamakgirl. Looking forward to try other vegan restaurants that I’ve discovered thanks to abillion app.

We checked out @plainvanillasg for a quick brunch.  The space is nice and the coffee good.  We also tried some of their bakes but found them kinda average.  Take the galette for example, whilst the filling was ok, the crust was too thick relative to the filling and a little bit stodgy rather than crispy layers.  The quiche was also ok but the crust could also be more crisp and buttery. But I guess I was most disappointed with the cauliflower salad?  I was hoping it would be more charred but it was a little wet and soft, like it was boiled rather than grilled. 😔

description:
Farewell to a dear colleague and friend and we marked the occasion with a thank you dinner @imperialtreasuresg .  Being all Teochews, it was a feast full of Teochew specialities, starting with some steamed cold crab (not really my thing cos kinda troublesome 😬). We even had the platter including some pig’s ear, you know, just as a dare to see how Teochew we are? 

Anyways braised pig’s ear is something I’ve had when I was growing up (yeah that’s a long time ago…) and I remember it fondly, together with pig snout which is actually even better 😬. Anyways the version here is soso with more cartilage then I remember.  Another notable dish from dinner was the smoked chicken.  I didn’t have much expectation as most roast chicken is just kinda meh, but the version here was tender and had a unique umami taste from the smoking process.  Quite nice, I like. 

But my favouritest dish and also more unique dish here, is the fried bee hoon like thingy.  Not sure what it’s called but it’s deep fried like a pancake and eat with a generous dousing of black vinegar and sugar!!! Sounds weird?  No, it’s absolutely delicious imho.  It’s kinda like a yummy savoury dessert and i really love it!  I always order this whenever I see it available in a Teochew restaurant and the version here didn’t disappoint! 🤤
fullName: This Is Why I’m Fat And Broke

description: We were out of ideas and out of time, so we finally settled on a nearby bakery cafe to grab a quick brunch.  Whilst @thekazocafe_sg is not hipster cafe, their bakes turned out to be quite a surprise find!  Whilst I’m not a big fan of garlic cheese bread, the version here is pretty soft and fluffy with a generous cream filling. But what impressed me more was their range of savoury danishes.  The puff pastry was very flaky and buttery and the danishes also had generous filling.  We enjoyed both their mushroom and bacon versions.  Quite a nice find in my neighborhood, I certainly wouldn’t mind buying more bakes from here in future!
fullName: This Is Why I’m Fat And Broke

Let's do some Thai 🇹🇭 Fiesta tonight! 🤩 This is one of my most favorite thai dishes ever! Not sure what this dish is supposed to be called. It's supposed to be "Miang Pla Too"  but I did not use Pla Too...so I'm a bit confused, if anybody could tell me what this dish called, please let me know 🥰😒

Was introduced by my Thai friends when I was in Bangkok, except I think they used mackarel instead.I could not find my mackarel around, so I substituted with carp, and guess what? It worked just perfect!✌🏻 what I think the most intriguing part from this dish is the way you eat. You wrap the fish with your favorite greens of your choice, put the fish and rice noodle in (traditionally I think they use Kha Nom Jeen, but I dont think they are available in my area, so I substituted with somen noodle✌🏻) pour some scrumptious seafood sauce and add some herbs. *Omg I thought I was in heaven🤤*

🚨 Dessert Alert!

📍 Thornys, 21 Woodlands Close 
🍽 MaoShanWang Mousse ($6.50)
5 ⭐ / 5

If you are a durian lover, this is definitely a place you have to go! And if you're not, this place might just convert you!

This MSW durian mousse has got to be one of the best durian desserts my mouth has ever had the pleasure of tasting! The mousse itself is so thick, creamy and rich, with the bittersweet MSW taste featuring so prominently! And it even comes with a huge dollop of durian at the top! I ate this thing so fast that I almost cried when I finished it! It is really THAT good!!

Also pictured:
Grass Jelly Longan ($3.50)
Mango and Pineapple Fruit Tea ($4 each)

Verdict: 🥇 Must come again!

[Invited Tasting] 🧋Bubble Tea!

📍 MILK Singapore, 27 Arab Street
🍽 Brown Sugar Milk Brûlée ($6) + Chendol Royale ($6.80)
4 ⭐ / 5

First Muslim-owned bubble tea in Singapore! Yesterday, they had their relaunch day at their flagship store, with a brand new look and new menu! 

One of their new additions is an interactive build your own MILK wall, where you can customise your own bubble tea! First, grab a Milk or Milk Tea pail, then choose your flavours + toppings. Bring it to the counter and watch your creation turn into reality!

Milk - Strawberry, Grape, Mango
Milk Tea - Caramel, Hazelnut, Taro, Chocolate, Ovaltine
Toppings - Ice cream, Nata de coco, Grass jelly, Pearl, Jelly

~ Brown Sugar Milk Brûlée 
This is a variation of the well-known brown sugar fresh milk with pearls, with a twist at the end; they add a layer of milk foam followed by a layer of sugar at the top and blowtorch it to get the nice caramelisation! I love it when you get those bits of caramelised goodness when you take a sip of the drink! Such a shame though that the plastic seal at the top hides the beautiful brown caramelisation underneath!

~ Chendol Royale 
Literally a dessert in a cup! Super authentic chendol taste, with fresh creamy coconut milk and gula melaka. It even comes with red bean and chendol to complete the drink! Although it was a tad too sweet for my liking, I would still highly recommend it! 

Verdict: 🥈 Can come again!
- Would definitely love to try the other signature drinks and have a go at their build your own MILK wall!

Thank you @milk.singapore for the hospitality!

#MILKyourdaybetter

☕ Coffee alert!

📍 Starbucks, various locations
🍽 Iced Smoked Butterscotch Latte, venti ($8.90)
4.2 ⭐ / 5

Never seen this drink before on the menu and decided to give it a shot since it sounded really intriguing! 

This drink combines espresso with steamed milk and smoked butterscotch sauce. When you take a sip, the first thing that hits you is this sweet butterscotch espresso flavour, followed by a smokey aftertaste. All the components seem to blend with each other really well, which is a pleasant surprise! The drink is rather sweet though, and so might not be everyone's cup of tea (or coffee in this case lol)! Give it a try for yourself!

Verdict: 🥇 Sure buy again!

🥤 Yoghurt alert!

📍 Hey Yoghurt, various locations
🍽 Avocado Yoghurt (UP $7.50)
3 ⭐ / 5

Hey Yoghurt is currently having a 1-for-1 promotion until 28 Feb, so of course I had to get onboard and check it out! Got 2 drinks at $7.50 i.e. each drink is $3.75 which is really value for money!!

Got the drink with 50% sugar, which was just nice and not too sweet; tastes super healthy too! The drink is super thick and smooth, which is absolutely divine! And surprisingly, it was super filling, enough to replace a whole meal for me!

Unfortunately, the avocado taste was super faint, barely perceptible if I may say so, which is such a shame considering that this is an avocado yoghurt drink. If this was a plain yoghurt drink though, it'll be at least a 4.5 ⭐!

Verdict: 🥈 Can come again!
- Heard the purple rice yoghurt is good so I'll probably try that the next time!

🍦 Frozen yoghurt alert!

📍 llao llao, various locations
🍽 Large tub frozen yoghurt + 3 toppings ($7)
4.8 ⭐ / 5 

Seems like as these companies grow bigger, their cups grow smaller lol.

But that being said, llao llao is currently my favorite frozen yoghurt chain. Absolutely love the smooth texture and the flavours of their frozen yoghurt, just the perfect blend of sour and sweet with it not being overly sweet! And they even have premium walnuts as one of the toppings now! So obviously I got that and my 2 favourites, as always, cookie butter sauce and hazelnut chocolate sauce! You can never have too many toppings!

Verdict: 🥇 Sure come again!

Been seeing these amazing-looking bagels from @jiababa88 everywhere on IG and was thrilled to finally be able to try them!! ☺️☺️

𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐒𝐞𝐬𝐚𝐦𝐞 𝐁𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐏𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐁𝐮𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫 + 𝐌𝐨𝐜𝐡𝐢 🥜🥯
The bagel was soo soft (yet kinda chewy) after heating up!! The mochi was SUPERR SOFT too omg and really stretchy as well. 😍😍 Love how thick the peanut butter filling was - there were also crunchy peanut bits to munch on! 

𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨 𝐁𝐚𝐠𝐞𝐥 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐌𝐚𝐭𝐜𝐡𝐚 𝐖𝐡𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨 𝐁𝐫𝐨𝐰𝐧𝐢𝐞 + 𝐂𝐡𝐨𝐜𝐨 𝐒𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 🍫🍵🥯
Love how thick and sweet the chocolate was!! 😍😍 (It melted after heating up, hence the ugly photo... 😥 but I promise it tastes WAYYY BETTER than it looks 🥺). The matcha taste was quite prominent and went really well with the chocolate + bagel. Overall, this was really chocolatey but so so good. 🙌🏻🙌🏻 Would also recommend pairing it with a glass of milk!🥛

Thankyou @jiababa88 for the bagels, they were super yummy!! Do follow them and keep a lookout for their different weekly flavours!! ☺️🙌🏻

📍Artea SG

Dropped by @arteasg (Vivo City Outlet) recently and tried some of their popular drinks!! ☺️☺️

𝐂𝐞𝐲𝐥𝐨𝐧 𝐌𝐢𝐥𝐤 🍼🍪
Really liked this because of the lotus biscoff (added a sweet layer to the drink)!! 🤤🤤 Even though this was quite milky, there was still a strong tea taste in the drink. Love how there was a good balance of flavours, plus it wasn't too sweet either! 💯💯

𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐰𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐅𝐮𝐣𝐢 🍓🍓

𝐌𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐨 𝐌𝐨𝐦𝐨 💛🍼

There were also some jelly bits inside - I'd say it's quite a fun drink hehe. 💯💯

The Spring Festival or the Lunar New Year is a time for the popular Pen Cai ( 盆菜 ), a traditional Cantonese festive meal filled with layers of ingredients.
 
Well, I’ve laid the base of my pot with Cabbage, then filled mine with Chicken Broth, Roast Pork, Prawns, Dried Scallops, Fish Maw, Black Moss, different types of Chinese Mushrooms, and of course my favourite Abalones! 
 
I’ve also rolled up a Cabbage Rose and placed it in the centre of my Pen Cai.  What do you think of my CNY Prosperity Pot?  What ingredients do you usually put into yours? 🧧㊗️

French Périgord Black Truffle Oil ( 黑松露油 ), Truffle Salt ( 黑松露盐 ) & Shaved Truffles ( 黑松露 ), that’s what you’ll find in this swanky 𝗖𝗡𝗬 𝗚𝗼𝗹𝗱𝗲𝗻 𝗧𝗿𝘂𝗳𝗳𝗹𝗲 𝗦𝗲𝗮𝗳𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗙𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗱 𝗥𝗶𝗰𝗲 ( 招财进宝黑松露炒饭 )!

Gosh, there’s so much things you can do with Truffles!  Add them onto Salads, Pasta, Eggs or even Fried Rice like this one to enhance your food! 😋

Besides having great nutritional values, Truffles are great for Vegetarians too. Simply remove all the seafood in this recipe & you’ll get a luxurious Vegetarian Fried Rice!

(Serves 4-5)
Ingredients:
3 cups Overnight Rice
1 dozen Prawns (diced)
½ cup Silver Fish
3 tbsp Tobiko
3 tbsp Edamame
3 Eggs (beaten)
2 Garlic Cloves (chopped)
½ Onion (chopped)
½ tsp Truffle Salt
5 tbsp Olive Oil
Pepper to taste
Truffle Oil & Shavings for toppings

Prawn Marinade:
½ Grated Ginger
1 tsp Sesame Oil
1 tsp Oyster Sauce
Pinch of Truffle Salt
Pepper to taste

Method:
1️⃣ Marinate Prawns for 15 mins.
2️⃣ Heat Oil & fry Silver Fish till crispy. Drain & set aside.
3️⃣ Fry Eggs till half cooked. Throw in Onions & sauté till fragrant, add Garlic & Prawns.
4️⃣ When Prawns turned pink, add Rice, Edamame, Salt & Pepper.  Mix well.
5️⃣ Turn off fire & throw in Tobiko & Silver Fish. Stir well.
6️⃣ Transfer onto serving plate, top with Tobiko, Silver Fish & Shaved Black Truffles. Drizzle Truffle Oil & serve your Yummy CNY Golden Truffle Seafood Fried Rice!

* 𝗧𝗶𝗽𝘀:
- Remove Truffle from juice & let it sit on a paper towel. Pat dry.
- Slice the Truffle with a microplane or knife, then add them to your dish. Enhance further by drizzling Truffle Oil.

📍 Hector's Deli | Richmond

I have heard sooo many good things about this place. I was ready for a good sandwich, but this was just next level 😍

On the menu: 
🥤 Iced coffee 
🥪 Beef & Pickles with Hector's crazy sauce 🤪

The sandwich was delishh (the sauce was similar to Big Mac sauce, is that rude?), the rye grilled to give it a good crunch, and the sanga overall was soo much more filling than I expected - had to take a couple deep breaths to get through it! Definitely no regrets though 🤤

The coffee was also sooo easy to drink, the only sad part was that our doggos got too excited and knocked the table and that was the end of my drink 🥲

And yes, my coffee name is Megan 😂 what's your coffee name?

📍 Palermo | Melbourne CBD (Little Bourke Street

If you're looking to splurge a little, don't be Sicily to pass up @palermomelbourne ! 

We had the Asada set menu ($110pp), which includes:

🍞 Fugazzeta - Charred spring onion, mozzarella & potato focaccia

🥟 Empanada - Braised beef, chipotle & pickled chilli

🐟 Ceviche - White fish, cucumber, salted grapes, gin, celery

🫔 Chorizo - Pork & paprika sausage

🌭 Morcilla - Spiced black sausage

🐄 Ojo de Bife - O’Connor’s premium, pasture fed scotch fillet, VIC (first photo)

🐖 Cochinillo a la Cruz - Western Plains pork slow cooked over the fire pit (second photo)

🥕 Zanahorias - Grilled carrots, carrot pureè, buckwheat, pistachio & tarragon pesto (missed photo)

🥗Ensalada - Baby cos, frisee, pickled zucchini, green olive, raspberry vinaigrette

🍮Flan - Dulce de leche crème caramel, salted peanut praline

🍪 Alfajor - Argentine shortbread cookie filled with dulce de leche

Every single dish was sensational! 💯

The medium rare on the beef was perfect, with a nice char flavour in the outside yet still juicy and tender in the middle. That being said, I LOVED the pork belly more than the steak (this was an unpopular opinion). 🤤

The ceviche was so fresh and was a great palate cleanser for the other dishes to come. 

I'm also not usually a flan person, but this one was 👌

One San Telmo restaurant ticked off the list, four more to go! 🥳
