Porridge & Steamed🥚 for breakfast!

Recipe:
• Add half a cup of day old rice🍚 & a cup of water into a pot
• Boil for 30mins

• Crack 2 eggs into a bowl
• Add a little less than a cup of water
• Mix mix mix
• Steam for 10-15mins
• Add whatever toppings you like!
( I added soya sauce & sesame oil )

👉🏻 O.BBa Jjajang
Had a mad craving for jjajangmyeon so obviously I had to visit the highly reviewed O.BBa Jjajang for it! & Y'all all I can say is this place has the best jjajangmyeon! 😙
We had Tangsuyuk & Kimchi Pancake too! Their tangsuyuk was quite popular too so we decided to try it. It was not bad but I think it's a personal preference as we didn't quite enjoy the thick and chewy batter. I guess we lean more towards the zichar kind of sweet and sour pork 😅 Kimchi pancake was nice and chewy as well, and it's good for sharing! 👍🏻
Now on to the best thing, their Jjajangmyeon! I really missed the ones in korea and this bowl of goodness brought me back to korea! Every mouth was super satisfying!! 🤤 It's really a MUST ORDER here!! If y'all having mad jjm cravings like me just go here and satisfy it even tho the waiting time was freaking 1 hour on a friday evening 🥲 but trust me the jjm is 10/10 worth the wait! ☺️

👉🏻 Wooshi 
Super overdue post butttt- Really sad to find out that Wooshi has closed their Orchard Gateway outlet 😢 It was my go to affordable food when I was in that area 😢 That being said they still have other outlets which I will patronise soon! I really love their concept, similar to Makisan but w different ingredients! They also have sushi roll option! Personally prefer their range of ingredients esp the sweet potato noodles which is super hard to find a place offering that as a choice!!Really wish they can open more outlets like makisan 🥲

👉🏻 MEIDI-YA
The sushi at MEIDI-YA is definitely the best quality for supermarket sushi imo!! Slightly more ex compared to Donki but definitely better!! The scallop was super good and fresh!! I forgot the price but it's around ~$14 very worth it imo as it's comparable to restaurant standard!! 😋 Unagi sushi and maki was pretty good toooo! Definitely recommend going here to get sushi! Worth it! 👍🏻

CNY is almost here and I've been so lucky to start indulging in bak kwa from the one brand that my mum only buys from - Fragrance (@fragrance_bak_kwa)! 🔥

This time, I tried their Freshly Grilled Honey Bak Kwa and it was as good as I remember it. 🍯 Tender and juicy, it's best enjoyed after a quick toast in the oven.

Also tried the Salted Egg Potato Chips and I appreciated how thick the chips were. 👌 They made every piece feel substantial and so satisfying.

Thank you @fragrance_bak_kwa for sending these over!

📍Fragrance 🇸🇬

Very late to the game, but I finally tried King Of Fried Rice (@kingoffriedricesg) a while ago to see what the hype was all about. 

I was surprised by the variety of options they offered, but I went for the classic Egg Fried Rice with Pork Cutlet (SGD6.50) since it was the original. 🍳

It was a more than decent plate of egg fried rice with rather sinfully oily rice but a lack of wok hei. 😕 As for the pork cutlet, it was beautifully deep-fried to a golden-brown hue, but wasn't as juicy as I was hoping it'd be.

Not sure if it was worth the hype, but if I'm craving pork cutlet fried rice and feeling like splurging again, then maybe I'd give this a go!

📍King Of Fried Rice 🇸🇬

I've always loved steamboats. They're a great activity to socialise over and the best part is you get a bottomless pot of soup that you can continuously add things in to cook! 😋 Fortunately, Nu Er Hong Hotpot and Grill (@nuerhong_restaurant) offers a Korean seafood hotpot + BBQ buffet, the first in SG. 

For a limited time only, they're having a promotion where adults eat for just $29.90++/pax (U.P. $49.90++). 🥘 With a wide variety of soup bases and ingredients to choose from, you'll definitely be spoiled for choice. Think Korean side dishes like Kimchi Cabbage, seafood favourites like Crab and Tiger Prawns, and meat items like Beef Tenderloin and Pork Belly which are great for BBQ-ing. 🥩 

The items all tasted fresh and the variety was more than incredible. If you or you know someone who are big eaters, this is the place to get your hotpot and kbbq cravings satisfied. 🔥

Thank you @nuerhong_restaurant for the invite! 

📍Nu Er Hong Restaurant 🇸🇬

Went for a late night drive to Yishun to have nasi lemak for supper but we were craving for dessert afterwards and luckily No Horse Run (@nohorserunsg) was still open at 12am! 🍨

I desperately wanted to avoid anything caffeinated because I didn't want to have trouble sleeping but I gave in and ordered two chocolate-flavoured scoops - the signature Fleur De Cao Dark Chocolate and Burnt White Chocolate. 🍫

Both contrasted each other well as the former was bitter while latter leaned towards the sweeter side of life and had a slight smokiness. 💨 Not to mention, the scoops were pretty large too so it was worth it. 

A pity their IG-famous pandan mochi waffles were already sold out, so I guess I'll have to return another time! 🧇

📍No Horse Run 🇸🇬

The Taro Coconut was as good as I remember having it on my very first P&P experience, while the Earl Grey Tea was interestingly decadent with a distinct floral aroma. 💐 I haven't eaten the Cookies & Cream yet, hence not pictured; will update in the comments once I do so!

[ Yat Ka Yan ] - A traditional traditional desserts shop situated at Fortune Centre, I like the name of this venue -  @yatkayan in Cantonese it means “one family”! 
.
This venue offers a huge variety of desserts and some local snacks like yam kueh, chee cheong fun etc, sweet or savoury they got your covered 🥰 but best part is their service is really good, you can feel the warmth from them just like being at home 🏠 
.
What we have tried: 
😋Yam Paste (Orh Nee) - $3(S), $5.50(L)
*the one you see on my photos is Large
Orh Nee is an all time favourite traditional Teochew dessert that is usually cooked with pork lard and shallot oil… due to the tedious process in making, most of the time we get to eat this is when we attend someone’s wedding although now there are many dessert shops also start to sell Orh Nee, but not many are good, most of them uses the pre-made yam paste, upon order they will microwave it and serve it to you… but this one here is really authentic, you get to eat the smooth yam paste with bits within, coconut milk and topped with generous amount of ginkgo nuts… MUST ORDER if you are here…
.
😋Black Sesame Paste - $3.50
This is smooth and flavourful, not too sweet… comparable with Ah Chew Dessert… for a more fulfilling experience we added 汤圆to it, every pcs is $0.50, flavours available are peanut and sesame… there are also other add ons eg. Taro balls that I am keen to try the next time…
.
Looking for authentic local dessert, check this venue out, don’t say I never share 😍
.

📍Yat Ka Yan 【一家人】

Usually, around this time of the year, some of us in the office will head up north to Malaysia for a conference. But since Covid doesn’t allow us to travel, some of us decided to book a hotel while attending the conference held in Singapore last year to simulate an overseas trip. 🤣
.
Well, we decided to do the same again this year. We tried @live.lyf.here last year and #yotelsingapore this time. 
.
Pleasantly impressed by the hotel - more about that later. Anyway, the stay came with breakfast - apparently it’s cheaper to book with breakfast than without - go figure 🤷🏻‍♂️
.
Breakfast was quite decent. We got the yoghurt, salad and croissant platter soon after we got seated and had a choice of 3 warm breakfast options to chose from. I had western for the first morning and Nasi Lemak for the 2nd. And there was a slight change to the warm breakfast menu during the 2 mornings we were there. 
.
While I wasn’t impressed by it - and I wasn’t expecting to be - but the breakfast WAS quite decent.
.
In any case, if you are looking a place for a short staycation - I would recommend #yotelsingapore - though the room is a tad smaller than @live.lyf.here’s - I really love the way they were able to pack everything in such a small space - sleek, high tech, and modern looking - with a comfy and reclinable bed. And we also had a great view of the city since we were on the 25th storey.

My first plate of Fried Rice since my Keto Diet - but not just any Fried Rice - it’s the “King of Fried Rice” - so the sign says.
.
My friend suggested going there to try since he hasn’t had it before. And actually, I’ve not had it either and wasn’t quite keen to having it for lunch cos fried rice is basically a plate full of CARBS…!! 😱😱
.
Well, glad I tried. There is definitely wok-hey. Interestingly, they use short-grain rice instead of long grain rice. But I guess the star of the dish has to the the pork chop - well seasoned with five spice powder - it was tender and aromatic - and this dish only cost $6.50 - pretty affordable compared to the food at the other foodcourt diagonally across from where this eatery is located at.
.
Would I eat it again - most definitely - and I will also come back for their other foods as well - Old Airport Road hawker centre’s Nam Sing Hokkien Mee, Famous Eunos Bak Chor Mee, Beach Road’s Scissors Cut Curry Rice, Ann Chin Popiah, Tiong Bahru’s Jian Bo Shui Kueh - all under one roof…!!
.
By the way, I didn’t finish the rice - I did have some but offered the rest to my 2 friends.
.

[Throw Back - “Leftover” food from 2021] 🤣
.
Was trying hard to search on internet for the name of this pastry shop at Ngee Ann City…and after what seems like forever - found it! It’s “Charlie Tea” … and how could I miss that ..?? “Charlie” - “茶礼”…!! Get it…?? 🤦🏻‍♂️🤣
.
Anyway, walked past it so often but never really tried until my friend suggested going for tea there. Not a fan of their tea - cos I don’t enjoy such tea drinks - but I DID enjoy their pastries. These bite size tarts were small and easy to eat and love the flakiness of the pastry. But do eat there. I got some home for my family to try and it wasn’t as nice. Guess due to the humidity of sunny Singapore - its flakiness were gone by the time we were ready to enjoy it.
.
By the way, thanks for tea - you know who you are…! ☺️
.

👩‍🍳MUNCH AT HOME👩‍🍳
Happy Chinese New Year's Eve🧧! For our Reunion dinner today, we made some Braised Minced Meat Noodles🍜, Boiled Dumplings🥟 and Savoury Tangyuan. Made our own Tangyuan which was super nice, soft and chewy as compared to the frozen ones. This version of Tangyuan has no filling, which went really nicely with the soup and other ingredients🍲. Tangyuan symbolizes family reunion and we hope that on this special day, all of us are all reunited with our loved ones🥰.

👩‍🍳MUNCH AT HOME👩‍🍳
Made some Mongolian Chicken🍗 and Kung Pao Ee Fu Noodles for dinner today! Loved the Mongolian Chicken, which are deep-fried chicken strips coated in a creamy sauce with a little hint of spice. We had it with Ee Fu noodles, but it'll definitely go well with a bowl of rice~🍚

🍴TAKE OUT🍴
📍Nam Kee Pau, Waterway Point📍
💸 Amy Yip Pau
...
We don’t usually think of having Pau as a meal, but the Nam Kee Pau's Amy Yip Pau is a hefty one😱. It's so huge and heavy compared to a usual pau that it could be a meal if you're not super hungry🍽️! Though its huge, the taste is definitely not compromised. The skin was not too thick and the filling is juicy and well-seasoned🥩, but just a bit oily. We recommend it to be shared actually, as it could get a bit much after a while😬!!

🍴DINE OUT🍴
📍Spago Dining Room, Marina Bay Sands📍
💸 3 Course Prix Fixe: $65++
• Traditional Kaiserschmarrn (For two) +$10 each 
• Tarte au Chocolat +$10 
• Agnolotti with Porcini Mushrooms
• Smoked Brisbane Valley Quail
• Chicken ‘Laksa’ Spring Roll
*Prices not inclusive of GST/Service Charge
...
Spied a few new dishes on Spago's menu since the last time we went so we just had to try it👀! The biggest surprise was definitely the desserts. First up, the Traditional Kaiserschmarrn! The serving for this was hugeee, even when shared between two👭. The pancake had a soft and custardy texture to it. And as it was served warm, it contrasted well with the cold strawberry ice cream🍦. A really nice and comforting dessert😍! The Tarte au Chocolat was equally good too with it's super rich and intense chocolate flavour🍫, and the hazelnuts and cacao tuile adding a nice crunchy texture to it. A great sweet end to the meal~😆
location: Spago by Wolfgang Puck at Marina Bay Sands

Established since 1971 at the former Mandarin Singapore, Chatterbox @chatterboxsg returns at Hilton Singapore Orchard @hiltonsingaporeorchard with a brand-new space, menu and dining experience. They are set to open next week, 14 Mar 2022.

My first visit to Chatterbox was at least 20 years ago and I came back multiple times for business lunch, dining with family and friends mainly for their Chicken Rice and Lobster Laksa. I remembered there is once Chatterbox shifted to Top of the M offers 360-degree views of the city before moving back to level 5, memorable experience. I feel that Chatterbox is not only just for business meals and visitors from overseas, but also suitable for those who are looking for a nice dining environment to catch up with friends over a meal or celebrating an occasion. If your intention is just to have a nice plate of chicken rice, finish within 10mins and go, here may not be suitable for you.

Their Mandarin Chicken Rice Set ($25.00++) is served boneless with a side of fragrant, broth-cooked jasmine rice, and warm soup, accompanied by trio of homemade signature chilli sauce, ginger puree and dark soya sauce. Aside from the Individual Mandarin Chicken Rice Set, you have options to order Half Chicken ($38.00++) and Whole Chicken ($72.00++) for sharing too.

Location: Chatterbox, Hilton Singapore Orchard, 333 Orchard Road, 05-03, Singapore 238887

happy new year everyone! here’s to satisfying our tongues and filling our tummies with more good food in 2022 🥰❤️

Tomato & Shrimp Bisque

Sometimes you just want soup and bread. I love a good bisque. A thick and creamy soup, it started with a base made with Shrimp shells and butter giving it an intense flavour. 

Add celery, onions, garlic, thyme, bay leaves and fry, don’t let it burn.

Next add water and simmer for 30mins, then sieve the stock and set aside.

In another heavy pan, add olive oil, minced garlic, thyme, onions, and celery, cook till soften. Sprinkle a little flour and stir for about a minute. This is your roux and helps thicken the soup. Add the shrimp stock, Worcestershire sauce, Cajun spices and purée in blender (you can skip this and just leave the whole soup chunky) 

I like my bisque blended but I like my tomatoes and shrimps in chunks. So I’ll add the purée soup back into a pot and add a can of chopped tomatoes, peas, cream and stir till combined. Salt & Pepper to taste. Serve with toasted bread. 

You need to get good fresh shrimps for this soup, preferably not frozen. 
.
.

Assam Batang anyone? 

These beautiful Batang steaks were from @9sseafood I first air-fried them in my @ninjakitchensg Air-grill before slipping them into this fiery appetite whetting sauce. Added whatever vegetables was left in the fridge and enjoyed this fresh spicy goodness with white jasmine rice. 

Satisfied and contented! 

What did I use for the paste? 
I grinded a simple paste from garlic, lemongrass, shallots, dried chillies and belacan and fried it in oil till fragrant. 

Next I added Assam juice (tamarind pulp soaked in warm water for 15mins and remove seeds) + fish curry powder.

Followed by the veggies, a must have is tomatoes 🍅, here I added sweet peas too. Next salt and sugar to taste and finally the fried Batang and some spare shrimps that was lying around in the freezer.
That’s it.
.
.

My sauce mixture is always done on an "impromptu" manner. Likewise, every crisping, grilling, baking/roasting on my Ninja Foodi is an experimental process. And when I get it so "𝑷𝒆𝒓𝒇𝒆𝒄𝒕𝒐!!!" like this plate of 𝑮𝒓𝒊𝒍𝒍𝒆𝒅 𝑮𝒂𝒓𝒍𝒊𝒄 𝑷𝒐𝒓𝒌 𝑪𝒉𝒐𝒑 and 𝑮𝒂𝒓𝒍𝒊𝒄 𝑯𝒆𝒓𝒃𝒔 𝑹𝒐𝒂𝒔𝒕 𝑷𝒐𝒕𝒂𝒕𝒐𝒆𝒔, then I better pen down the recipe (self note).

Grilled to perfection with internal temperature at 65°C, the meat is so tender and juicy, the best pork chop I have ever done. Perfect doneness (especially for this thickness at 1.5"). Served with homegrown scarlet kale and grilled tomato, it's yummilicious that hubs kept showing his thumbs up with every bite 😍.

2pcs 1.5" bone in pork chop 

Marinade sauce:
<<<SWIPE for 🅡🅔🅒🅘🅟🅔 

𝗦𝘁𝗲𝗽𝘀:
1. Wash and pat dry the meat. Prick with fork and perform quick vacuum marinating using Solis Vacuum Sealer and food container. Let it marinade in fridge for 1 hour after.(You can keep some extra sauce for basting, or simply mix some worcesthershire sauce with honey for basting if you like)
2. Remove from fridge after an hour and let it sit on counter while getting ready to grill.
3. Preheat Ninja Foodi "grill" at 240°C for 15mins.
Set the grill rack on lowest setting and grill for 7 mins. Flip the meat and grill an additional of 5-7minutes or until a thermometer insert in the centre of the meat reads ±65°C. (I added a tomato to grill at this point).
4. Let rest at least 10 minutes (covered) before cutting/serving

👩‍🍳 🆁 𝑴𝒐𝒏𝒌 𝒇𝒓𝒖𝒊𝒕 𝑶𝒔𝒎𝒂𝒏𝒕𝒉𝒖𝒔 𝑫𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒌【罗汉果桂花饮】

A perfect drink after all the cny binge eating and goodies snacking. Also good for current situation to keep away/relieve sore throat and cough!😍

罗汉果 ~ 清热润肺、止咳化痰、润肠的功效。 　　
桂花茶 ~ 益气养血、健脾暖胃、驱风散寒、活血化淤的功效。

Luo Han Guo (罗汉果) or monk fruit is known to many for its cooling benefits. Naturally sweet, it is normally made into a drink as a thirst quencher and also to relieve sore throat and cough, expelling body heat.

I added osmanthus (桂花) for its nice aroma, which is also rich in antioxidant, and have the benefits of optimizing the function of our immune system and further detoxifying the body.

To make this drink, it is as simple as making a cup of black tea. Just boil the 2 ingredients with water, cool and strain. As monk fruit is naturally sweet, no sweetener is required. Of course you can add a bit of honey if you like 😊. 

🅡🅔🅒🅘🅟🅔

𝗜𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀:
1pcs Monk Fruit
1.5-2 tbsp Dried Osmanthus Flower
1.5L water

* adjust ingredients accordingly if cooking more

𝗦𝘁𝗲𝗽𝘀:
1️⃣ Rinse monk fruit under running tap water.
2️⃣ Break up the shell and content of the monk fruit to smaller chunks using hand.
3️⃣ Add the monk fruit chunks and osmanthus flower to a pot of water.
4️⃣ Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer for 15-20minutes.
5️⃣ Done. Cool a bit, strain and and enjoy!

#latelatepost 😜

I don't practice a "must" to have this fish during CNY as the price can be exorbitant during this period for a fish that is actually available throughout the year. It is in high demand during CNY especially in the Teochew community as eating this fish is considered auspicious.

Hubs managed to get some before CNY this year, so I have portioned them and freezed up to be enjoyed slowly (finished long ago btw). Check out the roe (eggs) 😱. For the Teochew, it is normally cooked by steaming with chinese cooking wine and julienned ginger or just simply by poaching in boiling water with ginger slices and spring onions and served with garlic chilli vinegar (蒜泥醋) or tao cho dipping sauce. Flesh is super soft and fine.

The spawning season of rabbit fish peaks from Jan-Feb every year which overlaps the chinese new year, during which the bellies of the fish are filled with roe (eggs) and milt (semen) and are cleaner hence named 拜年鱼.

The rabbit fish is a common food fish found in coastal waters from the western Pacific Ocean to the eastern Indian Ocean  with the best ones believed to be from Kasu Region in Indonesia.

The rabbit fish is also known as 𝒔𝒑𝒊𝒏𝒆𝒇𝒐𝒐𝒕 because of its stiff, sharp dorsal and pelvic spines which are venomous (though not life threatening to humans except for a painful sting).

Piu M: Simple Home-style Japanese Italian Cooking 

8️⃣ Snow Crab A.O.P. Pasta 

This is another pasta which I really enjoy here. Jun-san shared that the secret to this pasta is the lobster broth which he uses as a base! Snow crab legs and cherry tomatoes are then added to give the pasta that additional sweetness. Honestly, I have no other comments apart from saying that this was pretty damn delicious!

Piu M: Simple Home-style Japanese Italian Cooking 

7️⃣ Uni and Bottarga Pasta 

This pasta is actually jun-san’s signature pasta which is very popular. Interestingly, jun-san cooks his pasta in a dashi broth rather than the usual water with salt which I think is a rather clever trick to give the pasta that extra flavor! He then tosses the pasta with lots of fresh sashimi-grade uni from Japan until the uni is infused into the sauce. He then tops the pasta with some bottarga, a cured fish roe, which is a really nice touch! Having tried different renditions of uni pastas from other restaurants, I have to say this version served by jun-san is my personal favorite!

Piu M: Simple Home-style Japanese Italian Cooking 

6️⃣ Iberico Pork Seafood Stew 

This was a really interesting dish which I have not actually seen elsewhere. Jun-san manages to sear the iberico pork such that it is slightly pink and superbly tender. The pork is then stewed in a buttery seafood broth which gets its sweetness from the generous amounts of clams and cherry tomatoes. Essentially the pork absorbs some of that tasty broth which makes it a real delight!

5️⃣ Hokkaido Corn Tempura with Parmesan Cheese 

Sometimes, Jun-san creates dishes based on what’s good in the season. During my visit, corn from Hokkaido was in season. .
I visited back when it was still 1-for-1 on @burpple & rn it’s 30% off the bill which is still rlly worth it plus prices are alr nett !! A no-nonsense solid brunch spot imo that proves sometimes simplicity is all you need 👍

The Corner Grill
.
Walked past this countless times as it is literally found at the first corner of Ann Siang Hill. Easy to miss if you never knew they were here as their main seating area is on the 2nd floor hidden from the street view ✨ The interior gave a very rustic & cozy feel & the service was amazing! Consider this for your next date night spot if you’re looking for somewhere quieter & more intimate 👏🏻
.
Lobster Roll ($32.00++)
With herbed pommery mayo on a grilled brioche roll. It’s hard to not shell out a fortune for a quality 🦞 roll & feel the guilt of your wallet screaming @ u 😔 so I was glad there was plump chunks of lobster in this for the price compared to other places! The side of lemon capers potatoes 🥔 also deserved the spotlight equally with its addictive sweet / salty / savoury combination. Brioche roll could have been more buttered & crisp tho 
.
Portobello Burger ($25.00++)
Raclette cheese, beef patty, creamed portobello, bacon, romaine lettuce & herbed mayo on a sesame bun. Also served with fries.
.
Truffled Mac & Cheese ($12.00++, small)
Parmesan, mature cheddar, gorgonzola. The very kind waitress cautioned us that the cheeses in this were very strong but strongly recommended it for the 🧀 lovers! I’m personally not a big fan of strong cheeses but I can see why cheese addicts would love this 🥺 The blue cheese is super intense & served piping hot, completely melted into a gooey glorious mess of comfort mac n cheese.
.
Harmony Twist ($16.00++)
Their house special of vodka, limoncello, simple syrup & freshly squeezed lemon juice.
.
Citrus Smasher ($12.00++)
Veltins “0%”, lemon, lime & orange juice.
.
Pro-tip to purchase the discount vouchers on @chopesg for 30% off!! Super worth it 🥰

.

Vodka, bacon, bird’s eye chilli, crushed tomatoes, cream & parmigiano. I chose the pumpkin 🎃 rigatoni for my pasta & loved how their rigatoni is longer than usual - providing the sufficient surface area to really soak up all that creamy rich yet not too gelat sauce 🥰 Bacon bits were sufficient & adequate heat from the 🌶  Defo recommend this combination!

Secret pepper mix, parmigiano, pecorino cheese & truffle oil. Note that the pasta choice for this is fixed! We weren’t the biggest fans of this as the flavours all felt very one-dimensional but mayb we just can’t appreciate the purposeful simplicity of this 🤣

Mezcla

Japanese-Mexican taco 🌮 bar from the folks behind @thefeatherblade & @rappu.sg 
.
Unagi ($9.50++ for 1)
Seaweed taco, unagi, oyako tamago, Japanese cucumber, chipotle teriyaki. I loved the char on the unagi & found the accompaniment of the oyako tamago 🥚 to be a very good addition providing a lil extra sweetness to the savoury taco ✨ But for $9.50… I could have finished it in one bite… it’s good but not $9.50 per taco good 😔

Crab ($11.50++ for 1)
Seaweed taco, tempura soft shell crab, tobiko, edamame refritos, spiced mayo, pico de gallo. A personal huge fan of soft shell crab 🦀 & it was fried well such that it retained its juiciness & flavour well. Loved the spicy kick from the wasabi too 😎 But again… I found myself trying to justifying the $11.50 price tag for something that could have been finished in a single bite. Flight of 3 ($16.00++)

200g of feather blade steak with smoked salt. Was cooked to a nice medium rare & tender! 🐄 However, I did find it slightly on the bland side & had to sprinkle some extra salt on there for some boost of flavour

Cheese Muffins 🧀

Made this super easy and quick cheese muffin 😊 No mixer needed just mix everything in a bowl.
They are soft, moist, yum with cheese cubes inside 🧀🧀

Yield 10 muffins
Ingredients:
2 eggs
200g icing sugar
275g all purpose flour
2 tbsp milk powder
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
125g butter, melted
75g vegetable oil
90g milk
1tsp vanilla extract
100g cheddar cheese, cut into cubes
Grated cheese for topping

Directions:
1. In a bowl combine all purpose flour, milk powder, baking powder and baking soda together. Set aside. 
2. Whisk eggs and powder sugar together until fluffy about 5 minutes. 
3. Add in the dry ingredients, melted butter, vegetable oil, milk, and vanilla extract. Mix until combined. Don't overmix. 
4. Add in cheese cubes. Mix until combined
5. Portion into muffin cups. Add grated cheese on top. 
6. Bake at 170°C for 25 to 30 minutes

Dinner this evening, was a plate of 猪脚米粉, or Braised Pork Trotter with Rice Vermicelli, a nostalgic dish of tinned Braised Pork Trotter cooked with rice vermicelli, usually cooked at home by the older generation of Hokkiens in Singapore. It is a dish that is moist, tasty, sticky with collagen, and greasy with fat from the braised pork, and added lard. Today’s version was missing the usual “healthy” sprigs of Chye Sim, or Mustard Greens, but the crisp bean sprouts were there to jazz up the texture. Optional condiments of Calamansi Lime and a savoury chilli paste add to the complex flavours of the dish, elevating it to a higher level. Delicious! 😋 #猪脚米粉 #porktrotterbeehoon #hokkienfood #hokkiencuisine #traditionalfood #sgfood #sghawkerfood #sghawkerculture #ourhawkerculture #adamroadfoodcentre

Amazing treats💘

@sy_bakessg for these delicious treats that use less sugar & are customisable too. I love their Earl grey chiffon cake which uses TWG tea leaves😘 It’s a healthier version that isn't as sinful as conventional ones. I love how soft and fragrant the cake is! They use Melaleuca grape seed oil and you can get a satisfying cake (12 cm in diameter) at $9.90

Craving for a asian delightful treat? Their chinese steamed sponge cake is so fragrant, soft and springy. Best consumed within 2-3days! It’s also fluffy and not-so-sweet tasting 😋When what you consume is homemade without preservatives and with less sugar, it’s the perfect chance to indulge in healthy, satisfying and guilt free food. The combination of Gula melaka and brown sugar is stellar.

Their ma lai gaos come in sizes of around 650g, perfect for a family of 4 to 6. Share this with your loved ones! [MA LAI GAO] $15 around 650grams😙

Indoor Pottery Studio & Vegetarian Café🌹

@amiaddicted.sg is located near City Hall Mrt and inside Capitol mall. It’s a full-service pottery studio along with a Korean vegetarian cafe, making it the perfect spot to spend your weekend in🤤 

🤗They continually source clay from South Korean makers, making them the only studio to provide high quality Korean clay to local potters in the Singaporean scene

From healthy nibbles to nutrition-packed mains, Am I Addicted’s vegetarian menu is made delicious with signature Korean-western fusion cuisine that adds unique, punchy flavours to plant-based dishes for that guilt-free and healthy dining experience😘

I love their Doenjang Truffle Risotto  and Ginseng smoothie from @amiaddicted.sg so much😋🌱Glad to have a Korean vegetarian cafe that serves delicious and creative dishes😌

Doenjang Truffle Risotto is so fragrant and the meal is surprisingly filling! They use Barley rice as a healthier replacement for carbs. Each bite has a burst of flavor from doenjang, sweet dashi stock, and creamy mushrooms. Having truffle fragrance with every bite is the most enjoyable part for me⭐️ 

For their Ginseng smoothie, there’s oat milk, healthier substitute of sugar and ginseng root which is grinded so the flavor is very prominent. Definitely one of the best smoothies that I had tried so far.

Salad Dressings, BBQ sauces & marinades

Loving the yummy dressings from @vrescano.cafe26sg as they add so much flavor to my homecooked food. They are the sole distributor of cafe26 products🥦in Singapore!

Their sauces are low fat, contain no artificial preservatives & colourings💘Love that the salad dressings are so versatile and can be incorporated in many dishes!  

🥬Cafe26 Original Salad Dressing is my favourite as it tastes so refreshing. I don’t usually pair my food with mustard as it can be quite strong. But this dressing isn’t too overpowering

🍋Cafe26 Tangy Salad Dressing has an extra zesty tang that brings any boring salad to life. It’s sour and citrus notes are very addictive

 🧀Cafe26 Caesar Salad Dressing🐟 makes the perfect caesar salad with notes of parmesan cheese and anchovies. It’s so unique and isn’t too heavy in flavor.

😘BBQ marinate is great for your meat. I usually marinate chicken thigh/drumstick in paprika and garlic powder. Then add some BBQ marinate to make it extra flavorful. It isn’t too sweet

.
Recipe:
.
. preheat oven top/bottom 160c
- A
- 380g mashed ripe bananas 
- 170g melted butter/oil
- 300g self raising flour
- 1/2 tsp baking soda
- 1 tsp baking powder
- pinch of salt
- combined all the above and set aside
.
.
B
- 5 large eggs 
-200g sugar
- beat the eggs & sugar till pale white, till tripe the volume.
.
.
Fold B batter into A into 3 batches. Bake for 1 hour. Your oven might vary on baking time.
.
.

My fav recipe of moist banana loaf
#brownsugar #bananaloaf
.
.
Recipe:
- 3 medium large ripe banana (mashed with fork)
- 125g butter (melted)
- 140g brown sugar (adjust according to banana’s sweetness)
-2 large eggs (grade A)
- a pinch of salt
.
.
-180g all purpose flour
- 1 tsp baking soda Or 3 tsp baking powder.
.
.
Mix and whisk all wet ingredient till all combined. Sifting the dried ingredient flour and baking powder. Fold till all incorporated. Bake for 45 mins at 160c or till brown.
.

Li Yuan - Japanese Fusion Mee Pok
Blk 511 Hougang Ave 10

After hearing my sister and niece raved about it, my friend just had to post a photo of it as well. The temptation was a little too big to resist. I finally managed to try it. Naturally, I had to try the fusion version first. I opted for the Miso version rather than the Shoyu version. A timer was used to monitor the cooking time for the noodles. Just before it was served, a spoonful of what looks like lard was added. It wasn’t all lard, more like crispy bits of fritters. So the bowl came with Japanese Char Siew and that was pretty good. There was an overload of ingredients that I could hardly focus on the noodles. The soup had a unique taste which is pretty nice but nothing like a good old bowl of minced pork soup laden with lard. Overall, a very good Mee Pok and I shall be back to try the traditional version. 

#meepok #foodreview #charsiew #fusion #fusionmeepok

Hor Fun King - Asia Square Food Court

Portion is huge and I am a big eater. Overall, it was pretty good, crispy hor fun may attract youngsters but for me, I want the burnt hor fun. For the place and what is being served, I think it’s still okay. It definitely does not compared to the best hor fun around but I think it’s still worth checking out. Give them a try and see if you like it. Be prepared to pay a little more for the experience.

Sake Karashi Don

Checked out the new Shin Yuu Yakitori and Donburi, which is opened by the same folks behind Shin Yuu Japanese Restaurant at Greenwood Avenue that serves an ala-carte Japanese buffet — their latest outlet, which is located at Royal Square @ Novena (just beside Novena Square) focuses on Yakitori, Sushi, Sashimi and Donburi offerings — all of which being rather decently priced with the Donburi costing in the range of $12.90 to $29.90 depending on the item; the most expensive being the Uni Kaisendon.

Opted for the Sake Karashi Don, which was one of the more affordably priced items at $13.90; essentially a Donburi which features salmon sashimi slices that comes with a spicy sauce that is similar to that found of the spicy salmon in Omote’s Salmon Sanshoku Don. Here, the Don comes with wasabi and pickled ginger, and the salmon does come sprinkled with Japanese chili powder as well. Overall, the Sake Karashi Don was pretty satisfying and hit all the right spots; the salmon used was fresh with the slices of sashimi being of equal sizes — the spicy sauce was peppery, yet carried just enough spice to tickle the taste buds without being too fiery. The level of spiciness is pretty manageable, considering how they have only used it as a sauce here in comparison to how Omote seemingly using it as a marinade — should be pretty fine even for those with lower tolerance to spiciness in general. The pearly, short-grain rice came at room temperature; slightly sweetened, we also enjoyed how the rice came at a decent temperature that didn’t create a stark contrast against that of the raw fish. It is also interesting to note how they had included crispy bits of fried tempura batter above the fish; really liked how that created a light crunchy texture that just made the entire bowl so interesting to have. Personally felt that the wasabi wasn’t of much use considering how the salmon was already flavoured from the spicy sauce, though it does provide quite a numbing kick that tickles the taste buds.

Homemade Kaya Butter Toast & Eggs

Have seen quite a fair bit about the new Babba which had opened their doors at 15-9 Jalan Riang recently — this is the latest venture by the same folks behind The Brewing Ground, which is located within The Yards (former site of Telok Kurau Primary School). The place sports a similar decor theme as The Brewing Ground — a rather clean interior decor that comes with a slight Balinese vibe with furnishing and fittings that features concrete, rattan and wooden elements. Serving up two different menus for breakfast/lunch and dinner service, Babba has rolled out its breakfast/lunch menu at the time of the writing of this post — dubbed “The Little Baba”, the breakfast/lunch menu features brunch dishes with a Peranakan influence. Dinner service will be launched on a later date; named the “Big Babba”, the dinner menu will feature “authentic traditional Peranakan fare” in a communal format that works for sharing across the table.

The breakfast/lunch menu is available from 8am to 4pm; split into several sections ranging from “breakfast” and “lunch”, to “salads”, “sides to share” and “dessert”, the Homemade Kaya Butter Toast & Eggs is from the “breakfast” section of the menu. Featuring elements such as brioche, house-made Kaya and French butter, the Homemade Kaya Butter Toast & Eggs is essentially a spruced up version of the local favourite breakfast — something that I will absolutely fall for.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets

Visited the East Coast Road outlet of the favourite place over the weekend instead of the Guillemard Road one since we were wanting to check out another spot around Marine Parade — pretty much a coincidence given how the folks behind Brawn & Brains had also introduced yet another new item on the menu; the Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets.

Being part of the “Munchies” section of the menu, the Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets is one of those items that could be shared at the table. A great vegetarian alternative to the Crispy Karaage Chicken with Side of Sriracha Dip, the Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets is pretty much almost the same here — cauliflower florets with a golden brown, deep-fried batter that is sprinkled with chili powder for a subtle hint of spiciness that lingers at the taste buds. Whilst the batter for the Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets doesn’t come with the bits of quinoa that gives their Crispy Karaage Chicken with Side of Sriracha Dip that extra crunch, we liked how crisp the batter was without being particularly greasy, while the cauliflower gives a soft crunch. Just like the Crispy Karaage Chicken with Side of Sriracha Dip though, they do offer a wedge of lime for a zesty touch if you do prefer it that way, though rather than to come with a sriracha dip, the Crispy Cauliflower Drumlets came with a creamy and light aioli that matches the more neutral flavours of the cauliflower here — a pretty thoughtful touch. Guess I now know what to order as an accompaniment to the BBFC (BB Crispy Fried Chicken) next time!

Kakuni Don

Much had been said about Itchy Bun before it’s official launch — whilst they were supposed to have opened their doors on 22 February 2022 initially, they had finally officially done so a day after due to “unforeseen circumstances” as stated in their social media account. For those whom are not in the know, Itchy Bun is an establishment located at Prinsep Street (several doors away from Mama Diam) brought by the folks behind Fook Kin (also by the same people behind Roast Paradise) and also The Muttons from Class 95FM. Being more of an Izakaya-style establishment, the menu offers fry buckets (i.e. beer bites), Zensai, Rice Bowls, Itchy Buns (i.e Mantou Sliders) and sides. Beverages available include beer, sake and non-alcoholic options such as canned drinks — pretty much in line with the other establishments around the area. 

While we were pretty intrigued by the Itchy Buns that they have to offer initially as they seem to be the signature offerings here, but we found ourselves going for the Kakuni Don for something more substantial since we were here for lunch on a workday in office (which is pretty much a stone’s throw away from us). Ain’t a fan of Foie Gras, hence steered away from the Subarashi Don which is pretty much the full works, and instead opted for the Kakuni Don. While the portions may be a bit on the smaller side for some, the Kakuni Don is actually pretty affordably priced at $8.80+. Coming with elements such as a sous-vide egg, Ebiko, Furikake, Japanese pickles, braised pork belly and seaweed, the Kakuni Don was pretty comforting and well-executed for its price — the braised pork belly was especially delicious having absorbed all the flavours from the braising liquid; all savoury without being too heavy-handed in flavour, while not carrying undesirable porky stench. Texturally, it was a great balance between the gelatinous fatty parts and the leaner parts; soft, tender and juicy, yet carrying a good bite for the best of both worlds.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Passionfruit Meringue Tart

Heard all about the new K. Patisserie at Onze; the same building which also houses DESEM Bakery and Sugar & Tease, as well as the ever-popular Beef Sukiyaki Don Keisuke which always sees a queue during the hours that they are open. K. Patisserie is situated within the mall, tucked in a corner not too far from where DESEM Bakery and Sugar & Tease are located. The cafe is pretty moderately-sized, with a small counter facing the patrons on the left displaying the cakes and bakes available for the day upon entry; the space being decked in a pastel pink and white colour scheme with splashes of gold for the furniture and fittings. Being a patisserie, expect a variety of cakes and bakes available here; drinks available includes specialty coffee, tea, as well as a small list of non-caffeinated options such as Chocolate and Mineral Water. 

Between the two items that we had, the one that actually set a better impression would be the Passionfruit Meringue Tart. It is the more well-executed one — priced at $8, it is decently sized; what we really enjoyed here is the biscuit-like tart base which crumbles quite neatly as one slices through it. The tart base also holds the passionfruit curd within pretty well; all that while the passionfruit curd remains zingy and tangy. The meringue was actually done pretty well here; fluffy and light whilst being slightly torched without being overly sweet — cuts through the zippy notes for a good balance of flavours. Overall, a pretty satisfying dessert for those looking for something a little sour to refresh the taste buds.

<continuation of caption in the comments section below>

Yakiniku-GO turned 1️⃣ on 9 Feb 2022 but they decided to celebrate their 1st anniversary today with this special ONE day promo with a 50% OFF Yakiniku-GO Set (100g + Full steak)! 😱😋

Oh boy… how could I not be there and join in the fun? 😂🤪
I waited slightly over half an hour as there were quite a lot of people waiting to dine in given this awesome promo!
 This signature Yakiniku-GO Set consists of 3 popular cuts of beef with a bowl of rice, soup and a side (a choice of kimchi, radish kimchi or mini salad).

The 3️⃣ popular cuts of beef are:

~ Angus Ribeye Steak
~ Karubi (Beef Short Plate) 
~ Gyutan (Beef Tongue)

I loved all 3 cuts of beef.
The Angus Ribeye Steak has a great balance between lean meat and fat with beautiful marbling. 
I cooked mine to medium rare so they were still tender and juicy with that rich meaty bite and a hint of smokiness from the grill. Tasted so good! 😋😍

The Karubi is fatty and has more marbling and this cut is rich in flavour and is characterised by slight sweetness.
I grilled this to medium and loved this on its own without dip for its natural flavour. So heavenly! 🤩👍

I also liked Gyutan although it is more of an acquired taste and slightly more chewy with meaty rich taste. 🥰

A tip on how best to grill Gyutan from a pro that I learnt recently too.
As Gyutan is sliced very thinly and cooks fast, as soon as the meat starts to curl, we have to flip it over quickly. 
Best to grill one side of gyutan well while leaving the other side a bit rarer to best enjoy Gyutan. 

There are 2️⃣ sauces provided for this set:

~ Negi Shio Tare
~ Miso Tare

The Angus Ribeye Steak and Karubi paired well with the Miso Tare.
I highly recommend to dip the Gyutan into the slight-tangy citrusy Negi Shio Tare.

I had a wonderful dinner and made even more sweet with such an awesome deal! 
I’ll definitely be back again to try out more of their meat selections. 
Their prices are really affordable too.

Happy birthday, Yakiniku-GO! 🎉🥳
Happy Twosday to all!

Inaniwa udon is a variety of udon noodles that are thinner and smoother than other types and they are made by hand in the Inaniwa area of Akita prefecture. @misosalmon imports them directly from Japan. 

𝗙𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲
While miso salmon serves up mean inaniwa noodles, also worth trying is their side dishes (Truffle Edamame $7, Aburi Mentai Tamagoyaki $6, Chicken Karaage with Parmesan Cheese $7) and Yakitori Chicken with Truffle Mushroom Don $15!

Those on a low carbs diet can try their Shirataki noodles. Other dishes tried include their Fish Collagen Miso Udon soup ($17) which was light and the Tiger Prawn with Mentaiko Bowl ($19) which is dry version but quite creamy. 

You can also choose to build your own bowl!

𝗔𝗺𝗯𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲
Casual Japanese diner suitable for catch up with friends, family over a hot bowl of delicious udon and more. Actually, I think their sides will go very well with beer too. 

Thanks @sociallyconnectedsg @exclusive_media_communications @misskueh_elizabeth for the invite and @miso.salmon for having us!

Still working from home and too busy to cook? @tingkat.richfood delivers freshly made meals with NO MSG added, straight to your doorsteps! 💫

Their menu for lunch and dinner everyday is different. Below is a list of dishes tried. Overall, I feel that there is a good balance of flavours across their menu for the day e.g. salty, sour, sweet and savoury.

- Fish maw and cabbage with sliced pork soup: very fresh, flavourful soup and the sliced pork was tender. Must try ✅✅✅ No MSG, I finished every drop of food. 

- Pork Chop: Seasoning is good, pork was tender ✅✅

- Fish fillet with Orange Sauce: I like that it wasn't too oily or tough for the batter but some might find it soggy. You can't really see the sauce so it's not your usual sweet and sour sauce type but I can taste a hint of orange. Fish meat is tender. ✅✅

- Stir fry Cabbage with Black Fungus: crunchy cabbage, lightly seasoned ✅

Their options are (min 2pax):
• 5 days trial for first-time (lunch or dinner) - starting from $62.50 
• 10 days (lunch or dinner)
• 20 days (lunch or dinner)
• Deliveries only Mon - Fri excl PH

Meal Options:
• 1 Soup + 3 Dishes (No Rice/White Rice/Brown Rice) or
• 4 Dishes (No Rice/White Rice/Brown Rice)

Book now at www.tingkatdelivery.com

Pretty hearty food, can give them a try if you're interested!

This is the first time I'm served lobster bisque for a high tea session and I got to say that it was pretty good! 😋

𝗡𝗼𝘁𝗲: Tried my best to list down the items as they seem to differ from the menu. It was also the first time at a high tea sess that the servers did not explain what each item was. When asked, she was unsure and needed to check with the chef, twice. 

𝗙𝗼𝗼𝗱 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲
Launch price of ~$40++ for one set of high tea that comes with either free flow coffee or tea (we were able to switch coffee to tea later on.) Note: now might be higher at $69++, suitable for 2pax (according to the website)

Overall, we prefer the sweets much more than the savoury. See below for a peek into what was served. 

𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗲𝗿𝘀
✅✅✅Lobster Bisque: rich and creamy, does not have an overwhelmingly fishy taste, absolutely delicious!
- Selection of Scones with clotted cream and jam: was floury and rubbery. We did not finish any.
- Quiche

𝗦𝗮𝘃𝗼𝘂𝗿𝘆
- Smoked Salmon, Apricot, Cream Cheese Roll 
- Boston Lobster Sandwich, fish roe
- Salmon terrine, apricot, honey walnut cracker
- Prosciutto, smoked bacon, cream cone
Seems like they have issues with their flour based items: sandwich, terrine and cone all did not meet expectations e.g. cannot finish cause not nice. 

𝗦𝘄𝗲𝗲𝘁𝘀
✅✅Yuzu Grapefruit Meringue Tart: Love this! but honestly, it tasted more like lemon, I don't taste the yuzu nor the grapefruit. Nailed that meringue texture. 
- Olive Basil Chocolate Cake: It is an interesting combination but not something I will order
✅ Pumpkin Gateau de Voyage: great texture, not too sweet
✅✅ Pesto Pine Nut Gateau de voyage
✅✅ Green Tea Peach Jelly: no peach jelly, seems like green tea chocolate? It's not bad. 

𝗗𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘁𝘀
Soft Serve: Not creamy, kinda icy and tasteless.... didn't finish it. 

Overall, if you really want to try, just order one set which will cost you about $35++ each. 

📍Beach Road Kitchen

💵: $$

I haven't done a count of how many fish ball noodle stalls (and Bak Chor Mee stalls) there are in Toa Payoh but I know Toa Payoh residents are spoilt for choice. 
🍜
Song Kee Fish Ball Noodles' flagship outlet is at Yio Chu Kang. Thankfully for me, they opened a branch  at Lorong 5 Toa Payoh in March this year.

Their Hee Keow (fish dumpling) is seriously shiok - handmade, with a generous amount of fish meat. The texture was not too gooey.  The noodles were just a touch on the soggy side (those who like their noodles eggy will enjoy this). Chilli packed a punch. Was served by the elder brother today. Super friendly. 🍜
There wasn't a crowd at 8am and the cool morning breeze made for a perfect breakfast.
🍜

description:
Continuing on with the tour of Pek Kio Market & Food Centre
🥕
Good Spice Carrot Cake always sees a long queue at weekends. Head there early (they start at 6am). The carrot "cake" is soft  and wobbly and is not fried flat or crispy like  some other stalls.  I only had stomach space for the white version. Old school, comforting, shiok! Chilli good too.
🥕
Trivia : the "carrot" isn't the carrot as we know it. It is white radish. It is shredded, mixed with rice flour and steamed. The "cake" is then ready to be used to make Carrot Cake aka known locally as Chye Tow Kway. Estee in Sweden has a clear video on how to make the "cake"  on her You Tube Channel (no I don't know her, just sharing)
🥕
Closed Tuesdays & Wednesdays
Opens at 6am
$2.00 / $3.00
🥕
#foodie #sgfoodie #hawkerculture #hawkersg #pekkiomarket #singaporefoodie #breakfast #eatsg #sgeats #food #heritagefood #streetfood #carrotcake #mysingapore #shiok #sgfoodies

Pek Kio Market is home to several great hawker stalls including 2 stalls selling Prawn Noodles.  The more popular one would be Wah Kee Big Prawn Noodle located in the centre block of the hawker centre.  However if one walks to the last row of hawker stalls you will find, at the corner, a queue at Lai Hiang.  Helmed by a friendly lady I got my bowl of noodles after a 10 minute wait in the queue.  Go early because the queue seems to get longer as the morning progresses (this was a thursday). A nice bowl of noodles for $3.00. The chilli was shiok and soup was not too rich. A nice balance of pork and Prawn broth.
🦐
I suppose I should have braved Wah Kee (even though there was no queue) but I was pretty full. Next week perhaps. Lai Hiang is closed on tuesdays and fridays.
🦐

[Dewgather Cafe] Words can't describe HUMMUS I miss you! How has everyone been? Took a break from mama duties to do breakfast! @dewgather coffee house is the closest I get to aussie style food for now. Being a glass roof cafe located in Star Vista, the vibes of the cafe is calm and lovely! Swipe to see the interior! We had Hummus in the Pan ($15) , in which the poached egg, crispy chickpeas, Gascony butter, tabouli salsa, Turkish bread makes it a nutritious and yummy breakfast. Will be back to try more! 

Do note that this is a non veg establishment serving veg options.

🍽 Dewgather The Star Vista, 1 Vista Exchange Green #01-46, Singapore 138617

[Splendip.sg] Words can't express HUMMUS I miss eating this! Chanced upon @splendip.sg ’s National Day collaboration with @soudo.sg and they are so kind to do an alliums free version for me. The #vegan dips are fresh, well seasoned with nuts and herbs and most importantly goes well with @soudo.sg #sourdough breads! 

🔸Beetroot Hummus
Creamy and flavourful hot pink dip that goes perfect with multigrain sourdough

🔸Japanese Sweet Potato Hummus
Healthy and hearty dip which is rich in fibre and vitamins, I could inhale this dip on its own. 

🔸Avocado Hummus 
Smooth and creamy, I love the tint of spices and this goes well with the cheesy soudough!

This homemade bundle is really wholesome and I will order again from them next round!

[Zi Zai] Happy Long Weekend everyone! With the dine in restrictions lifted soon, what will be the food you will be having while dining in? For me, it will be prata! Throwback to the food we have at Zi Zai branch.

Zi Zai Vegetarian has an extensive menu that offers a wide variety of food. We had

🔸Murtabak Prata 印度馅料煎饼
Filled with vegetables like cabbage & mushrooms, this goes well with their house made curry

🔸Nasi Briyani 黄姜饭
This traditional Indian rice-based dish accompanied by monkey head mushrooms, vegetables and housemate gravy with papadum! We love how well marinated the mushrooms are! 

Aside from these, I love their Veg prawn noodles too! Jalan Mas Puteh’s outlet has veg black pepper steak that scores good reviews too!

For online orders: http://zzv.com.sg/

🍽Address: 
Zi Zai Vegetarian @ Jalan Mas Puteh
9 Jalan Mas Puteh, 128615, Singapore
69095696

[Summerlab] I am the luckiest girl to received these mini-flower pots/succulents from @wishuponatart from @summerlab! A #vegan friendly concept store, this superfood smoothie açai bowls are to pretty to be eaten! Featuring the bowls in order of preference

Tropicana ($8.90)
Mango flowers with granola and blueberries with a base of more mango, banana, passionfruit and chia pudding. I find this combo refreshing! The granola adds crunch to the cup 

Daisy Joy ($8.90)
The base of this contains a blend of banana and red pitaya with fruits and granola on top. Its a joy to see the daisy flowers as toppings.

Was scrolling through my photo album and realised that I haven’t posted this meal that I had at @yardbirdsingapore last year. 😅
•
Lobster Mac & Cheese ($64): We decided to go big or go home, so we ordered this! This is the most decadent version of m&c I’ve had so far - whole lobster laying on a bed of elbow macaroni tossed in a 5-cheese sauce! The taste was exactly what we expected it to be - the lobster meat was fresh, sweet and succulent, while the m&c was rich and creamy (although it got a little jelak midway through)!
•
Chicken ‘N’ Watermelon ‘N’ Waffles ($40): This is their most popular dish that almost everyone orders here - fried chicken served with cheddar cheese waffles and spiced watermelon. The chicken overall was well-seasoned, moist and tender! Even the breast part (which I’m usually not a fan of) wasn’t dry at all! Love the spiced watermelon too, which was a nice food chaser containing some heat from the spices. The waffles weren’t that memorable though, nothing much to shout about.
•
We also ordered the Crab Cake ($23) to share as a side dish - it came generously filled with lump crab, served with creole beurre blanc sauce. It had a nice seafood-y taste, and went really well with the buttery sauce, but we felt that it was slightly pricey for the portion.
•

Visited @indulgence_by_roxey, a newly opened cafe in Telok Kurau a couple of weeks back. The cafe has a really nice interior (especially on the 2nd floor), and the food is pretty good overall too! Here’s what we had:
•
~Blue Surf Pizza: This was our first time seeing blue pizza, and we weren’t sure what to expect! To our pleasant surprise, this was delicious! It’s a pizza naturally coloured with butterfly pea flower, topped with shrimps, honey baked ham, pineapple and mozzarella. The dough had a nice bite to it, and the toppings went harmoniously well together!
•
~Chilli Crab Shakshuka: This was really yummy! The shakshuka itself is already pretty indulgent, but the eggs added even more richness to the dish! And it went so well with the buttered toast too!
•
~Azzuro Aglio Olio: Similar to the pizza, it was our first time seeing blue pasta too! This is a handmade butterfly pea flower pappardelle pasta served with shrimps, garlic and chilli flakes. The pasta was al-dente, and not overwhelmingly garlicky, but overall we felt it was a little under-seasoned.
•
~The Orient: This is a platter that includes a combination of pan-fried Asian style dumplings with shrimp & pork filling, and Braised Korean pork belly (bossam) & Indonesian style roasted pork belly served with kimchi and achar. My favourite dish in this platter is the bossam, which was really tender. Loved the tangy kimchi too!
•
We paired these dishes with some of their refreshing alcoholic drinks like Pina Colada, Strawberry Daiquiri and Oppa Saranghaeyo (watermelon soju bomb) too! We feel this is a worthwhile cafe to visit if you’re in the east of Singapore, for its ambiance and food, or if you wanna chill with friends or colleagues for some drinks after work as well!
•
▶️Indulgence by Roxey
📍#01-218, Bright Centre, 212 Telok Kurau Rd, Singapore 423835
⏰Tues to Sun: 9am to 9pm

Checked out @kahuna.acai, a new açai kiosk located at @amk_hub recently. There are a total of 5 options (Kahuna, Mahalo, Aloha, Maui & Waikiki) of açai bowls to choose from here, and each bowl comes with your choice of homemade granola (The OG, Black Forest, Speculoos, Chai-Spiced, Hawaiian Sunrise) and drizzle (Almond Butter, Cashew Butter, Maple Cinnamon Butter, Oatmeal Raisin Butter, Chai-Spiced Almond Butter).
•
We tried the Kahuna (cover pic, left) and Mahalo (cover pic, right) - the former is an earl grey infused açai, with fresh fruits, Black Forest granola, almonds, coconut flakes & Cashew Butter drizzle, while the latter is a cacao açai, with bananas, strawberries, The OG granola, almonds, cacao nibs & Oatmeal Raisin Butter drizzle. Both appealed to me in different ways - the Kahuna was light and refreshing with a nice subtle fragrance from the earl grey, while the Mahalo had a heavier, more earthy taste that grew on me after a few mouthfuls!
•
You can purchase their homemade granola and nut butters in stores too! 3rd pic onwards are from @sixthsensepr & @kahuna.acai.

Thank you @nanacurryrestaurant for sending over the food last night! 

Tried out several of their signature dishes which includes;
Curry Fishhead $28.90 🐟
👉🏻 Having tried out their Fishhead curry which have certainly won my heart over when i dined in in their Thompson Branch sometime back! 

👉🏻 Really loved how the standards still remained the same, and actually even better! The curry gravy was thick enough, and you can taste the fragrance of the curry and thankfully there wasnt a strong coconut taste unlike some curries i have tried (which i prefer). 

👉🏻 If you love spicy food, you will certainly love this curry, they include a generous amount of fish head and meat with seasonal vegetables such as lady fingers, tomatoes and potatoes. 

🍲 Chye Poh Tofu $9.90
Tofu was pretty smooth and silky paired with lovely bits of Chye poh and minced meat on top of the tofu. 
Certainly very delectable and a crowd favourite among my family as they are tofu lovers! 

🧆 Snow White Pork $10.90
Loved how the pork was beautifully seasoned with cereal bits, and you can taste the fragrance of the curry leaves embedded in the snow white pork 

Fried Rice Paradise $7.90 🥘
👉🏻 portion was actually very huge (at least for 2-3 pax) with generous portions of shrimps

Thank you @mummyyong.cafe for sending over such delicious homecooked food. They are a newly opened home based business who specialised in local traditional dishes.👍🏻

Gluntinous Rice, Abacus Seed are rare to find in market/hawker centres these days, not to mentioned good ones. If you have family members/ friends who really love these traditional dishes, I  𝙨𝙩𝙧𝙤𝙣𝙜𝙡𝙮 𝙧𝙚𝙘𝙤𝙢𝙢𝙚𝙣𝙙 yall to order and try🙌🏻 They are very generous with their ingredients as well, lots of mushroom, meat and shrimp. The glutinous rice and yam for the abacus seed is well seasoned and flavourful. Their Yong Tau Foo is also filled with huge peice of meat and the ratio is just nice. Cant wait to order and try their other dishes as well.😍😋✨

Also, i really love their packaging. Very oriental and their stickers are good wishes in Chinese. ✨DM @mummyyong.cafe or Whatsapp 94229947 to order. Swipe all the way to the right for their menu.✨
A must have snack while watching Netflix!!! Crispy and mild spicy from the mala. Hopefully they will come up with new flavours soon😋😋✌🏻👍🏻
Breakfast from @huajibaodang !!✌🏻

Thank you friends for sending this over. Amazing tart and cruffin, huge variety of flavours! The tart base aka the crust is very crumbly and i love the cream. The cruffin is flaky and the filling just oozes out once you cut it apart. Truly quality desserts/ pastries  which are perfect as gifts.

The flavours for the tart were:
- Orh Blanc
- Lemon Meringue
-Bourdaloue
-Passion Sesame
-Cherry Crumble
-Cognac Caramel Chocolate
-Chocolate Banana
-Strawberry and Vanilla

[HazelBakezel Banana Bread]
Banana Bread TRY 6 #hazelbakezelbananabread journey

In search of the BEST BANANA bread, this is my 6th try

TRY6: Sourdough discard Banana bread with walnuts (another SD discard recipe) naturally sweetened with no sugar added

▪️Texture
Tight close crumb that is super moist, more towards a cakey texture. Moist with mid-high denseness yet really soft and cakey; with a good chew texture.
-Bready level: 1.25/5
-Cakey level: 3.75/5
-Fluffyness: 3.75/5
-Softness: 3.75/5
-Spongy-ness: 3.5/5
-Dense-stickyness: 3.5/5
-Moist-ness: 4.5/5

▪️Flavour
Distinct and strong banana profile, not too sweet; taste like naturally sweetened
-🍌 meter: 4/5
-Sweetness level: 0.5/5 (very natural)

Quite like how this loaf has this velvety melty chewy texture 🤟👅

[📍HazelBAKEzel] Coffee Nutty date rye sourdough with pistachio and pumpkin seeds

Second try on this loaf was inspired by @urbanloaf.factory my no1 favourite sourdough bakery. I've really tried many sourdough from all around SG but seriously none could beat this Queen of sourdough or even come close to it. Definitely sitting tightly on her throne

My sourdough LOAF 10.

Texture:
The crumb is soft and moist but a little dense and slightly gummy because i didnt wait for it to cool properly and went ahead to slice it :((( lesson learnt, BE PATIENT😭

Flavour:
Distinct aromatic coffee fragrance accompanied by some bitter notes. Love how the dates added some sweet caramelised notes w gooey texture; and also how the pistachio nuts and pumpkin seeds adds a nuttylicious roasty profile and crunch texture contrast. As compared to try 1, the coffee notes is definitely stronger and flavour wise is better but still gonna improve on this loaf flavour. I really really love this loaf combination and will keep on improve this till it becomes my BEST sourdough

I think the addition of coffee w milk makes the dough so stiff and sticky/wet. Need to think again😅🤣 anyways YAY to loaf 10

[📍HazelBAKEzel] Pumpkin seed date sourdough

Second try on this loaf that was inspired by @serangoonsourdough (my 2nd fav sd baker in sg~) and I am glad to say I am pretty proud of this loaf 😛🤟😍 definitely missing Justin's bakes!! This flavour, mullberries and the buckwheat loaf are definitely my top 3 favourites from SS! And his cinnamon knots was soooo good!! I am constantly dreaming of it (need to make some soon)

Really proud of this loaf!! The crumb and crust texture is sooo good and its pretty similar @urbanloaf.factory sourdough (which is my epitome of a perfect sourdough loaf). Their crumb is so soft and chewy. And the crust is also really soft, chewy and not dry at all~ So glad that they are coming back 🔥

My sourdough LOAF 9

Texture:
The crumb is soft, fluffy and moist. Satisfied with the open-ness, its like open and really PLUSH (not too big alveoli) so that my nut butter wouldnt leak through. This loaf is gentle yet chewy. The crust is thin, soft and also really chewy. I dont really fancy too hard or dry crust. The dates added some gooey texture contrast and the pumpkin seeds added a nice crunch to the loaf.

Flavour:
Wheaty yeasty fragrance with natural caramelised sweetness fragrance from the dates added some  gooey texture; nuttylicious roasty aroma from the toasted pumpkin seeds. This loaf is so good to eat on its on~

I have a fussy toddler who doesn’t really seem interested in food. But as long as there is rice, his eyes glisten even if it’s just plain white rice! 😂

Clearly I can’t just feed him white rice every meal (although he’d be more than happy) , I constantly have to think of ways to jazz up the rice for a variety of nutritious dishes that cater for his growing body. 

@songhe.rice new crop rice is so convenient as it only requires one time rinse. Since I don’t have a rice cooker I usually steam my rice. Their rice is plump, sweet, moist and really fragrant! It’s approved ✅ by the rice lover in the house coz he said ‘yummy’ right after the first bite and happily finished everything I’ve prepared for him.😆

After preparing the white rice, I added Mirin to the rice and also a can of seasoned mackerel. Stir fry for a few mins and mix them well. Next I put in the kids’ seasoned kombu flakes from japan. Shape the rice using your hand and stuff it into the fried beancurd skin. I love making quick, easy and satisfying meals that the whole family can enjoy. 😋 

Song He New Crop Rice definitely makes an essential staple in your meals and it is easily available for purchase at FairPrice, giant, Cold Storage, Sheng Siong, Prime Minimarts, Esso and their online platforms Redmart/ Lazada, Shopee, Foodpanda, Amazon & Qoo10.

Thank you @songhe.rice for the delicious new crop rice and @getkobe for the arrangement! 🥰

I’ve made myself a cup of matcha rose latte to celebrate this special day coz Valentine’s Day is also a day to shower myself with self love! 🌹💕

🍵 Prepare a cup filled with ice
🍵Whisk Superior Ceremonial Blend Matcha powder with hot water 
🍵Pour in the oat milk then the whisked matcha 
🍵For the rose mixture, Whisk oat milk, dragonfruit powder, rose syrup and rose infused honey. 
🍵Pour it into the matcha latte as the last step. 

Enjoy this therapeutic and pampering matcha rose latte! 🥰 I really love the strong matcha fragrance and the versatility of this blend. Perfect for making Usucha (thin matcha tea ), lattes or smoothies. 😋

Here’s to a year of better habits, positive thinking, clean eating and most of all, loving yourself. 🥰

I’m a noodles lover but I tend to get indigestion from regular flour. I prefer using betterthan noodles as an alternative to regular noodles. It is made from Juroat® flour, a secret blend of Organic Konjac flour and Organic Oat fibre complex. This is also great for people who are trying to lose weight as it contains Zero Carbohydrate. The noodles are also wheat free, fat free and sugar free. 

I have tried many different konjac noodles and this particular brand from @zestyleafsg has the most similar consistency to regular noodles. It doesn’t have this weird plastic taste like some of the ones I’ve tried. The Noodles is very subtle in flavour and easily takes on the taste of the food and sauce i cook them in.

I’ve made some kimchi chicken collagen broth to go with the Thai style konjac noodles. 😋 

👩‍🍳 Stir fry Sakura Ebi and red onions with olive oil. 

👩‍🍳 Add in chicken collagen broth, Scallop powder, Sweetcorns and Kimchi seasoning powder.

👩‍🍳 Then add my fav kurobuta Shabu pork & Korean fishcakes. 

👩‍🍳 Throw in the rinsed konjac noodles to boil for a few mins. I’ve also added some baby spinach before serving. 

👩‍🍳 Add Himalayan pink salt to taste. 

Thank you @zestyleafsg for these healthy, yummy and versatile organic konjac noodles! 🥰

After Zayn’s long CNY school break, I finally can take a breather today plus catch up on my work and chores. 😮‍💨Although schedule still runs tight, I’ve managed to squeeze out some time to make myself a relaxing cup of iced matcha latte! 🍵😆 

I’m using the Superior Blend Ceremonial Grade Matcha from @naokimatcha . I love that it’s so fragrant, not overly bitter and comes in a shade of green that makes my matcha latte so aesthetically pleasing too. Definitely helps me to unwind after such an exhausting week. This particular blend is popular among those new to matcha and the experienced matcha drinkers who love drinking it as usucha. 

Naoki Matcha also offers other curated blends of Japanese matcha that can be used for your lattes, smoothies and bakes. Their matcha blends are so premium and versatile. 

Recipe for my dairy free matcha latte:
🍵 2 teaspoons matcha powder
🍵 2 tablespoons hot water
🍵 Honey as sweetener 
🍵 Unsweetened almond milk 
🍵 ice cubes

Thank you @naokimatcha for the matcha and whisk. 💕 Also thanks to @bappygirl and @domesticassie for hosting the #MatchaMondayMood ! 🥳

Going a lil nuts over these peanut butters 🥜 If you guys recall, I’ve posted about @manilife_’s peanut butter awhile back! & now, back with 2 other flavours from their peanut butter range (rich cocoa & original roast). 

As a choco lover, the rich cocoa was love at first bite. You can expect a rich and thick consistency for the texture. As for the flavour, fragrant nuttiness that combines well with the chocolateyness. Best of both worlds right in your mouth 💥 if you bored of your good old peanut butter spread, why not switch it up & try out the rich cocoa today! 🌞 For the original roast, it tasted almost similar to the previous one which I’ve tried, just slightly milder in terms of the roasting process, but ‘twas good for a  breakkie/snack idea (like what I’ve done) 😉

In a nutshell, it’s really peanut butter like no other 🥜 thank you @zestyleafsg for sharing this lovely treats with me! 🙆🏻‍♀️ do check them out for other cool offerings they have! ✨

What’s the one item that you cannot miss out during CNY? It’s ABALONE! Abalone is considered as a symbolic food during CNY that brings about good wealth and abundance for the rest of the year! So… hurry and stock up some abalones for the festive season! 

There are many ways to enjoy the abalone and I believe, for most, it’ll be eating it during steamboat! However, I decided to make something special that I’ve came across online! “Abalone Nest”, which simply is made up of air-fried shredded yam, abalone from @newmoonsg and some accompanying veggies to spice things up! 

If you don’t already know, @newmoonsg’s abalone is Singapore’s No.1 Best Selling Abalone. I would think that it’s largely attributed to its harvesting process and the procedures afterwards! The abalones are wild caught (less of nasties, more of wholesome goodness) and the abalone itself has a firm texture, with superior taste and lovely umami flavours.

If you are interested in getting some abalones, it is available offline at selected leading supermarkets islandwide and online on New Moon Official Website and and major online platforms.

🇯🇵 Izakaya Niningashi 🍣 

Missing Japan? The closest that you can get is probably by indulging in some authentic Japanese yummy goodness! Have heard so much about this Izakaya place & finally got to try it! Izakaya, simply means “stay-drink-place”. Usually a bar setting where you can experience a wide range of Japanese snacks and of course… alcohol! 

Here are some of the items I’ve tried: 
1) 4 pax assorted sashimi platter (5 kinds) 
2) Wagyu Yukke Sashimi (raw beef sashimi w/ egg yolk) 
3) Bansuke - 2 kinds (Grilled mackerel - Hokke & Akao) 
4) Kanpachi Kama (Grilled stingray fins) 
5) Grilled rice ball with Ikura
6) Wagyu diced steak (100g)
7) Hot sake 

One quote to describe the assorted sashimi would, “freshness you can taste”. This is probably one of the freshest sashimis I’ve tried, apart from that just look at the plating! How pretty 🤩 There are various kinds of sashimis you can go for (5/7/9 kinds). This is one of the dish that I thought was most worth it, given the thick slice & assortment! 👍🏻

The raw beef sashimi was totally mind blowing! (Mainly because it’s my first time trying & definitely not the last time!) At first bite, I was so amazed by how well marinated the beef was. The egg yolk added a creamy texture to overall mouthfeel. (Highly recommend!)

For the grilled fishes, my fav would be the grilled stingray fins as it’s so so soft & had the level of umami-ness. For the mackerels, it was a tad too salty for my liking and for texture wise, definitely not as soft as the stingray fins. 

Adding some carbs to the meal, we ordered the grilled riceball with Ikura. I would say it’s pretty unique because it gives off the pleasant chestnut flavour and goes really with the bursting ikura! 

Was tempted by the diced beef so just had to order some to try! Nothing special but it was still a good dish! 

Of course, no meal is complete without… drinks! It’s my first time trying hot sake and wow! Was pretty amazed by how much smoother the sake was when it’s hot. Not gonna lie, it goes really well with the cold sashimis! 🤗 

As this place is really popular, you might want to reserve in advance to save yourself from any disappointment! 🥳

🥯National Bagel Day🥯 

Two Men Bagel House, needs no introduction as it’s probably one of the go-to bagel places for most! If you are visiting during the lunch period, get ready for the long queue as it’s gonna take quite awhile! Thankfully, I went early (1130am) and there was no crowd at all! 🥳

My go-to order whenever I’m at TMBH would be Lox w/ cheddar bagel (smoked salmon, onions, fried capers, tomato, scallion cream cheese, lemon juice). If you look at the bagel to fillings ratio, you can tell how generous they are with their fillings! 🤩 also, if you are wondering if you’ll be full from just the bagel itself? The answer is…. YES. With the thick bagel and generous fillings, you’ll definitely fall into a food coma after that. Excess saltiness from the salmon is balanced out by the cream cheese and tomatoes. Each ingredient is paired nicely to balance out the overall taste of the bagelwich. ‘Twas a good meal 🥯🤗

Oh, to make it even better, get yourself a cuppa of coffee too! ☕️

About a month ago, we steam some glutinous rice, put some brewer's yeast and let them sit in a glass bottle. It started pretty dry, but after fermenting for days, now we have our yellow rice wine 黄酒.

The taste of this wine depends on the brewer's yeast. Normally there are 2 distinct profile. The pungent one or the sweet one. For me, sweet is good. 

2kg of glutinous rice yield 4 full bottles of rice wine. We added some cognac on the top to prevent oxidation & prevent the wine to turn mouldy. 

Soon its time to make yellow wine chicken 黄酒鸡! 😋

p/s Yes it is perfectly legal to make this at home in Singapore as long as it fulfills a certain condition. No worries. 
.

Hot & sour fish soup 酸菜鱼 is a traditional Chinese dish originated from a fishery village of Chongqing, China.

We have been craving for this dish for months, and today we thought, what if we make a hotpot dinner out if this soup. Turns out great!!!

Since its a rainy evening, it feels so warm to have hotpot at home. Not so much proteins, but we feel great to have abundance of veggie. 

So satisfied!

description:
This little 🐰 coconut pudding was too cute to eat 🥺

I love when new Asian restaurants pop up near me, especially when it’s as delicious as @heyyuetnyc 🥰 they have a variety of dim sum and Cantonese dishes, some of which are modern / have a fun twist (like the cheesy pineapple bun😍) and others that are classics and remind me of home. 

Pictured are:
• coconut pudding 🐇
• crispy char siu bao
• cheesy pineapple bun 
• pork bean curd wrap
• salted egg chicken 
• peach gum egg custard 
• wonton noodle soup 
• rice roll with shrimp 

Highlights for me were the salted egg chicken (I’m a sucker for salted egg), cheesy pineapple bun, and crispy char siu bao - definitely must trys 🥰

Also can’t leave out that the people here are amazing, thank you so much for having me @heyyuetnyc 💕

📍Hey Yuet, 251 W 26th St New York, NY 10001

Valentines Day bagel party 🥳💕

The cutest Valentines Day bagels ever from @libertybagelsny 😍 They are heart shaped and have the prettiest blends of pinks and white! I’m such a sucker for cute foods like this 😂

We got some with Nutella cream cheese, birthday cake cream cheese, and a classic bagel egg and cheese. Yummy & pretty! 

📍@libertybagelsny

Had a little early Valentines Day celebration at home this year because I had to leave for a work trip on the night of the 13th. Any excuse to celebrate by overeating, we are here for it 💁🏻‍♀️

We had a delicious feast at home, which included:
• home-cooked tomahawk steak 
• home-cooked Vancouver crab 
• abalone
• scallion chicken
• duck wings
• garlic bread

Quite a mish mash of different foods, which is usually how we like it 😂 

Hope everyone has a wonderful vday, whether celebrating with your SO, having a galentines, or just enjoying some me time. 💕

Taking advantage of this (relatively) warm weekend in NYC to walk around and enjoy some soft serve 🍦☺️☀️

Loved this matcha vanilla swirl from @chachamatcha 🍵 the matcha flavor is not too strong, so perfect for those that prefer a more subtle matcha flavor.

Hope everyone is enjoying the weekend! 🥰

Kamiiso-no-torii(one of the torii gate of Oarai Isozaki Shrine) located in Oarai-town,Ibaraki.
茨城県大洗町に鎮座する大洗磯前神社の鳥居の1つである神磯の鳥居。
平安時代の856年に、こちらの御祭神の大己貴命と少彦名命が降り立ったと云われる岩礁に立てられた鳥居です。
