So lucky to be able to try @misuboi.sg seasonal flavours 𝑹𝒆𝒅 𝑽𝒆𝒍𝒗𝒆𝒕 and 𝑪𝒉𝒂𝒊! Red Velvet is an interesting concoction of buttermilk, vanilla and cocoa, and all of these taste profiles blend with each other harmoniously! Chai is really like having fragrant chai latte in tiramisu form! Both tiramisu are so light and smooth that every bite seems to glide down my throat. Do check out their extensive menu, there is bound to be a flavour that satisfies your cravings! 😍

The same creative brains behind @misuboi.sg are also brewing cold brew coffee at @coldbrusg! I like that their coffee isn’t too acidic or bitter. My sweet tooth totally enjoys the velvety 𝑩𝒓𝒐𝒘𝒏 𝑺𝒖𝒈𝒂𝒓 white coffee. 🤩

Thanks again @misuboi.sg and @coldbrusg for sending over these yummy treats! 💕

#samxmediadrop

Hope everyone is having a lovely Valentine’s Day! 💖 These sweet treats definitely made my day! 🥰

So glad that I have the chance to try @misuboi.sg seasonal and unique flavours 𝑹𝒆𝒅 𝑽𝒆𝒍𝒗𝒆𝒕 and 𝑪𝒉𝒂𝒊! Their tiramisu are creamy yet light and easy on the palate. I finished one box on my own very quickly. 🤭 Kudos to the guys for creating so many distinct flavours to excite our tastebuds! 🤩

The 𝑩𝒓𝒐𝒘𝒏 𝑺𝒖𝒈𝒂𝒓 𝑪𝒐𝒍𝒅 𝑩𝒓𝒆𝒘 from @coldbrusg is smooth and fragrant. The natural bitterness of coffee is toned down by the sweetness of brown sugar. Great for people with a sweet tooth (like me)! 😍 But those who find it sweet can probably add ice.

Many thanks to @misuboi.sg and @coldbrusg for sending over these yummy treats! 💕

#samxmediadrop

@sabiobythesea.sg - Enjoy yummy Spanish cuisine in a chillax al fresco environment ☺️

💎El Pulpo 💵26++
The texture of the Grilled Octopus Leg is on point! The blue stuff is mash potato, so pretty right? It has a charred aroma as it is cooked in Josper Grill.

💎Atún a la Parrilla 💵28++
The Tuna Steak is also grilled to perfection in Josper Grill. Just look at that perfect shade of pink! Very fresh and no fishy taste.

💎Vieiras en Salsa de Cava 💵22++
Fresh Sea Scallops with creamy white wine sauce. Top up $4++ for 3 slices of bread to soak up the sauce!

💎Champiñones al Ajillo 💵12++
Fragrant and tender Garlic Mushrooms!

💎Paella Negra / Paella de Pescado 💵30++ each for Small
Both paellas are served with the same seafood mix (Squid, Sea Bass, Mussels, Clams, Shrimp), just different bases, black squid ink or tomato. My friends and I unanimously prefer the black squid ink one! The tomato one is decent too but I’ve tasted nicer ones elsewhere. 🤭

Check out @donburi_maruya that serves a wide variety of premium Japanese donburi at wallet-friendly prices! 🎉

Craving for deep fried food? Theirs are crispy and not greasy! Can opt for Curry or Teishoku version depending on our mood hehe. Their Pork Katsu is fresh, don’t have the “frozen” taste that I dislike. 👍🏻 Their curry goes well with both udon and Japanese pearl rice.

💎Ebi Fry Curry Udon 💵12.80
💎Pork Katsu Curry 💵9.80
💎Mixed Seafood Fry 💵13.80

Prefer non-fried options? Try their tender sukiyaki beef that comes with a perfect onsen egg! Their unagi toji is tasty and satisfying too. 🤤

💎Special Sukiyaki Don 💵12.80
💎Deluxe Unagi Toji Don 💵15.80

Many thanks to @liveloveatwithjie for the invite and @donburi_maruya for the sumptuous spread! 💕

#samxinvitedtasting

Affordable and satisfying cake sets at @parisbaguette_sg ☺️ A cake + coffee/tea at $10 nett, top up $2 for a premium cake, top up $2 for a premium drink. I paid with @krisplus.official app and got another 10% off! 🎉

The Blueberry Yogurt Tart is very light and refreshing that I kept taking bite after bite. The Sliced Double Choco Fudge Cake is rich and dense, great for chocolate lovers.

P.S. I had this in late Nov 2021 but kept forgetting to post 😅 Please check in-store posters for the latest promotions and prices ya! ☺️

Anyway our 1st.. see if its worth the Q hahahah 👍😁

Finally tried out the bak Kut teh at Michelin Bib Gourmand 2021 @joosiahbakkootteh.

It’s surprisingly cheap as compared to the usual restaurant BKT and quality isn’t compromised!

Ribs were extremely tender and the soup was a good balance of peppery and savoury.

The pork trotter was fantastic as well and literally fell off the bone. Highly recommend getting the beancurd too!

With all the hype surrounding @yatkayan’s traditional desserts, we definitely had to make our way down to see what all the fuss is about!

Of course we had to try their orh nee! Smooth, thick and flavorful with bits of yam and lots of gingko nuts – taste and texture wise, it really reminded us of the ones served at weddings, which we definitely love. However, for those who are not fans of shallot oil, this might not be your favourite.

We also thoroughly enjoyed their Ice Jelly with Soursop and Passionfruit. The tanginess of this bowl served as a refreshing contrast. This dessert may be overshadowed by all the hot options on the menu, but we highly recommend it as well!

Is it just us ? We feel like Ba Chor Mee (BCM) is one of the best supper food to have, after a drinking session (not forgetting KKM too) 🤤🍻🥃

The flavourful noodles that wakes us up a little (depending on how much you drink 😅), and that warm rich broth to calm our stomach down - satisfying 😌👍

And when it comes to BCM, undeniably Ming Fa is one of our favourites, partly because they open till late (24hours to be exact) 😁😋

Can never say no to a feast at @sushirosingapore! They’ve just revamped their price list and menu too so more menu items to get spoilt over 😬

Our favourite is the fatty tuna!

We don’t care what people say – Magherita Pizza is NOT lame, and good ones are actually hard to find! This one from @piccantepizzasg is *chef’s kiss* 👌🏻

That, together with Loaded Fries on the side, throws all the exercise that you’ve done on the way there right out the gates of the Botanic Gardens. But we think it’s worth every single calorie!

1月1號元旦第一餐
之前訂了枱
幸好早到了
可以自選一個很好的座位 

食物造型非常適合打卡
味道亦成正比 

其中瑤說必點的可麗餅
的確是有驚喜
包在餅中滿滿是菜
拌上煎蛋的一口
我認為是最佳配搭 

飯後可以在店內拍照
食客都守規戴好口罩出入 

餐廳附近有元朗小巴和64K巴士
交通還算方便
記得要訂位
否則walk-in有機會白行一趟

------------------------------

燒雞沙律 $128

蜜桃綠茶冰 $68
櫻花蜜桃梳打 $68
以上為2人用餐.

一直鍾情傳統西餐廳
多謝瑤訂枱為我慶祝生日 

餐廳的裝修、服務
對食物的嚴格
令整個氛圍都非常浪漫 

晚餐中我最喜歡的
除了扒牛柳拼鵝肝醬紅酒汁
就是百里香田螺清湯 

清湯重點就是要夠清
湯味濃但不會膩口 

牛柳點了五成熟
煎得剛好肉質軟嫰
淨下的紅酒汁再用法包沾來吃
完整的享用整個菜式 

最後還點了招牌拿破崙蛋糕
為這餐完美的生日飯作結尾 

Happy Birthday To Me~

------------------------------
-雅谷餐廳 Amigo-
是日晚餐 四道菜 $1200（每人）
香煎法國鴨肝
百里香田螺清湯／龍蝦周打湯
香煎鱸魚柳配淡龍蝦汁
扒牛柳拼鵝肝醬紅酒汁／扒大蝦配牛柳
香草脆糖燉蛋／橙酒梳乎厘
拿破崙蛋糕 $250
以上為2人用餐.

Where do fruits go on vacation? 

Pear-is. 

Exploring and finding new cafes to have brunch is a weekend mission for us. We are so happy to find this hidden gem in Point Cook @littlemissvioletcafe 🔥

The service is prompt and the owners are so friendly and down to earth. Their menu is Korean fusion, enough variety without been too cluttered. They even have treats for dogs. 🐶

We ordered the:
💥 Baked french toast with seasonal fruits - perfect for all the sweet tooths out there.
💥 Beef bulgogi burger
- perfectly cooked tender slices of beef between a soft milk bun served with chips
💥 The Galbi
- pork was well seasoned and so tender. Beautiful presentation as well
💥 Matcha Latte
-perfect matcha hit 

Overall we really liked this cafe. Food is great but it is friendliness of the owners that will make us regulars.

📍 Shop9/48 Windorah Drive Point Cook VIC 3030

As a proud born and bred Penangite, I always look out for Penang food everywhere I visit. So when I found this hidden gem in Warrnambool I couldn't resist trying. They specialise in 2 main dishes - laksa (curry and assam) and nasi lemak. Both laksas were delicious and comforting but the highlight for me is the nasi lemak. The coconut rice is super creamy and the beef rendang was fragrant and tender. The crispy anchovies and egg complemented a wonderful dish. Check out the drink! 

Happy New Year everyone!

What better way to continue the festive season eating than to have a BBQ. North China BBQ (using charcoal) in Preston has been around for nearly 4 years and we finally had the chance to try it. We were super impressed by the variety and especially the freshness of the meat. We tried 2 types of skewers and the lamb skewers were incredible - fatty, tender and well marinated. Their kimchi pork belly stir fry was also wonderful. We will be back! 🤩

Bomb-tastic sourdough bombolini @sourbombebakery !

Managed to snatch up a box of their signature sourdough bombolini during their October preorder. Box of 9 comes with their 6 signature flavours and 3 seasonal ones. Couldn’t decide which to get so all it shall be! These bombolini babies did not disappoint with their generous fillings encased with soft, fluffy and chewy exterior. Some of the flavours are on the lighter side, which is makes it less cloying and easy to demolish in a seating! Recommend to heat up before devouring as it tasted so much better when heated! Preorder available for those that want to secure a box and don’t want to queue!

The best man @mr_baguette_singapore ! 

Finally checking this place off our wishlist after seeing many reviews about it. @mr_baguette_singapore serves lava filled mini baguettes. The outer was crispy and a bite into it unveils a fluffy and airy inner with a generous amount of lava. Sort of like a baguette exterior mix with croissant interior. Got a shock when we bite into it as the lava started flowing out, making a mess on our plate. Ultra generous with their fillings! The best baguette I ever had and would definitely order again if I’m around the area.

I want bingsu! @wanwan.thaicafe 

The store was buzzling at 11pm when we got there and was put on waiting list which we waited for around 15-20mins before getting a seat. Went for the Thai Milk Tea Bingsu for an interesting twist to the traditional flavoured bingsu. The bingsu was lightly flavoured with Thai Milk Tea shaved ice, sprinkled with cookie crumbs and topped with a scoop of Thai Ice Milk Tea! Digging into it, we realised that there were more layers of Thai Milk Tea powder and crunch beneath the ice. We always loved it when they put in additional layer as simply just the top layer isn’t enough! The cookie crumbs complemented the refreshing and aromatic Thai Milk Tea Shaved Ice. However, the portion was much smaller than we expected. Nonetheless, we would definitely head back to try their famous toast!

Another day, another salad ✨

The sweetness from the watermelon goes oh-so-well with the saltiness of the Haloumi and the freshness of the mint. What a combo. 

Toss watermelon, Haloumi, rocket or salad greens and cucumber in a bowl. Add a citrus dressing and lots of cracked pepper. Enjoy 🍉

These lettuce wraps were so darn good 🤤🤤

In my aim to eat more veges and cut back on meat I’ve been experimenting with tofu more and woooow these exceeded expectations. Hoisin peanut sauce. Crispy tofu. Hidden veggies. Crispy lettuce. Zingy lime. You name it, this has it. 

Super easy to prep but a little messy at the table! Would also work as a simple salad bowl for those less-messy folk.

DM me for the recipe 😉

As far as possible, I try to incorporate plant-based options into my meals for health and environmental reasons. 

One of the reasons why I find it hard to go completely vegan is my love for cheese 🧀 

Yes, I’m cheesy. Even my jokes are.

✍️An honest review of @herbyvorefoods Sustainably Cheesy Spreads: 

A good alternative but not a substitute - I like it because it actually tastes like pea hummus, a bit nutty, smooth and creamy, but it’s not as savory and addictive as cheese is. That being said, even regular cream cheese isn’t exactly “cheesy”, so don’t expect like your cheap fake nacho cheese taste that we associate with cheese - it’s as neutral as cream cheese is so this was actually a pretty good alternative to cream cheese. I thoroughly enjoyed it with the bagel and dill - and would eat it again.

✌️Two flavours: Original and Garlic & Thyme. 

ABOUT @herbyvorefoods CHEESY SPREAD

🧀A cheesy spread made of peas.
🍀Plant-based, non-dairy, vegan
🇸🇬 Manufactured in Singapore and the peas are carefully sourced from farms in Canada.

Visit @herbyvorefoods to find out more.

Delicious & Authentic Filipino Food at Lucky Plaza that will win your heart ♥

This place was introduced to me by my ig friend @foodie_luwee quite some time back and I finally get to try it on 2 occasions.

I like what I’m eating the 1st time, so I decided to go back for a 2nd time. This place has a casual homey vibe that I like too. 

So far I’ve tried out 𝘀𝗶𝘀𝗶𝗴 (refer to 4th slide - 𝗮 𝗽𝗼𝗽𝘂𝗹𝗮𝗿 𝗺𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘁𝗲𝗺), adobo, chap chye and liver. Everything was very yummy, has good size servings and rich in flavor. A really good meal for me ;) 

Of course, not forgetting the very tempting dessert - corn pudding with coconut which is super delicious. They have more variety of other food and desserts in their store. Shall try it out next time. ☺️

Overall pricing is rather reasonable. We can choose to order it with rice as a set or ala carte individual items. When you dine there, you will be provided with a free soup. 

If you have not tried Filipino food before, I highly recommend you to check out this place. The auntie there is very friendly, she will advise you on what to order if you are not sure :)

description:
One of the iconic Peter's #porknoodles stall at Restaurant Shangri-la in Brickfields. This is the 2nd stall in Brickfields which sits in a much more comfortable and cooling coffee shop than the original oven hot Money's Corner food court.
.
.
#chuyukfun #malaysiannoodles #noodles #Chinesenoodles #malaysianfood #brickfieldsfood #brickfields #staplefood #hawkerfood #foodcourtkl #foodcourt #eatlah #musteatporknoodles

Do you fancy a classic good ol'  type of #wantonmee ? Unlike Klang Valley ones that are often heavily flavored with pork lard oil, dark soy sauce and light soy sauce, this springy noodles at #khengpincafe is lightly salted and tossed with chicken broth for a wetter, smoother texture. The wanton noodles are then paired up with #bqqpork #charsiu , shredded chicken, green leaves and succulent, juicy #wanton dumplings . Just taking a bite stirred fond memories of school days where my friends and I will ride our bikes to a coffee shop for a simple but satisfying plate of wanton mee 😊

Braved the CNY jam and drove up to Batu Feringghi bumper to bumper for 50 mins to a small little hut serving delectable #hainanesefood and yes the place is small. It can only cater to about 8 tables max. So do book ahead if you plan on going.

Wanted to order the popular chicken pot pie but it was too huge a portion for us. So had their #hainanesechickenchop , hailam noodles and sizzling #porkchop instead though the pork chop didn't turn out how I was expecting it to be 😅 It was more of stir-fried pork slices served on a hot plate. The homemade #springrolls were my favorite amongst the food ordered and they are not your average size rolls. I will be completely full from eating a plate of this 😁

This #prawnfritters is my no. 1 #musteat when I visit #Penang . It's perfectly deep fried to just the right crunch that feels light to the bite and is filled with big prawns. Their #lohbak or #ngohiang is also very good. Thank goodness they reopened the day I was leaving Penang. If not my trip would have felt lacking this awesome eat. 

#penanglobak #penanglohbak #penangmusteat #penangeats #penangfood #MustEatPenang #musteatpenangfood #MustEatToday #yummyyumyum #foodiepenang #malaysianfoodie #foodilicious #foodgasm #foodporn

Pitt Street #kuayteowthng but location is  actually at Carnavon Street #Penang as they have relocated from their original location.

Their specialty here is eel meat #fishball  but not too worry if you don't eat eel meat as you can't really taste it in the fishball. The soup has a strong 3-in-1 broth taste as it is boiled with chicken bones, pork bones and duck bones 😋

Uniquely, the flat piece of meat is actually made of minced pork and is not fish paste nor fish cake.
.
.

Threepointtwo Gelato & Coffee 
@threepointtwo.sg
🍽(Invite Tastings)🍽

🇸🇬📍: 85 Kampong Bahru Singapore
🚇Outram Park 

Signature Gelato Bun 
💵$4 
A must to be order if u are here for Mao Shan Wang ice cream!
The very unique outer coating of the bun is somehow crispy!
Love the presentation of the bun as a little cute monster! Thumbs up!👍

Waffle 
💵$5.50 
Waffle served with ice cream!
Soft & Fluffy Waffle paired together with ice cream is definitely a perfect match!
If u prefer to have it sweeter, maple syrup is provided!

Gelato Flavours we tried: 
•Ferrero Rocher 
•Mao Shan Wang
•Triple Coconut Sorbet 

Ferrero Rocher: 
Thick chocolate 🍫 that taste similarly as Ferrero Rocher! Chocolate lovers will sure love this! This was one of my favourite gelato! 

Mao Shan Wang:
Heavenly as if we are eating durian!
The durian is creamy and sweet,right choice to eat with the bun!
Love the presentation of the bun as well 😍

Triple Coconut 🥥 Sorbet:
Genuine coconut fresh inside the coconut sorbet! Refreshing yet not so sweet!
Awesome choice on a hot day!

Matcha Latte (Cold) 
💵$6.50 
I like how the Matcha Latte isn’t sweet and it’s very fragrant! As a Matcha lover, this was perfect! 

Chocolate Latte (Hot) 
💵$5.50 
Thick and creamy chocolate latte for a tea break. 
Perfectly great to see the coffee art on it!

Thank you @threepointtwo.sg for the invite 🤩
Convenient cafe as it is a bus stop away from  Outram MRT. Spacious car parks and bus terminal within 5mins walking distance! 
A great spot to chill/relax & it’s very instagrammable 😍 Definitely great for those who love sweet treats 😋 and for people who are hunting for supper as it closes late at 12 midnight!
Would strongly recommend y’all to head down and give them your support!

McDonald's 

Hopped on the bandwagon to try the special BTS meal ($8.90). If you like McNuggets, it definitely doesn't disappoint. For the sauces, i think the sweet chilli dip was the better one, as it was a slightly sweeter version of the old McDonalds sweet chilli sauce. The Cajun dip really wasn't a Cajun dip, more like a spicy mustard-mayo like dip that caused a stinging sensation in the nose. Personally, i prefer the new honey dip that Mcdonalds offers compared to these two.

Smitten Ice Cream Bar

Throwback to when we could still go out and eat, Smitten is a quaint little neighbourhood dessert spot with delicious ice cream.

Signature Waffle ($5.20) with Ice Cream (from $4.20 per scoop) - We got the Artisan Chocolate, Speculoos, and Premium Pistachio flavours. The ice cream was as pleasing to the tastebuds as they were to the eye, and the texture was smooth and rich. The waffles were nice and fluffy on the inside while maintaining a crisp exterior. However, I would skip the chocolate sauce, the quality of that wasn't great. Will definitely go back to try the other creative flavours, such as Atas Paddle Pop!

#sgdessert #sgicecream  #sgwaffles

Mott 32

The ambience of Mott 32 is really fancy and the menu certainly matches that. The quality of the food here is unparalleled.

South Australian Scallop, Prawn, Hot & Sour Shanghainese Soup Dumplings ($10) - The colour of the dumplings already sets the tone for the vibrant burst of flavours you can expect from these dumplings. It's tangier than the classic pork XLBs we know and love, similar to hot & sour soup.

Barbecue Pluma Iberico Pork, Yellow Mountain Honey ($48) - When I saw the price for this dish, I was taken aback. Who pays $48 for char siew? But to the sceptics let me assure you that it is the best char siew you will ever eat in your life. The honey gently caramelised the exterior of each piece, while leaving the interior perfectly melt-in-your-mouth tender. Definitely a must-order at Mott 32!

Cold Free-Range Chicken, Szechuan Peppercorns, Chilli Sauce ($26) - The sauce was numbingly-delicious as the szechuan peppercorns gave it a mala-like flavour. The chicken was extremely tender and went perfectly with the sauce. It was like chicken rice chicken, but elevated to a whole new level with that fantastic sauce. I recommend eating it with steamed rice to absorb all the sauce you can!

#mott32sg #charsiewsg #xlb #malachicken #mott32 #sgfood #sgfoodies #charsiew #xiaolongbao

Menbaka Fire Ramen

The wait was really long and the service wasn't great, but it's good to check it out if you want to experience the theatrical, burn your eyebrows off show.

Kara Miso Fire Ramen ($19.90) - I ordered the spicy ramen, which tasted like a pretty standard spicy ramen, with an almost mala-like flavour. The ramen comes with spring onion, black fungus, corn, and one piece of chashu, which was quite chewy and tasteless. I added the egg as well ($3) which was delicious.

Crispy Karaage Salad ($13.90) - Nothing to rave about, just some pretty mediocre veggies with sesame dressing. The karaage was crispy, but not hot.

📍zazz pizza

parma ($29.00) and burrata ($29.00): both were good pizzas. the parma had a good amount of parma ham. the cutting of the pizza was weird though like it wasn’t evenly cut so it was a bit hard to share among a bigger group of people.

gnocchi with sausage and fennel cream ($31.00): so good!!! the sauce was so thick and flavourful so it went v well with the gnocchi. the sausage was rly nice too. loved this

we also tried their cocktails, zazz fizz and zazz bliss ($17.00 each): alright, nothing special

prices are quite high but the food was good 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

📍iO italian osteria

been wanting to come here for a rly long time! had v high expectations and wasn’t disappointed

porchetta, baked pork belly, wild fennel (small, $9.00): this tastes as good as it looks. the skin was so crispy and the meat was soft, went well with the mustard too!

orecchiette, pork sausage, saffron sauce ($19.00): rly rly good too! the sauce was so creamy and had a rly homely taste, there was a generous amount of sauce too which i loved. i couldn’t get enough of this

traditional stuffed roman schiacciata (small, $10.00): kinda like toasted bread with truffle and cheese in between, which was quite nice. the bread itself tasted good too

assorted pizzas (medium, $24.00): v normal, the crust was quite hard to chew so my mouth was v tired lol and they weren’t served hot either. there were 4 different flavours but 3 of them were very similar so it was kinda like just getting one pizza. would give this a miss 🙁 the meal would’ve been perfect without this

would def come back to order the porchetta and orecchiette pasta again! 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

📍hoshino coffee

double matcha pancake souffle style ($16.90): hoshino is well known for their souffles so i had high expectations for this, but was quite disappointed 🙁 the pancake was not fluffy at all but very dense, it was more like a very thick regular pancake. you had to eat every bite with a lot of the sauce to taste anything more than just pancake, so we ended up with not enough sauce. the matcha sauce was not bad though

wouldn’t be ordering this again, but might come back to try other things as they’re on entertainer

📍the coffee academics

the academics breakfast ($28.00): a decent breakfast platter but nothing very special, quite standard. i should’ve gotten my eggs scrambled instead of poached just because i think scrambled eggs go better with a breakfast platter.

truffle portobello mushroom pizza ($26.00): rly good! the pizza base was like a tortilla instead of the normal base so it was very thin which i liked! the flavours mixed well together and it was rly cheesy too. the portion was a bit small though 

jawa ($6.40 hot): super good coffee it was so creamy and smooth and the gula jawa gave the coffee just the right amount of sweetness 

okinawa ($7.50 iced): good as well but i think it would’ve been nicer hot! and i prefer the jawa haha

a bit expensive even with burpple/entertainer 1-for-1, but the food is decent and the coffee is rly rly good so i wouldn’t mind coming back 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

📍a hot hideout

been craving this for the longest time since it’s in ntu which is rly far away but i finally had it and i had it for dinner 2 days in a row which my stomach is kinda regretting now

but it was soooo good the potatoes were fried so nicely and the scrambled eggs were so creamy and good. i had both the mala tang and dry mala and i preferred the dry mala much more because there’s more taste in every bite and i rly love how their mala tastes. the mala tang is less spicy and u need to drink the soup to taste the mala but the noodles absorbed the soup pretty quickly so it was slightly underwhelming for me. many of my friends like the mala tang though so i guess it’s different for everyone!

not the cheapest and it’s very popular so the queue is always super long. the first day i went there right when they opened so we were the first to get our food and so the waiting time was short but it was rly early for dinner (5pm). the second day i went at 6pm and the queue was already crazy we waited for over 1h to get our food :( just have to take note of the timing but would def come back again 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

Injeolmi Bingsu(S)($11.90)😋
Sweet and milky finely shaved ice spammed with roasted soya bean powder, chewy injeolmi and hidden crunchy cornflakes. Its a bowl full of pure joy.🥰 Loving it!
Injeolmi had a delightful glutinous chewy texture.
By the way, this small size consists of this great amount already, imagine if we order the large one; can feed an army liao.😅
.

Octopus Rice($16.90)🐙
Pearl rice topped with loads of savoury marinated octopus, vegetables and seaweed flake. This is octually good and look at that monsterous bowl size, literally fits my whole head in it. Tastisfying, slippery smooth, succulent & a little slimy octopus together with the mild spicy savoury sauce mixed with rice is simply enjoyable.
-
Bacon Pancake($26.90)👌
Hmm... Sounds fatty and oily but let me tell you, it wasn't super oily as we expected it to be. In fact, there wasn't any much greasy jelakness when we had it. Tasty savoury pancake texture was chewy with a delicate crisp. Bacon, what we thought its going to be high on saltiness and charry crispy on texture surprised us with its soft and tender strips with just the right amount of clean saltiness. The size of pancake was Big till we had trouble finishing it so we takeaway the remaining pieces.😅
-
Mini Steamed Egg($4.90)😋
Ooo... Just look at that eggy bouncey creaminess on top! Isn't it beautiful?😍
Though it was stated as size mini but in reality, the savoury steamed egg was served in a bowl that can feed 2-3 pax.😅 We are just glad we didn't go for the normal size.🤣

Since already make a trip down and had breakfast, might as well get their lunch too.🙃
-
Dew Swordfish Pasta($24)🍝
Linguine, parmesan cheese, rocket salad, baby capers, chilli, lemon, Thai basil, tarragon emulsion, olive oil.
Was kinda shocked by the huge portion they served.😮 Y'all should see our expression.🤣
Anyway, pasta had an incredibly strong, distinct, and an acquired taste with capers giving its briny floral tartness, lemon for a citrusy profile, fresh minty note from Thai basil and olive oil giving an slurpy oily mouthfeel.🤔
As for the swordfish, although they gave quite a lot, but its still a Nope to me. Although the cut was thick but the texture was tough, chewy, plain and super-cooked. Felt like torture when trying to finish it.😅
Definitely interesting in taste but not one to go for as I felt it will not suit most people tastebud.
-
The Aussie Crumpet (V)($15)🥞
Lemon myrtle crumpets, ricotta cheese, lemon curd, fresh berries, berry compote, meringue, wild ﬂowers.
In contrast with that savoury pasta, this sweet crumpet brings great joy to the one who ate it. A fruity sweet happiness. Spongy, chewy and elastic texture with a slight outer crisp. Love the sweet decor of fruits and toppings on top of it especially that lemon curd which gave a good zing to appetise the tastebud.
-
Niko Neko Ajisai Matcha Latte($8)🌹🍵
Not the usual creamy type matcha latte in your mind but rather a clean, pure and refined matcha taste with plain milk. Says to have soybean-like flavour and medium umami savouriness. Appreciate the rose art in it.
-
White Coffee(6oz)($4.50)
Coffee with milk. Swan art for it.😛
.
🚩Dewgather Coffee House, 1 Vista Exchange Green, 01-46, The Star Vista, Singapore 138617
.

Feeling bloated after a meal or having a constipation? Or just your mouth craving for some bubble tea but you also kind of health-conscious?
Fret not, "Hey! I am @yogost_sg " is here for you!
-
Watermelon Yo Tea($6.80)🍉
Fresh watermelon blended with ice poured over into a base of crystal jelly and yoghurt. Mixed well before drinking. Taste like watermelon calpis to me but on a lighter note and more refreshing. Super chilled drink that send your brain freezing too. Good for hydration, cure excess intestinal gas formation and useful in maintaining healthy skin and hair, plus its low calorie.
-
Strawberry Lemon Yo Tea($7.80)🍓🍋
Citrusy burst of prominent lemon taste with mild strawberry flavour mixed with yoghurt. Truly, an atas version of Yakult that not only aids in digestion but also boost your immune system.
-

description:
Newly opened food stall in NTU’s Koufu. If you still remember my post last week, you will find out it’s the same stall. 

I started exploring this stall with their pork bun at first, and it’s a trap that made me dream of it everyday!

I couldn't control myself and endup coming here every day and tried almost all of their noodles (not forgetting their pork bun [Chuckle]). 

My top pick for the sounds base would be the Mushroom followed by Pickled Pepper then last but not least, the Mala.

The springy noodles are generously topped with an array of ingredients. Coriander, fungus, chickpeas sprout and seaweed. You named it, they have it.

This textural combination with the tasty and fragrant soup base  definitely makes for a moreish dish.

Visit our website for more recommendations👇
WAK WAK HAWKER
https://wak-wak-hawker.com/en/ 

the items in the menu. A hidden gem in NTU.

【小馆子】

A newly opened food stall in Nanyang technology University. Pork bun is one of the must-try dishes for Xi’an cuisine. 

Compared to other pork bun in Singapore, this special airy and flaked skin makes the bun tasted crispy. Generous amount of pork with adding a little bit pepper to enhance the favour. 👍 

I keep visiting this stall everyday and almost tried all the items in the menu. A hidden gem in NTU.

𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤 𝐊𝐢𝐧𝐠 & 𝐖𝐡𝐢𝐭𝐞 𝐊𝐢𝐧𝐠 

I prefer black to white king as the addition of fried garlic paste to the original Tonkotsu broth elevates the flavor of the bowl of ramen. As usual, the meat was very tender and flavorful! Both bowls of ramen were topped with bonito flakes and a huge amount of cabbages.

I personally don’t fancy the idea of cabbages with ramen though. Hence, I prefer their tonkotsu black ramen to black king! I’d recommend you getting their normal tonkotsu ramen series as they are somehow more flavorful too and while you’re there, don’t forget to get some xiao long bao from @youpengxlb !

I'm no Singaporean Chicken Curry connoisseur, but this is so gooOOOOd! 

🥓Premium Curry Rice with Pork Belly & Pork Chop ($8.50)
🥘Famous Beach Road Scissor Cut Curry Rice with Chicken Chop ($6)
🍘Fish Patty ($2)

Although we got our fix delivered, everything still tasted amazing - the curry sauce was thick, rich and added so much flavour and dimensions to the entire dish. While I thought the meat🍖 was a little tough and may have been left out for awhile, I'm not complaining! I definitely enjoyed the curried cabbage🥬, it was the best.

Fair warning though, the fish patty/fillet is definitely not worth its price! Also with so many fried things already in the dish, I think I'd go for fish cake next time if I had to choose.
.
Beach Road Scissor-Cut Curry Rice
📍229 Jln Besar, Singapore 208905

Already planning my next visit to @botanicosg because one visit is NOT enough! 

4-Course Set Brunch ($60++ per pax)
🥐Bread of the Day
🦪Seasonal Oyster 
🍠Beetroot 
🥑Smashed Avo On Toast
🎋Asparagus Tempura
🥓65 Degree Kurobuta Pork Belly
🥩Wagyu Beef Cheek
🍫Chocolate Merlot Cake

I loved how the bread was perfectly toasted🍞 and flaky, the oysters🦪 fresh and earthy with the chilli-coriander🌶☘️ granita (don't worry, the coriander taste isn't strong at all!)

My favourite was definitely the 65 Degree Kurobuta Pork Belly🥓, which was so tender melt-in-your-mouth-y that I could barely tell fat from meat! The leak flowers🌱 that accompanied were delightfully crunchy, and went so well with the black vinegar🍾!

I also really enjoyed the dark chocolate mousse🍫 of, feuiletine and chocolate biscuit🍪 on the Chocolate Merlot Cake🍰, which was the perfect sinful ending to our perfect little brunch. I've got to thank my dear friend for this treat!
.
Botanico at The Garage
📍50 Cluny Park Rd, Singapore 257488 (above Bee's🐝 Knees)

Greek cuisine by the river? Yes please! Popped by @zorbatavernasg to try out their weekend brunch menu and mmHMM do they do their meats well!

🥗Dips Platter ($24)
Tzaziki, Hummus, Tirokafteri, Taramasalata, Black Kalamata Olive, Pita Bread
🥘Greek Style Loaded ‘Mac N Cheese’ ($18)
🍖Zorba Mixed Grill Platter ($58)

As always, the Taramasalata dip takes the cake. This one has a stronger roe taste, and would’ve been better if it was slightly colder. Still bangin’, though. The hummus didn’t impress either, and I found the dips overall a little more oily than what I was used to. Don’t worry, there was more pita bread that came along, we just couldn’t resist popping some before everything was here!

I thought they did their mac well, which was chewy yet perfectly cooked. The cheese sauce was creamy but tasted more like nacho cheese, which I’m admittedly not a great fan of.

The platter was a winner. What’s supposed to be crispy was🥓, and the beef steak🥩 was moist, flavourful and tender. I liked also that the oven baked potato chips🥔 were lightly salted🧂, though a select few may have been left out for a little too long.

Honestly we’d still prefer the other Greek restaurants we’ve tried, but this one was really not bad! It’s pet-friendly🐶 too!
.
Zorba The Greek Taverna
📍3A River Valley Road, Singapore 179024

Don’t laugh at me - it’s my first time trying @monstercurry.sg! 

🥘Sausage Curry ($13.80)

Don’t be fooled by the huge plates, the portion size is actually pretty manageable. I liked how the sausages had a distinct smoked taste, and were delightfully chewy! The shredded cabbage definitely can’t compare to the ones served at more premium Japanese restaurants, but still tasted light and crunchy after being dipped in the curry. I personally found the curry a little salty, but there’s always rice to combat that! 🍚
.
Monster Curry
📍Various locations

Bar and bites by the bay? If you've walked along @esplanadesingapore in the evening you may have seen this gastrobar bistro that's usually bustling by nighttime!

🌮Mexicano Taco Fries ($18)
🍝Chicken Aglio Olio ($20)
🍖Meat Grilled Platter ($49)
🍹Classic Mojito ($15)
🍻Go Nuts ($15)

I've tried their famous Pizza Fries ($18)🍟 the previous time, but definitely prefer this Mexicano Taco one! Perfectly seasoned with taco flavour, I could taste real potato🥔 in them fries which go extremely well with the salsa💃🏻 and nacho cheese🧀 dip. Not too overwhelming, and very dangerously moreish!

I had trouble finishing the rest of the food unfortunately - pasta🍝 was a little undercooked with barely the taste of garlic or olive oil, chicken was d r y🥵, marinated lamb cutlets were gamey beyond belief and I wish the sliced beef was marinated better. Wasn't all too impressed by their drinks either because they tasted a little diluted to me.

Maybe a bad day for the kitchen?🧑🏻‍🍳 I do enjoy the vibes of @alteregosg in the evening but didn't have an impressive meal the previous time here either!

Thank you @carbs.monster for the invite and @alteregosg for hosting!
.
Alter Ego
📍8 Raffles Ave, Singapore 039802

Wintermelon pork rib soup, egg tofu w minced pork & my recent obsession of stir fried kangkong for dinner. I like the minced meat gravy! I think I’ll use it on noodles next time. 😋 the King also had a lot of soup - he loves soup just like mama!

I think this could be the first time I’m making sukiyaki without store bought sauce… & meat.. & eggs. Bcos I forgot about them😅 so this is vegan sukiyaki!

I have gotten used to being okay with subpar photos & rushed cooking since becoming a mother. Thankfully, this still tasted good enough!

It is a very flatly coloured bowl, but it was a hit with the boys yesterday. 

Boiled chicken feet with dried scallops & peanuts for half an afternoon, used it as soup base. Added wongbok, enoki mushrooms, marinated meat balls & whole wheat kway teow. The fussy King loved it too! 🥳
I’m not usually great at repurposing leftovers so I’m quite proud of this repurposed sesame chicken noodles from last night’s dinner!

Pork ribs with red dates & carrot soup, stir fried kangkong & steamed eggs w minced meat for dinner. 

A portion of the egg is missing from the main photo bcos Mr Impatient makes it impossible for mama slave to take properly staged photos when he’s hungry😅 but happy to report that he loves his soup just like mama ☺️

⏩ swipe to see what was going on!

📍 yu ba fang • taiwan-style 御八方  锅贴 🥢
Another IG #latergram of the popular < Yu Ba Fang Classic Signature Pan-fried Pork Dumplings $10.90 > with 8 pieces that's good for sharing. The first time we had this was via a care package we received last year.
.
Yu Ba Fang 御八方 is a Chong Qing-based brand that serves Taiwan-style dumplings.
.
Lengthy, light and crisp on the outside, fresh, moist and juicy on the inside. The Taiwanese-style Guo Tie 锅贴 have a fresh and tasty pork filling, best enjoyed with the accompanying chilli oil and ginger vinaigrette dip. 
.

description:
| #ibringmyownsg • peanut muah chee 🥢
A latergram from some time ago, when I requested for my order of < Muah Chee with Crushed Peanuts > to be served in the #OFoodin reusable food bag, to save on disposables used for dining in.
.
Boss Aunty howled: "Why? I don't charge for any dine-in disposable plastic box. How to eat like that from a bag?" A few minutes of utter disbelief and wonderment ensued, with her fellow workers joining in the fray.
.
One of them however, was quick on the uptake. "She doesn't want to waste the box lah" and went scouring for a solution in the form of a soup bowl.
.
OK, CAN !
.
Used my own Miffy cutlery and together, I avoided:
✅ One plastic disposable box and fork
.
.

description:
//sh*t I eat that is #uglydelicious 😂// By now you must all know I have an affinity towards dirrrty-saucy-food. Luckily, there is no shortage of this in Sg 🥳
.
I've been trying to hit more of my local #coffeeshopsg spots during this lockdown and it's brought me a new appreciation of my neighborhood. Was surprised by what a huge selection of Indian and SE Asian-Indian food they had (and at hawker prices). I have a regular spot I usually order from and it usually comes in at double the price🥲 Fair warning ⚠️I had to wait 30+ min for my food when there were only about 5 orders in🤯 So if you are in a rush, this may not be the place for you.
.
Helped myself to the Kottu, Butter Chicken, and Garlic Naan. All these dishes were made fresh, which can sometimes be a risk when ordering from a hawker. This might be blasphemous but I found myself shoveling spoonfuls of the Butter Chicken on top of the Kottu 🔥🤤🍛 You can thank me later😘 Wow was this combo good 👍👍👍
.
In summary #supportlocal and don't be afraid to get your hands dirrrty👽
.
.
.
.
.
.

//when spice is life🌶️💥🍜// If you're searching for a bowl of flaming goodness, then look no further. With all the cool and rainy weather we've been having in Sg recently, I've really been craving soupy things. I had heard about @thailiciousboatnoodles and their famous 1-10 spice level Tom  Yam noodles but hadn't made the trip. Well the time was just right⌛
.
This small Thai shop is tucked away on what I deem as, Hotpot Street in Bugis. Easy to miss, but if you like Thai food you will regret not giving this a try. We tried a lot of dishes, all of which were delicious and fresh. I feel that Thai food is best, especially the salads, when the ingredients are fresh as it is usually mixed with very strong and pungent flavors. When done well, it is a gorgeous pairing that really gives meaning to the term, "opposites attract". 
. 
For this post I am only highlighting the Spicy Tom Yam Egg Noodles. We went with the lvl 10(duh😋). I was a bit nervous if I could handle the spice, as the waitress asked me twice to confirm that I was sure about ordering the max level. However, if you are a spice lover then worry not! These noodles definitely pack a punch, and it is a heat that builds as you eat it🥊💥
I was pleasantly surprised by how much I enjoyed this dish. The Slurp-ability was 💯 and the heat didn't overwhelm the flavors! The broths are rich and thicc🤤 I'm honestly considering going back ASAP to get another bowl because it left me so satisfied 👌
.
.
.
.
.
.

//sun's out, get your Chinese buns out🌞🌭// I made a goal for myself this year that I would try and get to Chinatown at least once a week. I've spectacularly failed at this 🤫🥴 After visiting @siweimaocai my motivation has been reignited🔥⚡
.
After getting over my initial anxiety over their sprawling menu (if you have a tendency to over order and a general lack of self-control when it comes to choosing between delicious foods, like me🙋‍♀️-- boy are you in trouble🤔)
We finally decided on egg fried rice, stir fried cabbage, si wei tofu, and the crowning jewel👑 - Pan fried spicy chicken with BUNSSSS🍑 Bold flavors with that customary Sichuanese oily stir fry glean 👌Next time I would ask for extra spicy 🌶️🌶️🌶️ and bring more people so I can try everything on the menu 😂🙌✨ Until Sg allows for a group larger than 2pax for dine-in, I will gladly take on the challenge of running through their menu, one visit at a time. 😘😋
.
.
.
.
.
.

Waited waaaay too long to visit @starterlab.sg . I'm ashamed to say that it is within walking distance from me and I've just been too lazy to check them #regrets 🥲
.
Their bread is 𝙵.𝚁.𝙴.𝚂.𝙷.
Dine in and they will heat it up for you to that perfect soft-yet-crunches-when-you-bite perfection. In Chinese we have a way of describing food that gives your mouth that satisfying "feel"➡️ 口感👄

Ordered their Grilled Cheese and let me tell you, DO NOT SKIP THE PICKLED PEPPER. They are a Mαƚƈԋ ɱαԃҽ ιɳ ԋҽαʋҽɳ😇 Not sure how Starter Lab discovered this pairing but my life is changed🙏 If you can get there early you may be able to snag yourself one of their Sausage Rolls. It is deceivingly filling and also comes with a delicious side of their "fancy tomato sauce" 🍅 Lastly, I had to to get their Morning Roll🌅 If you are a fan of croissants and also love a cinnamon roll, this is the pastry fusion you need in your life 🙌🔥 🥐 
.
A super chill and neighborhood-y cafe feels kind of place. I only tried three dishes but I am hooked. Located next to the atas af Bootle's Market, giving you the perfect excuse to "run errands"👌🤫

//The QUACK is back 🦆// Nothing beats fresh and steamy-hot roasted duck ♨️🤤 Now that dine-in is reopened in Sg, duck is back on my menu 😁
.
It was my first time at @dianxiaoersg and it definitely won't be my last. We got the Signature 🦆. Pacific Rim is a 2013 American science fiction monster film directed by Guillermo del Toro, starring Charlie Hunnam, Idris Elba, Rinko Kikuchi, Charlie Day, Robert Kazinsky, Max Martini, and Ron Perlman, and the first film in the Pacific Rim franchise. 

The screenplay was written by Travis Beacham and del Toro from a story by Beacham. The film is set in the future, when Earth is at war with the Kaiju, colossal sea monsters which have emerged from an interdimensional portal on the bottom of the Pacific Ocean. 

To combat the monsters, humanity unites to create the Jaegers, gigantic humanoid mechas, each controlled by two co-pilots whose minds are joined by a mental link. 

Focusing on the war's later days, the story follows Raleigh Becket, a washed-up Jaeger pilot called out of retirement and teamed with rookie pilot Mako Mori as part of a last-ditch effort to defeat the Kaiju.

#pacificrim #kaiju #jaeger #movie #thehistoryprofessorwhotravels #pacificocean

By the 6th century in the Chao Phraya River Valley, Mon peoples had coalesced to create the Dvaravati kingdoms. 

In the north, Haripunjaya (Lamphun) emerged as a rival power to the Dvaravati. By the 8th century the Mon had pushed north to create city states, in Fa Daet (modern Kalasin, northeastern Thailand), Sri Gotapura (Sikhottabong) near modern Tha Khek, Laos, Muang Sua (Luang Prabang), and Chantaburi (Vientiane). 

In the 8th century CE, Sri Gotapura (Sikhottabong) was the strongest of these early city states, and controlled trade throughout the middle Mekong region. 

The city states were loosely bound politically, but were culturally similar and introduced Therevada Buddhism from Sri Lankan missionaries throughout the region.

#laos #vietiane #southeastasia #history #thehistoryprofessorwhotravels #laosairlines #nightphotography

Douglas MacArthur (26 January 1880 – 5 April 1964) was an American military leader who served as General of the Army for the United States, as well as a Field Marshal to the Philippine Army. 

He was Chief of Staff of the United States Army during the 1930s and he played a prominent role in the Pacific theater during World War II. 

Macarthur received the Medal of Honor for his service in the Philippines campaign. 

This made him and his father Arthur MacArthur Jr. the first father and son to be awarded the medal. 

He was one of only five to rise to the rank of General of the Army in the U.S. Army, and the only one conferred the rank of field marshal in the Philippine Army.

【 NEW 】With launch of 7 specialties from 4 prefectures [Aomori, Akita, Miyagi and Iwate] from the Tōhoku region, the new menu from @ichibanboshi.sg will surely please diners who love a good Japanese cuisine.

I’ve tried a couple of the dishes on the new menu:

🌸Gyutan with Green Chilli Miso *FAV*
A Miyagi specialty, this is an umami-packed dish with delectable savoury flavours. The miso sauce complements the Gyutan (beef tongue) which has a good bite. Addition of green chilli also gave a satisfying mild spicy kick. Paired with asparagus for an added crunch.

🌸Morioka Reimen *FAV*
Such a refreshing number – thick & chewy Morioka Reimen doused in sweet vinegar soy sauce, to be enjoyed with the watermelon slice, cucumber, kimchi, tomato and egg with black pepper beer & garlic chilli oil. Oishii!

🌸 Hotate Miso Tamago Kaiyaki
Features premium scallops imported from Hokkaido, served with shimeji mushrooms and scrambled egg on hot plate. Hearty dish!

🌸 Senbei Jiru
A country-style dish from Aomori, this essentially means “rice cracker soup”. Quite an interesting dish for me; simmer the crispy rice crackers in the broth before eating them to enjoy a chewy, spongy texture. Dashi broth is wholesome and comforting with ingredients of chicken, shimeji mushroom and cabbage.

🌸Salmon & Ikura Harakomeshi
Featuring salmon and ikura as the 2 key ingredients, served with shredded egg, salted kelp and yuzu zest on seasoned rice. Hearty dish.

Another 2 dishes are Kiritanpo Nabe (over 10 ingredients in this hotpot) and Morioka Jyajya Men (al-dente Japanese noodles with miso minced pork, egg, cucumber and tomato, in a light dashi soy sauce).

The new menu is available from now till 9 May 2022 at all Ichiban Boshi outlets.
🌐 https://www.ichibanboshi.com.sg

Småkagers (aka Danish cookies) and mini tarts/bakes are definitely some of the highlights at 【Leckerbaer】. But that’s not all!

We were equally excited about their new open-faced savoury sandwiches (better known as smørrebrød in Denmark) that are exclusive to the new outlet at Keong Saik! Total reminiscene of my Copenhagen trip ♡♡♡

So of course, we went for both sweets and savoury! We had the tasting set (good for 2 pax) and their savoury sandwiches:

🔸4 Småkagers of choice [tasting set]
We had the Milk, Lemon, Chocolate, Banana. I enjoyed all of these, given a good variety of sweet and zest. There are a couple more other flavours as Raspberry, Hazelnut, Vanilla and Passionfruit.

🔸2 small Bake/Tart/Puff of choice [tasting set]
We picked Lemon & Sea Buckthorn Meringue, Blackcurrant & Vanilla. Tarty goodness! Meringue tends to cloy but given this is shared between 2 of us, so no issue at all.

🔸2 drinks [tasting set]

🔸 Crab and Avocado Salsa
Flavours complements one another so perfectly! Our preference over the other sandwich ♡ 

🔸Roasted Baby Potato and Bacon Sandwich
With pea shoots, pickled red onions and horseradish mayo.

And oh, if you’re looking to indulge the at home or as gifts, they come in boxes of 8 ($24), 12 ($35) and 16 ($46).

📍14 Keong Saik Road

description:
< LIMITED > Look forward to ‘Carles Abellán Specials’ from now till 27 Feb 2022. The ala-carte menu and exclusive lunch/dinner sets (on 25-27 Feb only) are specially curated by @tapas24sg as Chef Carles Abellán made his long-awaited trip from Barcelona.

I really enjoyed the couple of dishes I’ve tried and it was hard for me to narrow down to just 1 favourite. I’ve tried:-

🔸 Mcfoie Burger
This is Chef Carles Abellán’s signature and I can easily understand why. An indulgent dish, no doubt, features foie gras patty sandwiched between brioche buns and served with foie gras mousse. Awesome umami punch and absolutely delectable.

🔸 King Crab Ensaladilla Rusa
I had this as the first dish and it was a great way to start the night. The miso mayonnaise and tobiko gave a savoury lift and added Japanese flavour to the classic Spanish potato salad.

🔸 Truffle Spanish Tortilla (avail during the lunch/dinner sets only)
Good old comforting Spanish omelette with a luxurious touch of winter truffle.

🔸 Squid Ink Paella
A hearty Spanish classic main. Spanish saffron rice in squid ink with slivers of cuttlefish.

🔸 Churros
Perfect way to round off a meal. Served with chocolate, coffee toffee and mango & passionfruit sauces.

🔸 Chocolate Cake
Looks simple but it’s really good. Made with 70% Belgium chocolate, this is rich and indulgent.

To complement the dining experience, guests may choose from an impressive and affordable selection that includes bottle and glass options for all – Sparkling/Champagne, White, Rosé, Red, Fortified, Sweet – starting at $12 a glass/$48 a bottle (Bodegas Luzón, Finca Luzón Blanco). Also the Jean Vesselle, Prestige Brut ($24 by glass and $108 by bottle), which is imported directly by the L’Angélus Group.

📍 The Quayside, 60 Robertson Quay, # 01-04

description:
💛 超美和風𝖢𝖺𝖿𝖾 𓋂 
⸜⸜ 𝖬 𝖴 𝖳 𝖠 ⸝⸝
⁡
𝖠𝖳𝖴𝖬期下既𝖬𝖴𝖳𝖠開左了✨
行西式加日式餐廳，有好多主菜同甜品揀
不過今次就係為左佢地個𝗍𝗈𝖺𝗌𝗍 𝗌𝖾𝗍 而黎 😚
所有野食都唔錯而且環境好岩打卡呢
⁡
⟣ 𝖳𝗈𝖺𝗌𝗍 𝗌𝖾𝗍 ($𝟤𝟪𝟪)
⟣明太子三文魚子帶子奶油意大利飯($𝟣𝟨𝟪)
⟣月見雞肉串棒 ($𝟩𝟪)
⟣ 𝖬𝖺𝗍𝖼𝗁𝖺 𝖫𝖺𝗍𝗍𝖾 
⁡
其實佢仲有另一款𝗉𝗂𝖼𝗇𝗂𝖼 𝗌𝖾𝗍 , 不過𝗍𝗈𝖺𝗌𝗍 𝗌𝖾𝗍 有個爐仔烤下多士好似有儀式感𝖽 😻  套餐包左幾款麵包配自家製果醬、兩款湯（當日係粟米濃湯同薯仔湯）同兩款小泡芙，烤完既麵包脆卜卜好好食 ✨
想飽肚𝖽 佢地既𝗉𝖺𝗌𝗍𝖺 同意大利飯都好好食，小食方面竟然有月見雞肉串，有三大串都幾抵食
稍為可惜嘅係當日咖啡機壞左試唔到咖啡 🥲 
⁡
MUTA Restaurant (尖沙咀)
尖沙咀彌敦道132號美麗華廣場1期地庫B131號舖

☽ 𝖦𝗐𝖺𝗂𝟥 𝖩𝗒𝗎𝗍 𝟨 
⁡
深水埗真係臥虎藏龍既地方
桂月既是咖啡店 同時係酒吧 亦都係𝖺𝗋𝗍 𝗀𝖺𝗅𝗅𝖾𝗋𝗒 
今期佢地仲同本地啤酒品牌「大圍啤」合作推出四季套餐，每款都會配上唔同既手工啤酒🍻 
⁡
【 夏 】 
鐵觀音沖繩青檸𝖳𝖾𝖺 𝖠𝗅𝖾 𝗑 法式桂花鴨胸
第一次飲帶有茶感既啤酒，再加上清新既青檸好有夏天感 ✨ 特意配上桂花鴨胸，醬汁加左桂花所以酸酸甜甜幾開胃
⁡
【 秋 】 
日本煎茶蜜柑𝖠𝗅𝖾 𝗑 牛油果沙律
秋天配上比較溫和既啤酒，柑皮帶有甜甜香氣再加上煎茶
而個牛油果沙律真係好驚喜，切開係釀左三文魚到
⁡
桂月 (深水埗)
深水埗汝州街75號地舖

⁡

◭ 𝟥𝟢 𝖬𝗂𝗅𝖾𝗌𝗍𝗈𝗇𝖾 
⁡
大家仲記得細個時寫既我的志願嗎? 
係香港呢個地方生活得太耐可能會消磨左你既意志
但呢間小小𝖼𝖺𝖿𝖾 既店主話比你聽 理想係一步一步行出黎架 ✨
店主𝖤𝗆𝗂𝗅𝗒 一開始由做網店去到有宜家既實體𝖼𝗈𝖿𝖿𝖾𝖾 𝗌𝗁𝗈𝗉
雖然冇華麗既裝修但卻充滿人情味
小店仲選用比較少見既匈牙利咖啡豆品牌, 而且仲有𝗁𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗆𝖺𝖽𝖾 𝖻𝖺𝗀𝖾𝗅 呢 🤍
⁡
⟣ 𝗁𝖺𝗇𝖽 𝖽𝗋𝗂𝗉 - 𝖤𝗍𝗁𝗂𝗈𝗉𝗂𝖺 𝗁𝗈𝗇𝖾𝗒 𝗉𝗋𝗈𝖼𝖾𝗌𝗌 
⟣ 𝖫𝖺𝗍𝗍𝖾 (𝗁𝗈𝗎𝗌𝖾 𝖻𝗅𝖾𝗇𝖽)
⟣ 抹茶紅豆卷
⟣ 雙重芝士貝果
⁡
聽完𝖤𝗆𝗂𝗅𝗒 介紹後我地揀左𝖤𝗍𝗁𝗂𝗈𝗉𝗂𝖺 限定豆，帶有少少𝗅𝖾𝗆𝗈𝗇𝗀𝗋𝖺𝗌𝗌 同𝗀𝗂𝗇𝗀𝖾𝗋 得黎又唔會太搶味，好飲 ✨ 𝗅𝖺𝗍𝗍𝖾 用左𝗁𝗈𝗎𝗌𝖾 𝖻𝗅𝖾𝗇𝖽 都好𝖻𝖺𝗅𝖺𝗇𝖼𝖾好好飲
⁡
黎到都一定要試下𝖤𝗆𝗂𝗅𝗒 親手整既𝗉𝖺𝗌𝗍𝗋𝗒 😍 
抹茶紅豆卷帶濃郁抹茶亦好鬆軟
雙重芝士貝果夠足料，成個脹卜卜加埋個𝖼𝗋𝖾𝖺𝗆 𝖼𝗁𝖾𝖾𝗌𝖾 好正🤍
⁡

🔸Potato Pancake🔸

Dear Parents, I hope you are doing well today. It's the first day of the 875 times we are having home based learning and I'm not sure why I still decided to cook today. The chaos have settled a little by afternoon. Since there are some leftover potatoes from days before, the kids had potato pancake for lunch, a dish inspired by the Polish placki. Some grilled and shredded salmon were added, making each piece of the pancake rather filling. Shall keep this post short and sweet. Gearing up for the next 9 days!
💪💪💪

🔸Kids Favourite Sweet & Sour Dish 🔸
酸甜咕咾肉配米饭吃, 太开胃了！

This must be one of the most popular dishes in every Chinese restaurant. I don't know any kids who don't enjoy the sweet and sour pork. Certainly, my all time favourite childhood dish and even now, i stilll love it! What's more, the beta carotene and Vitamin C in bell peppers are well absorbed in the presence of iron and fat found in meat. Very riped pineapple was used in this recipe to enhance the natural sweetness. Also, apple cider vinegar is a good substitute if there's no vinegar for Chinese cooking, just like in my kitchen :) Here's a recipe I've simplified and tested which has turned out well. Hope you try out too. 😉

Ingredients :

Sliced Fish/ Sliced Pork Shoulder
Onion (preferably red but I used the white as i had that) 
Tricolour Bell Peppers
Tomato, Red and Ripe 
Sliced Pineapple
Corn Starch 
Plain Flour
Cooking Oil

Sauce 
Tomato Sauce (6 tbsp) 
Brown sugar (2.5 tbsp) 
Apple Cider Vinegar (2 tbsp) 
Soy sauce (1 teaspoon) 
Cornstarch (1 teaspoon)
Water (3 tbsp) 
*mix well 

Method :

1. Pat dry the fish/pork. Slice and coat with plain flour throughly. Then coat with cornstarch. Press each piece with cornstarch firmly before frying. 
2. When the oil is hot enough, fry the sliced fish/pork til golden brown.  Set aside. 

* For healthier alternative method, you can airfry. 

 3. Using the same wok, after removing the oil, leave a little to stir fry the vegetables til slightly soften. Dont overcook. Remove the vegetables and set aside. 
4. Then, pour in the sauce and cook for a minute  or until the sauce starts to thicken. 
5. Add in vegetables and the fried meat. 
6. Coat well with the sauce and serve.

🔸Salmon Broccoli Fingers🔸
三文鱼+西兰花香脆鱼条这样做，不吃蔬菜小孩都会喜欢!试试看🤗

Here's an easy method to make healthy and yummy fish fingers with lots of hidden vegetable! All we need are baked salmon, steamed broccoli, a little flour to bind the ingredients and some salt + pepper, mushroom/ chicken powder to taste. 
Also, this recipe works well for batch cooking too. I can just pop them into oven in the morning to make a quick lunchbox for the older kids. So hit the save button if you'd like to make some homemade healthy fish fingers for kids who dislike vegetables! My youngest who dislike broccoli finished every bit of these. Not like he didn't see the green bits but he just didn't mind them because they were tasty✌️😉.

🔸🇸🇬National Day Lunchbox 🔸

A very good morning on the National Day of Singapore. It's a public holiday with great weather!We are heading out for some outdoor activities. Instead of school lunchbox, I've packed for the hiking trip. The petite rustic French boule from @wholesomeharvestsg fits nicely into the lunchbox and they also carry many healthy products suitable for breakfast. My kids love the organic packet milk which comes in 4 flavours.

After warming the boules, they are sliced to create the lion's face. I've used some yoghurt and red dragon fruit mix to create the pink layer but the intended colour is red. However this shade is the closest that could be achieved using fruit. So that's our National Day bento. Did you create any national day food art too?

🔸Kids Breakfast - Fruit Roll-Up🔸

It's another stay home Sunday breakfast for us. Made some fruit roll-ups using strawberry, banana and green apple. Simple ingredients, easy steps.

1. Cut the fruits into tiny pieces.
2. Sprinkle some honey on the green apple and brown sugar on the strawberry.
3. Roll up using the mini tortilla wrap.
4. Pan fry til golden brown in some butter.

Voilà ! These mini tortilla wraps are super easy to create kids meal with. Very blw friendly too. Have a good weekend!

🍜 Ramen 🍜

Invited tasting to @kanadaya.sg 
📍 Marina Square #02-203/204

My first dining experience at Kanadaya as I have heard many good reviews on their Tonkotsu Ramen 🍜 

Kanadaya has been Voted No.1 Best Ramen in London by the Telegraph. Kanada-Ya specializes in authentic Tonkotsu Ramen. Kandaya-San shares his success story behind the bowl of this delicious noodles on the wall of the restaurant. 

Here are the Ramen that we have for this tasting experience:

Spicy Yuzu Ramen 🍋🍜
Refreshing Yuzu taste with light spiciness. The combination is pretty delightful and is served with 2 slices of charsiew collar, spring onions, and pickled onions with spicy miso and nori. 

Tonkotsu mix Ramen 🍜
An all-time favourite and no 1 vote! 
Love the rich broth, and it was perfect with the standard noodle. 
3 slices of charsiew belly, wood ear fungus, spring onions, and nori.

Tokoyaki 🐙 
Another favourite Japanese side dish with chewy octopus. Delightful! 

I brought my little girl along and I have ordered a bowl of Kids' Ramen for her. 
❤ Kids Tonkotsu Ramen 
Smaller version of the mix Tonkotsu Ramen with option to add Hanjuku egg, corn, or Chashu Belly. 

You can request for your noodle firmness of soft, standard, hard, or extreme.
Broth - light or standard.

Kanadaya outlet located in Marina Square is cozy with warm ambience and we had an enjoyable dining experience! 

Thank you @kanadaya.sg for the invitation and experience. Thank you @mrdidijiak for the makan companion and enjoyable food journey.

🧡 Fragrance 香味 🧡

Received the CNY festive pack from @fragrance_bak_kwa 🧡 I'm truly grateful and felt so appreciated in this food journey. 

One of my favourite all-time zi char dishes is Prawn Rolls (hei zou). Fragrance has got me super excited to try their Bak Kwa Prawn Rolls. 
This is a frozen pack and is easy to prepare as a CNY dish. You can achieve this yummy dish by using an Airfryer or deep fried to golden brown which is around 3 to 4 mins. 

Fragrance 香味 uses the freshest ingredients of minced pork and prawns together with their signature Bak Kwa wrapped with beancurd skin. 

My family really enjoys this dish from @fragrance_bak_kwa 🧡 and I will definitely stock a few packs of Bak Kwa Prawn Rolls in my freezer 💯

Thank you @fragrance_bak_kwa for sending over this CNY care pack to many of the foodies in this community ❤❤❤

🧁 WHIPPLY BREAKS 🧁

!! New HBB offering roll cakes freshly baked on order, prettily packaged in a sleek, minimalistic cake box!! 🎀 

Their thicc roll cakes are 21-23cm long, painstakingly handmade by the talented @whipply.breaks 🧁They come in chocolate, blueberry and matcha mochi flavors, and I personally love how they dont compromise on the taste/quality, despite being not too sweet😚👌 Besides their yummy roll cake selection, @whipply.breaks also makes homemade oatmeal butter cookies 🍪~

~ CHOCOLATE ROLL ($20/roll) ~
Soft, fluffy chocolate cake, liberally slathered with a generous helping of luscious chocolate ganache cream!😻🍫 (swipe for the oOze🤤👌) Light and flavorful, without being too sweet/jelak! Perfect for chocolate lovers who want a less sugary option that will hit the spot equally well😋👍

~ BLUEBERRY ROLL ($20/roll) ~
Fragrant, moist vanilla sponge layered with plenty of light blueberry cream!🍰 The light sweetness of the cream was further enhanced by the pleasant tartness of the homemade blueberry jam😋 Thoroughly impressed by the amount of effort at making the cakes from scratch, and nailing each component at that!💯👏

Thank you @whipply.breaks For the delightful bakes!!🥰 Looking forward to your future creations💐~

🧋 XING FU TANG 🧋

🎉 newly launched Japanese series from Xing Fu Tang’s “Taste the World” campaign, with 3 types of Calpis Sodas and Japanese Milk Teas! 🎏 

~ Hojicha Milk Tea w Matcha Marble Boba ($5.70) ~
Aromatic hojicha coupled with smooth, creamy milk 🥛 Coupled with the QQ matcha marble boba, this concoction is pure genius🤤 packed with rich matcha flavor, the pretty marble-like boba is a must-get for all matcha fans!!🍵

~ Yuzu Calpis Soda ($4.90) ~
from the zesty tang of the fresh yuzu, to the pretty pink aloe jelly, the refreshing Yuzu Calpis Soda is the perfect thirst-quencher in this sweltering heat! 🤩💦 

~ Limited Edition Shiba Inu Plushie ($14.90) ~
this is so adorbs omg🥺💖

thank you @xingfutangsg for the invite💐

description:
🥘 CHEN's MAPO TOFU 🥘

~ Mapo Don ($11.80++) ~

By Chef Chen Kentaro of 2-Michelin-starred restaurant Shisen Hanten, Chen’s Mapo Tofu serves comforting japanese-chinese fusion dishes🥘

Their signature Mapo Don came with a generous helping of mapo tofu heaped upon a bed of hot, fluffy japanese rice🍚🤩 The spicy, flavorful sauce paired perfectly with the soft tofu, coating every single grain of rice with its umami goodness🤤👌 You can even customise the spice level, would recommend level 2 for those with a decent spice tolerance!😋 Loved how fast their service was, we had barely sat down at our table when the food was served😩👏

🍪 @kekoh.sg 🍪

~ CRUNCHY CHOCOLATE CHIP COOKIES ($15) ~
‘These crunchy and caramelised addictive bites with hints of toffee will sweeten the harshest of days and also treat you on good days:)’🍪 these crispy lil bites of joy were ADDICTIVE indeed, it was simply impossible to just stop at 1🥵 (so good that it we wiped it out pretty fast, given how large this bottle was!) Upon opening the jar, the tantalising aroma of freshly baked cookies, infused with hints of toffee is enough to make anyone salivate🤤

~ KOPI SIU DAI ALMOND COOKIES ($12) ~
‘Intense coffee bites with bittersweet notes and almonds for added crunch.’ As a coffee-lover, i thoroughly enjoyed these delicious caffeine-infused treats!☕️ the strong, aromatic coffee paired perfectly with the finely-chopped crunchy almonds for the perfect teatime snack🤩

thank you @kekoh.sg once again for the lovely treats💖

🍫 KEKOH 🍫

~ CHOCOLATE MOUSSE CAKE ~
Made with Valrhona Guanaja 70% dark chocolate, @kekoh.sg definitely does not skimp on quality🤑 From the feuilletine crunch layer, to the velvety chocolate sponge, to the rich chocolate mousse, every layer of this decadent cake was flawlessly executed💯 Topped with a luscious chocolate ganache glaze, this is every chocolate lover’s dream come true😍 Every bite was full of heavenly, chocolatey goodness🍫 可口 indeed!🤤

Thank you @kekoh.sg For the delectable bakes💖 will also be reviewing their delicious cookies soon✨

Calling for all K-foodlovers! 🇰🇷💕 Now you can make this dish at home under 10 minutes and tastes even better than the restaurant one.

Ordered:

1. TOPOKKI
I've had another type of instant rice cake, but this is a good one so far. It's very easy to make and if you love spicy Korean food, you are bound to like this one!

2. RABOKKI 
Rabokki is what happens when you mix tteokbokki with ramen noodles. So if you like tteokbokki (which most people do) and you like ramen noodles (I mean who doesn’t like ramen noodles?)🤔 you will love Rabokki. One of most favourite Korean food. These were delicious. 🤤 As I type this I’m actually craving more. I would definitely buy again!

ps : the sauce is going to appear watery at first , but if you let it sit for a few minutes it thickens up. The taste was amazing , a little spicy so I put some mozzarella cheese which is included in the package too. I definitely recommend !!

Overall rating : 9/10 ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
📌 Available by SHOPEE! Do check them out @koreareaofficial

SANKRANTI
Jewel, Changi
Indian Cuisine from down south, the state of Andhra Pradesh. Usually spicy, this cuisine is full & bursting with southern flavours.  Vegetarian hubby loooves it for the spice, I like the flavours, and always request for lesser spice 😄
We ordered cheese stuffed mushroom kebab and masala papad for starters. The main course was gongura paneer. Gongura is a reddish leavy vegetable popular in central, western and some southern places in India. It has a tangy flavour and is different from most other greens. Also had Lemon Carrot Rasam, southern version of soup, usually made for good digestion. Kadai Veg (mixed vegetable). The rotis were Kasthuri paratha & Lacha (layered) paratha
If you have taste for southern Indian food, you will love this.
$82 for 2 pax
.

The Royal Albatross
Sentosa

23 years of 23rd October!! Married the guy when I was just 24 years old. A marriage full of ups and downs, but never a dull or boring moment 😂😂 Good or bad times, there was always excitement!!
So he booked us a table onboard the Royal Albatross. The dinner cruise, with a three course meal, was my anniversary surprise!
Dinner under the moonlight. The sound of the ocean. 
Singapore coastline lit up with bright lights in the distance. 
We are not the romantic type, so we spoke about work, our children, family ... but it was fun & joy throughout.
The meal was good. 
The service was great.
The staff was very pleasant & friendly.
We started with a mini focaccia & brioche bun, with a fizzy drink. Complimentary!
Appetizer was scallops, main course was chicken, and dessert was cake with ice-cream. The man had pasta because he is vegetarian. 
Its a set menu & all pre-ordered.
But they do have a bar, and you can order drinks if you like.
Expensive, as it works out to about $250 per person (minimum), depending on what package you take.
But this is not about the food, its about the experience. So if you can afford it, its all worth it.
.
.
.
.

Fragrance 香味   |  Crispy Bak Kwa & Almond

Happy Lunar New Year too all my foodie friend and followers! May the new year be filled with love, peace, health and happiness! ❤🍊🧧🎆

J&C Bakery    |   Halal Certified 

Exploring the woodland industrial park area has been a yearly affair for my family to 感染新年气氛。As guilty as I am,  I'm also glad to finally (1st time) grab some freshly made pound cake from J&C Bakery! 

We got the mix box (promo price of $9.80(?) for 16pcs) which consistent of the usual butter, marble, banana & chocolate cake but also more interesting flavours like pandan marble cake & banana almond cake with choco chip 🤤 

This bakery offer other selections like brownie, ondeh cake, cheesecake and puffs too! Best of all it's all halal certified and affordable! Shall be my yearly purchase from now on!👍👍

Co Chung |

Have been wanting to try this place ever since I chanced upon it in Plaza Sing last year! After a long wait, we finally made a trip down last Saturday to get replenish after our donation at bloodbank 😬

We ordered:
- Co Chung Grilled Pork Ribs ($13.50)
- Fresh Spring Rolls ($5.90, 2pcs)
- Crab Paste & Pork Vermicelli Soup ($11.50)
- Vietnamese Mik Coffee ($6.80, Cold)

Overall, we enjoyed the food here especially the pork ribs and bowl of vermicelli! The sauce for the fresh spring roll is unlike the usual ones we had, and not really to our liking - some sort of peppery taste. 
Coffee was potent and carries a great fragrant (note that we are not daily coffee drinkers). The only downside is that the serving were a lil smaller than expected. So be sure to order more sides for sharing when you come! 😅

Fragrance 香味   |  Bawaiian Floss Pizza 

Back with another series of Fragrance's fun meal recipe! This time, we attempted frozen prata pizza with products specially from 香味。 

Ingredients:
- Bak Kwa
- Pork Floss
- Tomato Puree
- Instant Prata
- Capsicum
- Button Mushoom
- Mozzarella Cheese
- Salted Egg Fish Skin (on the side) 

Combine the ingredients and/or other ingredient of choice, baked it in the oven at 200°C for 20minutes. Paired it with Salted Egg Fish Skin for extra dimension of texture 👌 

Once again, impressed by the snacks (especially Salted Egg Fish Skin) by @fragrance_bak_kwa ! Do head over to check out more of their productions and ongoing promotions 👉

KANADA-YA    | 

Our visit to Kanada-Ya boosted our dopamine level and left us with satisfied belly 🥰 

We tried the regular Kotteri Tonkotsu Ramen ($16.90) and Gekikara Ramen ($19.90), and while both broth carried full-bodied flavour and mouthfeel, the latter bring a kick of spiciness which C really enjoyed! 

For the toppings, the charsiew belly has a good ratio of meat-fats but zng up further from the smoky charred-ness. The hanjuku egg was perfectly cooked and has one of the best texture, however, a tad bit sweet. They are also very generous with the spring onions, corn & black fungus which is definitely a plus point! 💯

Other dishes in picture:
- Truffle Ramen ($24.90)
- Gyoza ($5.90)
- Green Tea ($1.90) 

Although this our first time patronising Kanada-Ya, we look forward to being back! It is noteworthy to highlight that they carry vegetarian option (Truffle Veggie Ramen) which broth is made using soy milk and vegetable dashi! Totally caught my eye 🤤 

Lastly, thank you @kanadaya.sg for having us! 🍜

📍Kanada-Ya is located at multiple location such as Marina Sqaure, Paragon, PLQ Mall, Change Alley Mall and Century Square.

Today I’d like to share my simple, fast, and yet delicious recipe. That’s Teriyaki Rice Bowl with Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat. Although it’s plant-based luncheon meat by @yumeat.malaysia, it tastes scrumptious 😋 

Difficulty: Super Easy
Time: 15 mins
Number of servings: 2

Ingredients:
* Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat
* 200g (7oz) Shimeji mushrooms
* Teriyaki Sauce - 2tbsp
* Lettuce leaves
* 2 bowls rice
* 2 half-boiled eggs 

Directions:
1. Dice Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat. Remove the stem of Shimeji mushrooms then cut into bite-size pieces.
2. Heat cooking oil in a frying pan, cook diced Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat until nicely browned.
3. Cook Shimeji mushrooms until coated with oil. Cook together with Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat Season and add Teriyaki sauce.
4. Serve rice in a bowl, place lettuce leaves, put Teriyaki Yumeat Plant-based Luncheon meat, and garnish with boiled eggs.

Do try out the new plant-based luncheon meat by @yumeat.malaysia! You will fall in love with it!

Available: Luncheon, Luncheon Spicy and Minced Meat with Bean Paste, No Preservatives, and Certified Halal!

Come and grab it at Aeon Big, Giant, Hero, Jaya Grocer, Mydin, Village Grocer, Ben Independent Store, and Lotus's!

#veganuary Delicious plant-based Caribbean flavours from @wadalikitchen! ⁣
⁣
[PR sample] I have to say I don’t eat a lot of vegan products but this absolutely blew my mind! Every dish was appetizing and worth eating again! I especially loved their aubergine and mac & cheese. I can’t wait to try it again! All I needed to do was heat them up in the oven and voila! ⁣
⁣
In the box: ⁣
🍽Golden tamarind tofu⁣
🍆Orange & ginger crispy aubergine – the best eggplants I’ve ever had!⁣
🧀Plant-based mac&cheese – the highlight⁣
🍌Fried plantain⁣
🥦Green slaw, coco bread, scotch bonnet salt, escovitch pickle, hot sauce ⁣
🍄Mushroom umami curry (not pictured) ⁣
⁣
Launching in January, Wadadli Kitchen At Home will be a series of limited-edition boxes released every two weeks throughout 2022.  Each edition will have a curated menu by Andi Oliver packed with award -winning Wadadli Kitchen favorites as well as special one-off releases.

RECIPE - BUDAE JIGGAE (KOREAN ARMY STEW)🇰🇷🥢⁣
⁣
Ingredients used in the stew: ⁣⁣⁣
🍖 Spam ⁣⁣⁣
🟨 Tofu ⁣⁣⁣
🐟 Fishcakes ⁣⁣⁣
🌶 3 tbsp of Gochujang paste ⁣⁣⁣
🧂 1 tbsp of Soy sauce ⁣⁣⁣
🧊 1 tbsp of Sugar ⁣⁣⁣
🍜 Ramen noodles ⁣⁣⁣
🧅 Spring onions ⁣⁣⁣
🧀 2 slices of cheese⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Method: ⁣⁣⁣
❀ Fill some water in the pot and bring it to a boil. ⁣⁣⁣
❀ Add gochujang paste, soy sauce and sugar and mix.⁣⁣⁣
❀ Add spam, fishcakes, spring onions and tofu and let them cook. ⁣⁣⁣
❀ Once they are cooked, (spam will need a longer time to cook), throw in your ramen and boil. ⁣⁣⁣
❀ Add in an egg if you wish and voila! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Tag someone who would love this! SAVE & SHARE if you wanna try!😚⁣⁣
